product_title: Omron 7 Series Wireless Wrist Blood Pressure Monitor (Model BP654) Clinically Proven Accurate with Bluetooth Smart Connectivity
review_headline: Finally an accurate BP monitor that works easily accurately and every time!
review_body:
Wanted to take as long as possible to review this because I wanted to take my blood pressure over a series of days and compare it to the blood pressure taken at the two doctor's appointments I had this month. I am happy to report, that the Omron was on par with the manually taken blood pressure at the doctors. The app works great on my Galaxy S5, syncs every time. It was easy to set up, easy to put on, touch of a button and it inflates silently and deflates right away, no long drawn out inflation or long wait for it to deflate. It is telling me that I'm holding my wrist too high, but I'm not and I'm not worried about it, because I have the back up from the doc.

It's small and came in a nice little black plastic case. I just leave it sitting by my recliner so I remember to take it daily. I've had 2 arm BP monitors from Omron, both of which had glitches, one of them right out of the box. I like this one, and for the past month it's worked like a champ.

Pros:
Small
Easy to set up
Easy to sync
Easy to put on
Keeps an accurate record of your BP

You can't really ask for more. So far no cons.

product_title: FemmyCycle Menstrual Cup TEEN Size
review_body:
Ok here is the thing with the Femmycycle.

I have been through the 3 cycles advised and I still haven't managed to have this work for me and here's why...

First off, my cervix dropps and shifts during my "days", making it almost imposible to know where to put the Femmycycle.
Second and worst, my vaginal wall (the front one) swells and enlarges during the second day, making it impossible for the femmycycle to open up. For this reason, I really was about to throw the Femmycycle in the trash because I couldn't figure out why the heck it would leak no matter what I did to insert it right .

I tried all kinds of folds and insertion methods. I even bought both the regular and teen version and nothing. Until I figured out that since my vaginal wall is swollen, there is no space for the femmycyle to open at ALL, because the swollen wall presses on the femmycycle. It will never work for me! This is just my anatomy and there's really nothing I can do about it! And if on top of that my cervix shifts, that makes it even harder! Not to mention that you are totally working in darkness and blind, which makes it impossible for me. It works perfectly the first day because it is not yet swollen, and the last days because the swelling goes down; the rest of the days it doesn't, so it's pointless.

Even though I love the idea of using a menstrual cup, i think I will try a different cup; a normal cup that creates a "seal" and hopefully it will work.

The Femmycycle is definitely not for me. I hope this review helps at least one person. If you are planning to buy this cup I would suggest examining yourself closely during your period, maybe this doesn't happen to everyone, although both things I have read to be normal so you could be one of the unlucky ones.

I still give this cup a 5, because the cup is very well made and I love that it is made of medical silicone so there's no need to boil it. The cup itself is great regardless of my anatomy.

product_title: Convatec DuoDERM CGF Extra Thin Dressing 4"x4"
review_body: When my child crashed her bike at high speed and turned her hip to hamburger, I was at a loss. She was miserable at every bandage change and they all leaked. Until, that is, I turned to some cyclist friends who said duoderm was the only way to go. I researched and then ordered these. The school nurse thought I was crazy, but we couldn't be happier. They stay in place very well without sticking to the wound or damaging the surrounding skin. There is a white ish goo that forms, that tended to leak due to the size of the wound vs bandage, and made the nurse very nervous. She thought it looked like infection.  I stuck to my guns, only having to change the bandages a bit more often than expected, and less than a week out, the wound is healing beautifully. When I say we changed them more than expected, I mean every 12 to 24 hours at first rather than every 4-6 hours with more traditional gauze, but less than the 3-5 days my research promised.  The 4*4 patch was just not big enough to handle it. For two days I staggered 2 patches together and had very good luck. I will keep these in the house from now on. I have no doubt we'll need them.

review_headline: I had multiple people try these pods and everyone loved them. In fact
review_body:

I was very excited to receive this campaign because I have sensitive skin. I have found a detergent that is not scent free and that does not irritate my skin. However, I had to give this a try.
Tide Free and Gentle pods cleaned my muddy sneakers. They also cleaned tough grease and food stains on my kitchen towels and clothes. I was pleasantly surprised after doing the laundry.
The only reason I gave this a 4 star review is the scent free aspect for me. Since I am used to a detergent that has a scent, I missed that clean scent I get when taking out my clothes from the washer.
I had multiple people try these pods and everyone loved them. In fact, they were all using scent-free detergent to begin with and they are now making the switch to Tide Free and Gentle pods.
So if you have sensitive skin and you want your laundry to come out looking extra clean, give this a shot.

product_title: First ResponseÂ® Early Result Pregnancy Test - 3 Tests
review_headline: If you're actually pregnant, you have nothing to fear about this test.
review_body:
Don't be scared by all the negative and mixed reviews of this test... Those were likely done by folks taking the test wrong or who were not pregnant.

I was pregnant and I took this test approximately 4 days before my anticipated missed period. At first I didn't see the line, but my husband noticed it, as it was very very faint. Faint, but turned out to be the first accurate result. I took another one the next day and it was slightly darker. On the day of my missed period, the line was just as dark as the test line.

You'll get a positive pink result if there are HCG levels in your urine... and that means that you're pregnant. Good luck!

product_title: Scrubbing Bubbles  Automatic Shower Cleaner, Starter Kit, 34 Ounce.
review_headline: This product works, but you’ll never know how long
review_body:
So before I purchased this, I read the reviews that said that the cleaner gets wet and doesn’t necessarily last a long time. I also read the many reviews that provided tips on how to keep the cleaner going for a long time, and decided I should risk it. First technique I used, I immediately began storing it upside down as soon as I got it to prevent too much water getting into the mechanisms. I then started taking the batteries out and then air drying it as a preventative measure. With all of this, after just 4 months of use, the shower cleaner died on me. I called SC Johnson, got them on the phone, explained all of the information and then had them send me another one. Ugh, this product works when it works, but you’ll never know how long that will be. Unreliable.

Update: This is an update to this review that I was really wrote unhappily. With a few hacks, I’m now really satisfied with my scrubbing bubbles cleaner, and have had my second version for nearly a year now. Basically, here’s the biggest problem with this cleaner, they advertise it for daily use when it should be advertised for 3-4 times a week use. This makes the cleaner live far longer than if you use it every day. For me, I started using a homemade after shower spray, and I only need to use the shower cleaner every other day if not less. My homemade shower clean is ultra simple, with just citric acid and water. I use one third of my favorite citric acid brand [[ASIN:B00OV8ST8W Citric Acid Powder - Ultra Fine Pure Powdered Crystals - Natural Preservative Food Grade Quality (16 oz)]] and two thirds water. As soon as I hop out of the shower, I just spray lightly for about five seconds and then go on about my day. Every couple days I then use my automatic shower cleaner, and I lie to you not, I only have to scrub my shower once every 8-10 weeks if I do this. I’m a really neat guy, so I like things clean, but really, doing this method I don’t have to scrub nearly as much as I did before. Now, I’m pretty satisfied with the shower cleaner, and I recommend it.retty satisfied with the shower cleaner, and I recommend it.

product_title: Atkins Endulge Treat
review_headline: Contains Malitol -- WILL cause you intestinal distress
review_body:
These are absolutely delicious but if you are on a low carb diet such as keto you should *avoid* as this contains a ton of Malitol, which has about 70% of the GI effect as sugar and will give you intestinal distress. Malitol is generally considered one of the worst sugar alcohols -- which is unfortunate as it is used in many sugar-free products.

Better alternatives will include a sugar alcohol called Erythritol -- which has about 0.2% the GI effect as sugar.

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_headline: A great fitness tracker that's to the point and dependable.
review_body:
After researching fitness wearables, I finally purchases the best one (for me).

With lots of options available in the wearables market, one can get confused with the various brands, options, purposes and prices. Let me explain my thought process, research and what I like and dislike about the Fitbit Charge HR.

I consider myself a fairly active person: I run, bike or lift weights 5-6 days a week. I bought this Fitbit because I wanted to keep track of my steps throughout the day as well as my heart rate. I didn't want anything over complicated or bulky and it had to take the day-to-day abuse in stride. After reading extensively about the Garmin Vivoactive I decided it was a little too much for what I needed. I didn't need the GPS feature because I take my iPhone 6 with me when I run, bike and lift. Also, the Vivoactive had poor reviews with regards to its design and display. The Apple Watch seemed like more of a vanity piece than an actual useful fitness tool. Plus I didn't want to spend $400 on something that didn't even have a GPS option. And the Fitbit Surge was too bulky for daily use, at least for my liking. I purchased the large and it's a great fit for a 5'10", 190 lb adult male. My friend is similar in size as I am and he bought a small and it's rather tight on his wrist.

What I like about the Charge HR:
• It's super comfortable. This was a huge necessity for me because I wear it day and night--except during bathing.
• The battery life is exceptional. I've used it 5 days without charging it. Mind you, 5 days is what Fitbit claims. Many people have complained online about the battery life. The solution is to turn of "all day sync" on your phone and computer. Just sync it a few times a day.
• It's accurate and gets better with time. The more I wear it the more it adjusts to my movements. The heart rate monitor was a little off at first but it's very accurate after two weeks of use. I've compared it to a Polar monitor and it's very close. This thing is perfect for tracking my heart rate while running and biking. Plus it tells my what my resting heart rate is all day and night.
• Checking my steps and time on the fly is easy. All I have to do is raise my wrist and it displays my preferred display and the same is true with the tapping feature.
• The caller ID feature is great. I don't always have my phone with me at work or home. Having the ability to be notified of a call is super useful.
• It charges fast. It takes about 2 hours to charge if it's almost dead. I charge mine little by little each day. I keep the charger in my bathroom and plug it in when I'm in the shower. That way I never worry about it going dead.
• The fitness tracking options are nice. I can either use the device to track my runs, the Fitbit app, Endomondo or Strava. There are more but those are my preferred. The other fitness apps sync nicely with Fitbit's.
• The Fitbit app is great. I track all of my activity and food. I was using Myfitness pal and LoseIt prior but have now deleted them and solely use Fitbit. I also disconnected my other apps from the Apple Health app. I don't like its UI anyway, Fitbit is much better.
• Competitive features. I love being able to connect with friends and family to compete in step challenges. They really do motivate you--it all depends on the other people involved.

What I dislike:
• This is cliche but the charging cable is short. I connected a USB extension to it so my problem is solved.
• I wish I could sync my calendar notifications with it but this is so minor and it will probably be supported with an update eventually.
• Limited colors. They are releasing a blue option soon.

As you can see, I didn't have much to complain about. I've been wearing this thing 7 days a week and it hasn't bothered me a bit. Just buy one and start moving!d it to a Polar monitor and it's very close. This thing is perfect for tracking my heart rate while running and biking. Plus it tells my what my resting heart rate is all day and night.
• Checking my steps and time on the fly is easy. All I have to do is raise my wrist and it displays my preferred display and the same is true with the tapping feature.
• The caller ID feature is great. I don't always have my phone with me at work or home. Having the ability to be notified of a call is super useful.
• It charges fast. It takes about 2 hours to charge if it's almost dead. I charge mine little by little each day. I keep the charger in my bathroom and plug it in when I'm in the shower. That way I never worry about it going dead.
• The fitness tracking options are nice. I can either use the device to track my runs, the Fitbit app, Endomondo or Strava. There are more but those are my preferred. The other fitness apps sync nicely with Fitbit's.
• The Fitbit app is great. I track all of my activity and food. I was using Myfitness pal and LoseIt prior but have now deleted them and solely use Fitbit. I also disconnected my other apps from the Apple Health app. I don't like its UI anyway, Fitbit is much better.
• Competitive features. I love being able to connect with friends and family to compete in step challenges. They really do motivate you--it all depends on the other people involved.

What I dislike:
• This is cliche but the charging cable is short. I connected a USB extension to it so my problem is solved.
• I wish I could sync my calendar notifications with it but this is so minor and it will probably be supported with an update eventually.
• Limited colors. They are releasing a blue option soon.

As you can see, I didn't have much to complain about. I've been wearing this thing 7 days a week and it hasn't bothered me a bit. Just buy one and start moving!

review_body: My friend's mom got me into essential oils and I needed a diffuser. Without hesitating, I got on Amazon and picked this one first because of the reviews and second because it has a nice design unlike some of the other diffusers on here. The blue light is a really nice touch but if it's on your nightstand, it will probably be distracting if you're trying to sleep due to it's brightness. I noticed in other reviews people were saying that there is no way to operate the diffuser without the light which is not true at all, one push of the button turns the diffuser on along with the light and another push of the button turns the light off while continuing to run the diffuser. Another feature I really like about this diffuser is that it has an auto shut off once it runs out of water which really helps with the life of the diffuser as well as energy. Overall, this is a great diffuser if you're new to essential oils like me or you're much more advanced. I would recommend this InstaNatural diffuser to anyone.

product_title: Bausch & Lomb Magna Visor with Lens Set
review_body:
Like so many, the expectation of Bausch & Lomb would have quality stamped all over it. The plastic (that's right, I said "plastic") lenses will probably find a shelf life of 6 months tops. There is really no go instructions for removable and changing. Don't bother going to the B&L web site. I think you would stand a chance of a rhesus monkey giving you better tips on lens changing. There is a tab in the upper left corner marked "b". I've come to the conclusion that this means break here.

There is one thing I can say in favor and that is about the adjustable head band. With my noggin being the size on an over ripe Casaba melon, there does stand the need of comfort, and this does meet the criteria intended.

I think what bugs me most is the fact that nearly all reviews for the Magna Visor orbit around 1, there seems a great need in the B&L company to listen to the people. When the people have spoken, and the leaders don't listen . . . well it can just be a terrible mess. Just like other things.

When this breaks all 3 lenses, I am going to take the advice of another reader and opt for the product of which company's name begins with a "D" as they seem to be well satisfied.

product_title: Best Health Shield (Compare to Thieves Oil by Young Living, Four Thieves by Eden’s Garden) 100% Pure, Therapeutic Grade Essential Oil Blend
review_headline: it smelled like walking into a room of Vicks Vaporub
review_body:
Let me get the first item out of the way. I did receive this item for free in order to test the product.

This oil comes in a 10ml amber glass bottle. There is a European Dropper Cap included. The product is rated as 100% organic pure therapeutic grade essential oil. The ingredients are Cinnamon, Clove, Eucalyptus, Lemon and Rosemary oils. The product is made by Health Solutions in Scottsdale, AZ.

When I first opened this bottle, it smelled like walking into a room of Vicks Vaporub. That is exactly what it smells like. Just like you use Vicks to open your nose when you have a cold, this oil does the same thing. You can pick out the clove scent. I used this oil to dab a drop on my nose before I went to bed and I dabbed it on my nose before I went to work in the morning.

I had a bad case of Bronchitis back in June and I don't want to repeat it. Two of my co-workers came down with Bronchitis within the last two weeks. Just to make sure I did not get sick, I dabbed it on my nose before I went to work. So far, so good. It does give me a level of comfort that I would not have without this product. I do not detect any harshness to the smell. No alcohol or chemicals. The smell does not linger long. Once I dab my finger in the oil, I cannot smell it in the air after about one hour. I have to put my finger to my nose to smell it. However, I can smell it if I put my finger to my nose for a good 8 hours.

The oil has a very fresh, light and effervescent smell. This would work great in a diffuser. I would highly recommend this product. I was pleasantly surprised and I will purchase it on my own.

review_headline: Just started the treatment today, and already am super excited about how it feels!
review_body:
I'll probably give this a 5 stars when I've finished the treatment. I've been struggling a lot lately to find something that works. All Dr. prescribed stuff was a no-go, and have mostly relied on using garlic cloves as a suppository, which has worked wonders thus far. That is until this last one hit. I switched around my birth control and I think it made my vagina really confused.

So far, these suppositories are the first real relief I've felt in 3 weeks. I'm usually very aware of how I'm feeling internally, especially when it comes to candida. I can tell pretty easily that it's starting or that the remedy I'm using is working. And these already are working way better than the Dr. prescribed pills.

Definitely refrigerate them, though, before using, cuz I smushed one trying to open it. Noob problems. I also eat a yogurt high in probiotics from a middle-eastern market nearly every day, drink kombucha as often as i can (not too keen on the sugar in it though, but hey), try to drink lots of lemon-water and eat ginger as often as I can. None of this has worked exceedingly well on its own, but has helped to maintain it from getting too bad. Today, though, I also just bought goat-milk keifer, AND garlic pills to take while i'm on my period (garlic cloves and DivaCups don't quite work well together).

So far, I'm super satisfied with the relief these are giving me. We'll see, but I'm pretty sure these are awesome.

product_title: Natural Detox Tea Powder | Matcha Green Tea + Yerba Mate + Milk Thistle + Spirulina + Coconut Water + Cinnamon + Ginger | Health Cleanse Drink Mix Supplement | 30 Servings
review_headline: Quality liver cleansing supplement with caffeine inside
review_body: I really enjoy their brainiac product and decided to give this a try. I bought more as a "fancy milk thistle extract + fillers" supplement than actually as a green tea supplement. Milk thistle extract is one of the main ingredients in most liver cleaning or detox supplements. I am certainly say this product does help promote regular bowel movements and probably help boost your immune system. Around 80 mg of natural caffeine from the matcha green tea and yerba mate is present in each serving to give you a boost of energy as well. At 1 dollar per serving for a month supply it is similarly priced compared to other popular liver supplements which are usually 23 to 30 dollars for a month supply. The main difference between this and most other liver supplements is this is a powder as opposed to capsules and this does goes with caffeine inside. Those who are just looking for a green tea supplement can certainly find better quality certified organic green tea for much less and those who want the VERY BEST (from an ingredients standpoint) liver supplement can also find better, though in that vein this is a good quality product. The tea aspect of this product should be thought of as just an alternative to capsules this really is just a quality liver support supplement that happens to contain some caffeine and its drink flavor is matcha green tea.

product_title: Facial Moisturizer, Organic and 100% Natural Face Moisturizing Cream for Sensitive, Oily or Severely Dry Skin - Anti-Aging and Anti-Wrinkle, for Women and Men. By Christina Moss Naturals.
review_headline: Great for skin suffering from adult acne and dryness caused by benzoyl peroxide
review_body:
UPDATE:
I eventually went to a dermatologist and got a prescription which healed my acne. Since then I have tried other moisturizers and BB creams because I still do not love the smell of this stuff. But after using other products for a few months I stumbled across my old tub of this and used it again one night. It felt so wonderful and my skin looked so plump and smooth and hydrated the next morning. I still haven't found a moisturizer that my skin loves as much as this stuff. And if I use this with [[ASIN:B00FYI6VCO E.l.f. Acne Fighting Foundation Ivory, 1.21 Fluid Ounce]] it looks like I'm not wearing makeup at all and just have perfectly smooth clear skin. I cannot recommend this moisturizer enough.

ORIGINAL REVIEW:
I have been battling an awful attack of adult acne. I looked like my face had been drug across gravel. It was so red and swollen it almost looked like an open wound. I've been using benzoyl peroxide which has been helping A LOT. However it makes me look like a reptile shedding its skin. Given the choice between looking like a mummy from the crypt or having swollen red painful clusters of cysts I'd choose the mummy. But I didn't want to just give up and accept my flaky fate. My regular moisturizer wasn't doing much to help with the dryness. I tried a few others but some were super heavy and oily, others did nothing, some moisturized but aggravated the acne. This has been the best I've found so far!

While the lotion is nice and light it does leave a slightly oily sheen on my face which isn't optimal. But if I use a setting powder on top of my makeup it helps soak up the excess oil (although later in the day I start to look oily again). I also found that if I apply this first then the benzoyl peroxide cream it isn't quite as drying, but still fights the acne. I know everyone says to do the benzoyl peroxide cream first, but after months of doing it that way then months of doing it my way, I think putting the moisturizer on first is not only fine but preferable for my skin.

This smells like licorice or anise. At first I hated that but now I'm used to it... and even kind of like it now. The packaging made me think it would smell like lavender. Just a head's up, it doesn't! And while I'm OK with the smell.... I'd still prefer a different scent. The scent does wear away pretty quickly. As soon as I'm done getting ready in the morning the scent has already worn off. Also, scent isn't as important as the healing properties.

So the pros are that it really helps moisturize my poor acne-laden skin and is nice and light and feels really good and is quite healing. The downsides are the slightly oily sheen left after massaging it in, and the smell isn't ideal. Overall, the pros DEFINITELY outweigh the cons. I can deal with an oily look and temporary scent to get the benefits of having a moisturized healed face.eferable for my skin. This smells like licorice or anise. At first I hated that but now I'm used to it... and even kind of like it now. The packaging made me think it would smell like lavender. Just a head's up, it doesn't! And while I'm OK with the smell.... I'd still prefer a different scent. The scent does wear away pretty quickly. As soon as I'm done getting ready in the morning the scent has already worn off. Also, scent isn't as important as the healing properties. So the pros are that it really helps moisturize my poor acne-laden skin and is nice and light and feels really good and is quite healing. The downsides are the slightly oily sheen left after massaging it in, and the smell isn't ideal. Overall, the pros DEFINITELY outweigh the cons. I can deal with an oily look and temporary scent to get the benefits of having a moisturized healed face.

product_title: NatureWise CLA 1250 Softgels, 1000 mg
review_body: I've been using the product for three weeks and noticed a visible difference in my stomach at the end of the first week. The difference is only in my stomach, below the belly button, not in my hips or anything like that, but that's okay, because it's doing exactly what NatureWise promises. In the interest of full disclosure, I want to say that I also take a fish oil supplement, Vitamin C, B6, and a multi-vitamin. I'm not sure if any of those help,but I do know that I didn't see a positive difference in my body until I started taking the CLA. I've only gone to the gym twice in the last 3 weeks and my eating habits have been atrocious, so exercise and a healthful diet are obviously not factors in my progress. I can't imagine what would've happened had I been behaving myself. Also, I haven't experienced any side effects, which is as it should be since CLA is a natural fatty acid. Last but not least, NatureWise is sending me a free bottle for providing this review. I think it's important to say that nobody at the company tried to influence the content of my feedback. They're very friendly and helpful. I'm looking forward to receiving the next bottle.

Stevia is a very healthy and great tasting alternative and natural sweetener but extremely hard to find in current products and if the so-called health food companies would just use it, then it could be called healthy. Also, Saccharin is a very good sweetener that has been given a bad rap for years by the FDA for supposedly causing cancer but has never been proven. I have used "Sweet & Low" daily for over 35 years in my coffee, tea, cereal, etc. and have had virtually no reactions ever and am cancer free! Other countries don't want America's health foods because of the awful, unhealthy ingredients. The FDA should demand that products containing splenda and nutrasweet have bold lettering on the package warning consumers. Shame on atkins. Thanks

product_title: Finish Dishwasher Cleaner, 8.45 Ounce (Pack of 2)
review_headline: The only dishwasher cleaner I'll ever buy
review_body:
This stuff is awesome. I ran out of my usual detergent and picked up the Target brand dishwasher detergent (I think it's called Up & Up?) while shopping for my kids' school clothes. BIG mistake. I always put essentially clean dishes in my 1.5 year old Bosch dishwasher--I rinse and scrape down the dishes pretty well before they go in--but the Target detergent caused them to come out slightly sticky and covered in water stains, and I'd have to hand wash them AGAIN. After 2 weeks of this nonsense, I threw away the rest of the Target detergent and switched back to my usual brand (Cascade), but the results were the same for the next week. I was convinced that awful detergent ruined my dishwasher. After reading a ton of reviews on the Finish and Jet Dry Dishwasher Cleaner product, I figured I'd give it the old college try and hope for the best.

Wow. Just... wow. It's like a new dishwasher. I'm throwing caution to the wind and not even scraping all the cheese off my plates and they're coming out sparkling clean. I LOVE this stuff and will recommend it to anyone and everyone who uses their dishwasher on a daily basis.

5 stars!!!

product_title: Ankle Foot Orthosis
review_body:
I'm not sure how to rate this. It's a comfortable brace with relatively weak support. I wear heavier custom AFOs but sometimes, I've found off the shelf braces are more comfortable. This was more comfortable but I need more lift/strength. I have CMT and very little strength, my foot drop is significant.
Update: March 1, 2016
I bought the large brace even though my footsize dictates a medium brace. The result is a longer footplate and a taller brace. It is remarkably better. The brace is still thin and if I flex my foot too far forward (by accident, e.g., getting into my car) the dorsiflex snaps the brace. I have grown to appreciate its comfort even though it's not strong enough for my foot drop. If they made the exact same model with a thicker polypropylene, it would be a lifesaver. I hope you're reading Elite-Ortho.

Given how comfortable I've been, I'll actually keep buying a replacement and trying to be more careful not to snap it.

product_title: CLEAR CARE Cleaning & Disinfection Solution with Lens Case, 12-Ounces
review_body:
I was diagnosed with Giant Papillary Conjunctivitis (GPC) from overuse of my contacts and "poor hygiene".

For years I had been using Alcon's Opti-Free contact solution and it was great until I started getting lazy with the rubbing part. I never reused my solution and always rinsed my case out. But after several years I started pouring new solution in and simply dropping my contacts in it after every use. Never thought skipping the rubbing part would cause so much harm.

Since switching to Clear Care I haven't had any issues. My lenses feel cleaner and more comfortable throughout the day and during my last optometry appointment I was told my GPC has resolved completely.
I still avoid wearing contacts whenever I can but at a -7.00 that's a bit hard to accomplish.

Definitely recommend buying. Just make sure you allow enough time for the solution to neutralize otherwise yoyre in for some serious stinging.

review_headline: Even more annoying was that it was not sensitive to small changes ...
review_body:
Accuracy is questionable and precision is non existent. I purchased to use to weigh for athletic competition where we have to make specific weight classes. The scale I got was nearly two pounds off my actual weight, as measured by a certified scale. Even more annoying was that it was not sensitive to small changes in weight. It showed that I weighed the same just out of the shower (but dry), in underwear, and finally wearing a sweatshirt. Finally when I put on jeans, the scale showed I weighed two pounds more. In short, it is completely insensitive to small changes in weight and thus useless for my purposes.

I had hoped that this scale would be better than my fifteen year old model that is on the verge of dying, but still gives accurate readings. I was disappointed. Perhaps technology is better now in some home devices, but clearly not in this case.

review_body: I bought this for my parents, both 55 years old, who were advised by their doctor to start monitoring their blood pressure. The machine is super easy to use, just plug in the cuff to the machine and you're ready to go.  As long as the cuff is placed appropriately and is tight enough, it does not over squeeze your arm, which is a complaint my mother had with the last cuff we bought at Costco. I do not remember the brand of this previous cuff, but it looked very similar and was approximately $35.  It seems to give consistent readings (blood pressure is the same in both arms when tested) and it is generally consistent. I cannot attest as to whether or not it reads irregular heart beats, as it has never shown up in our use in the last three months. No complaints for the battery life, as we use this machine almost daily and have not had to change the batteries yet. Overall, worth the money and easy to use.

product_title: BulkSupplements Pure L-Ornithine HCL Powder
review_body:
I received a 100g bag of L-Ornithine HCL powder after ordering a small bag of Hyaluronic Acid, in exchange for a review...

I have not had much chance to actually use the product thus far, but I have used many Bulk Supplements products in the past, and as far as I can tell this is up to their usual standard. The packaging is excellent, with no compromises and straightforward labeling. The bag I got also has an expiration date of May 20, 2016 so I should be able to use it all by then. It is important to take into account when ordering large quantities from bulk companies that the expiration dates are often quite close to when you will receive them, so the most efficient way to utilize them would probably be to share them with others if possible.

The main thing I have noted about this product is it has quite a strong bitter taste to it, comparable to the powdered caffeine I have tried. For this reason it is best either packed into capsules or mixed in with some kind of strong citrus drink for quick consumption, not mixed in with something you plan to consume at a leisurely pace.

While I cannot speak to its effectiveness as of yet (my homemade preworkout cocktail contains a laundry list of various suppliments, all from Bulk Suppliments) I have thus far not seen anything to make me question its quality. Four stars simply because I cannot be entirely certain what its effect is, if any, due to my method of taking it.

product_title: GermGuardian AC5300B Elite 3-in-1 Air Cleaning System with True HEPA Filter, UV-C Sanitizer, Allergen and Odor Reduction, 28-Inch Air Purifier
review_headline: Great Air Purifier for the price
review_body:
We love the GermGuardian brand and we own 6 units, from very small plug units to the large ones like this Elite 3-in-1. I also have owned several very expensive air purifiers. Here's what I like about this one:

This is an improvement over the older large unit that we own in that it's very quiet, takes up a little less space, and is sleeker looking.

- One of the things I like about GermGuardian is that it has they UV-C light that kills airborne mold spores, viruses, bacteria and germs. We live in Florida and the air here is humid, so there are a lot of mold spores in the air. I feel this really helps. It's also great when one of us is sick. I feel it can help cut down on the transmission of a virus or infection in the home. It also removes dust, dirt, smoke, etc. We get the occasional everglades fire out here in the dry season and it gets smokey, so that will be very helpful.

- The 3 speeds are great. The lowest speed is ultra quiet, and we use that speed at night.

- The UV light can be turned off at night so the unit doesn't give off any light.

- There's a little light that will go on when the HEPA filter needs to be replaced. That's very convenient. It's also great that there's only one filter that needs replacing, and that's only needed every 6-8 months approximately.

- The charcoal filter removes household odors well. The only issue with this unit, and the reason why I've given it 4 stars instead of 5, is that it's still giving off a very mild smell which I think is from the charcoal, even after using it for a couple weeks. I suspect this will diminish further over time.

So I'm happy with this unit and would recommend it. It's an effective air purifier for the price.

review_body:
I've been taking the CLA for 8 weeks now and I am very happy with the results.

Coincidentally and unfortunately i had fractured my foot a day before i got the CLA and had to stop all my normal activity, daily gym classes, as well as pretty much anything that required walking and moving around… My foot wasn’t healing after 3 weeks so i ended up basically on my couch for 5 weeks.

After 5 weeks without my workout routine and even normal moving around, i haven’t gained any weight, i actually lost some, while eating as usual. I lost basically all my muscle from that one leg out of its immobility, but the rest of my body seemed to be able to keep the muscle it had built up, or at least most of it. I believe this was due to me taking CLA regularly throughout that time. I was taking 4 pills a day, 2 during urge day and 2 at night.

Thank you NatureWise!

Stevia is a very healthy and great tasting alternative and natural sweetener but extremely hard to find in current products and if the so-called health food companies would just use it, then it could be called healthy. Also, Saccharin is a very good sweetener that has been given a bad rap for years by the FDA for supposedly causing cancer but has never been proven. I have used "Sweet & Low" daily for over 35 years in my coffee, tea, cereal, etc. and have had virtually no reactions ever and am cancer free! Other countries don't want America's health foods because of the awful, unhealthy ingredients. The FDA should demand that products containing splenda and nutrasweet have bold lettering on the package warning consumers. Shame on atkins. Thanks

product_title: Salon Sundry Portable Electric Hair Removal Hot Wax Warmer
review_headline: Shuts on and off before it gets hot to melt.
review_body: The wax does not melt. If you put it at the highest temp, even with a half full wax pot, it heats up half way, and then shuts off, before it gets close to getting to the right consistency. product_title: WanLiu TSD Revolutionary Anti Snoring Tongue Device Transparent Medical Silicone Sleep Apnea Aid Stop Snore Tongue Retainer Soft Sleeve
review_body:
I tested two tongue stabilization devices (TSD) to see how they work - one based on the Good Morning Snore design, and one based on the Aveo TSD design. I used a SnoreClock app on my phone to record noise all night to see if there was any snoring. This generic is based on the Aveo TSD design, and it was the clear winner. It resulted in zero snoring all night. The 'bulb' section is big enough to hold a decent amount of your tongue forward, and it's easy enough to customize how much by choosing how much vacuum to use. The bulb provides suction at many levels, depending how much it's squeezed, but even the lightest is enough to prevent pop-offs over the night, so you can find a comfortable amount to use. The 'flange' that goes across your teeth is well sized and comfortable between the teeth and lips. The 'V' groove goes under the tongue to accommodate the tongue web. In the morning, there might be some minor swelling of the tongue depending on the amount of vacuum, but it subsides very quickly. To release the suction, you press on the sides of the bulb. My only recommendation is to take it out of your mouth over a sink instead of your pillow for drool control.

Please note: TSDs will only work for mouth/tongue snorers, not nasal snorers, and it won't help obstructive sleep apnea. To figure out which kind you are, here's a link: http://www.withoutsnoring.com/determine-why-you-snore-easy-tests-you-can-do-alone/

product_title: Nerium EHT
review_body: I began taking EHT daily when it was first released several months ago.  So far I have noticed no real improvement in either my memory or overall energy level.  I plan to continue taking it for a few more months because I really would like to believe that it helps.  I noted NO adverse side effects, however my main concern is that EHT has never been tested on humans (only studies presently available were on laboratory rats).  I was taught that in order to scientifically prove the efficacy of any medication or supplement, a double-blind study with a significant number of subjects should be run.  The study should also be replicable and peer reviewed.  I realize that since EHT is being sold as a supplement, the testing requirements are much less stringent than for pharmaceuticals, but in order to avoid the "placebo effect", more study should be done with human subjects, especially considering the monthly cost of this supplement.  The jury is "still out" for me!

product_title: Essencell Menstrual Cramp relief Patch
review_headline: I am so glad to have found these heat therapy cramp patches
review_body:
I am so glad to have found these heat therapy cramp patches. They are super easy to use, just open the package, take off the sticky back paper and place on the outside of your underwear. It isn't supposed to go right on the skin and I wondered if it would work well through my undies and it really does and it lasts hours. It does start slow so my suggestion is to use them soon as you think the cramps might get bad. The heat goes on and on though and it really does get hot. I found myself pealing it off and using it on the outside of my shirt for back pain relief and then moving back to the prime cramp area. I wish it was larger though.

I plan to get these for my daughters Moon Box as she is a teen and I think responsible enough to handle this. The packaging warns it could burn so keep that in mind and don't sleep with it on! So far these have not burned at all, just comforting pain relief!

I received this product in exchange for my honest opinion.

review_body:

I keep frozen concentrates of grape juice around. Two teaspoons of undiluted concentrate mixed with a capful of minerals works just fine for bypassing the horrible metallic taste.
I bought this when I learned you cannot overdose on plant derived minerals.
Also, I learned that minerals are even more important than vitamins because vitamins can't work properly without minerals. I had heard that our soils are depleted now.
I wasn't happy with a couple of things in the ingredients so I gave it four stars.
The testimonials convinced me to give it a try. It is definetly helping my joint pain.
The first day I had a bizzare symptom. The ever present ringing in my ears became louder than ever!
Then with each passing day it subsided and now the ringing in my ears, which had been there so long, is cured.
Is it the minerals, or perhaps the minerals allowed the vitamins to work properly?
I don't know. But I will continue to take these minerals.

With \\"Ultimate Gum Solution,\\" I'm a little more confident and less fearful about the results of my next visit. While the ingredients listed in the product description seem rather conventional, I suspect the gentleman who formulated this stuff has some \\"secret sauce\\" which takes care of the bacteria that gunk between my teeth. Indeed the mult-page document that accompanies this product boldly makes that claim.

I say that because....hey...I'll admit to only flossing 3 or 4 times a week. If you're cringing because you're even lazier than I am, then you might want to check this out.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Surprisingly Gentle Unlike Some Mouthwashes
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I've been using this stuff every day for about week.. The effect of using it is supposed to be that it kills off the bacteria that causes receding gums and tooth decay. Unlike mouthwashes like Listerine which pretty much NUKE your mouth with antibacterial compounds like Thymol...which burn like crazy -- this takes a different approach.

On my first user, I was bracing myself for some kind of burning sensation when I first put this into my mouth, but instead, felt and tasted like Jolly Rancher candy that had dissolved in my mouth. Per the instructions, I distributed it around my teeth and then let it swirl around in mouth for a few minutes and just basically swallowed it thereafter.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Very Unscientific Way I Convinced Myself This Works
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
But, honestly, does it work? Well I did an experiment. First of all, let's establish the baseline. When you floss your teeth, there's smell that emerges that smells somewhat like barf. Some might say poop, but to me it's closer to barf. I used this for a couple days WITHOUT FLOSSING. Then on the 3rd day, I flossed and behold, there arise no barf smell from between my teeth. In fact, no smell whatsoever. I was just as much surprised as you probably are, but I'm not kidding. Hopeful, someone out there can replicate these same results.

But for me, it's doing something that no mouthwash, ultrasonic toothbrush or flossing gadget has ever down, i.e. gotten rid of the smell between my teeth with a floss. That is certainly encouraging.

Got this at no cost for unbiased review.

review_headline: Stops snoring, but it will move your teeth
review_body: I tried a lot of stuff before that didn't work, but this actually stopped the snoring. The only problem with this is the process which you mold it. You heat it, bite into it, and then let it cool. The problem is once it cools, the actual mold is smaller than when you originally molded it by biting into it. So the net result is you have this mouth guard that works a lot like a retainer and will start moving your teeth to fit into the shrunken mold. I tried it for a couple days, the snoring stopped, but my teeth hurt so I had to stop using it.

review_headline: Gives my daughter a rash on her lower back
review_body: I wish I could give these diapers a zero rating. Ive been buying huggies for my daughter since she was born..I would typically buy them from the pharmacy so when I signed up for Amazon prime and saw that I could get them a few bucks cheaper and the convenience of being delivered to me i went ahead and signed up for a subscription. Now when I recieved my order I saw noticed that it came in a Amazon box instead of a huggies box but I didn't make a big deal about it. The first night I noticed that my daughter had developed tiny red bumps on her lower back where it has the little folds in the middle of the diaper. That's never happened before so I thought it could've been a minor irritations rom something else so I put a bit of a&d and continued to use the diapers and monitor it.  After a few days she was scratching and very uncomfortable and the rash was huge and it covered the entire lower back area of my baby girl. I heard some rumors about fiber glass being found on some of the huggies products and that was causing rashes and normally I wouldn't really believe that but now I don't know what to think! I called Amazon to complain and they are issuing me a refund but this is completely unacceptable on huggies behalf! Hope this review helps and informs u moms and dads out there.

product_title: Ms Energy Super Weight Loss Blend - Pure Garcinia Cambogia Raspberry Ketones Green Coffee Bean Extract Complex Plus Premium Natural Fat Burners Formula - Lose Weight with Best Complete Weight Loss Supplements That Works Fast for Women - Extreme Diet Pills Product - 60 Capsules
review_body:
This supplement is packed full of well-known ingredients known for aiding in weight loss, such as Pure Garcinia Cambogia, Raspberry Ketones, and Green Coffee Bean Extract. I started taking this supplement around a week ago, and even though I haven't noticed any weight loss, I have noticed some beneficial effects. Like the name of the supplement, I feel like Ms. Energy throughout the whole day without those well known jitters some supplements can give you. I have also noticed a decrease in my appetite that occurs at meal time. These benefits are coming from these lovely little capsules that have no aftertaste and are very easy to swallow even though they are a tad on the larger side when it comes to size.

One bottle of this supplement can last anywhere from almost 7 to 20 days depending on recommended dosage you decide to go with. I started off with 1 pill, 3 times daily and that amount seems to be working well for me so far. I wish each bottle included 90 pills, since that would give you a 10-30 day supply, which is a nice even amount of capsules. If you take the full dosage each day, this can end up being a VERY pricey product and may not be affordable for everyone. The amount of pills needed per day seems excessive and is one of the key reasons why I can't give this product a full 5-stars.

I have been really enjoying this product and I hope to continue seeing beneficial effects from this supplement. I did receive this product at a discount in exchange for an honest, unbiased review. This review is a reflection of my personal experience with this product.

review_body:
My wife and I get on this elixir at the first sign of of cold or flu symptoms. It may be useful as a flu/cold seasonal immune booster even before symptoms show up but I've not used it in that way previously.

It has a bitter initial taste but isn't terrible, I take a swallow of tart cherry juice immediately following to mask flavor. My wife actually doesn't mind it...it's a personal preference obviously.

We start feeling better within 24 hours and have had complete elimination of symptoms in 2-4 days typically. Shop your local health food or vitamin shop to see if the price is similar to here if you need it ASAP. I've found it priced around $20 locally in the past.

It says on the bottle to use within 45 days of opening. That is quirky since it can knock out symptoms in a fraction of that time so your conflicted between taking it regularly to meet the 45 day deadline even though you're symptom free...only to not have any left should symptoms return months later and you've got to purchase another bottle.

Anyway, what is feeling better quickly worth to you? Highly recommend you give it a try.

product_title: Pure Copper Magnetic Therapy Bracelet - For Arthritis and Carpal Tunnel Pain Relief - Copper Bracelet for Women & Men
review_body:
I don't know if I believe the claims about therapeutic magnets. Some people swear by them, but I cannot vouch whether they're objectively any better than placebos. That said, if you believe the anecdotes, this attractive copper cuff makes both a good-looking accessory and a potentially useful alternative medicine aide.

It's made of a single piece of copper, designed to be opened by gently bending the metal apart by hand, then gently bending it closed around your wrist. The metal is soft enough to be malleable, yet resilient enough that I've worn it out biking or pulling weeds, and it's stayed firmly in place and resisted ordinary wear and tear. All that is to say, it's workable, but durable.

The magnets are placed just right to fit over your pulse points. (Also, if I remember some of my charts, it also corresponds with certain chi lines, but that's really outside my expertise.) Again, I don't know if I believe magnets have medicinal qualities, but I have found wearing this, particularly after a stressful workday, very cooling and relaxing.

Also, it comes in an attractive dark-navy velour gift bag, perfect for storage or for giving as a gift. So, if you want a good-looking accessory that doubles as alternative medicine, or if you just want something that takes a little edge off physical stress and hard work, maybe give this piece a try. I've had good experiences with it, and I'm a cynical skeptic. If you believe, maybe it'll do even better.

product_title: AirTamer A302 - World's Best Portable Travel Air Purifier Negative Ion Generator Virus Dust Protection
review_body:
Unfortunately, airlines have banned these because of the lithium batteries. Seems silly to me since they allow cell phones and computers on flight. But these, no way. Double standard.

I love mine. We are currently in fire season in Eastern WA (August 2015) and it is especially bad. The smoke is so thick sometimes that just looking across my backyard it is hazy. Some times the house smells like a campfire inside and that is with a hospital grade NEW A/C filter and other room filters running. On one of the worst days I was wearing my Airtamer and I was feeling some effects from the smoke. I thought it wasn't doing me any good so I shut it off and put it away. With in half an hour I was in much worse shape. I put it back on and began to feel better. When the smoke is that heavy, it has a hard time keeping up, but does more good than you think it is doing. I also find that when we leave the valley, if I don't wear my Airtamer, when get over the pass my throat clogs up so badly sometimes I can hardly talk. Not so with my Airtamer. Great little product! My daughter has one and I'm considering buying two more of them for my son and husband for the next round of smoke headed our way.

review_headline: they look like regular old black socks
review_body:
These socks arrived safely packed in its own little box, inside a larger Amazon box. Upon first appearance, they look like regular old black socks, but when you put them on, you can feel the difference.

My husband has been dealing with a combination of problems, a bit of sciatic nerve issues, coupled with a sore hip and plantar fasciitis. He is never comfortable and always in pain. I actually bought these for MYSELF because I'm slowly getting back into running, but he asked if he could try them out, thinking that maybe a little compression might help alleviate some of his pain.

He wore these socks for 24 hours straight and actually believes that they lessened his sciatic pain a little. The run pretty true to size and they seem to be made of a high-quality material.

All in all I believe these socks are a good value--and my husband has told me that I need to get another pair for me. I received these socks at a discount in order for an honest review.

product_title: Thyroid Support Supplement - #1 Premium Formula to Boost Metabolism, Support Weight Loss, Increase Energy & Focus - with Iodine (Kelp), Zinc, L-Tyrosine, Ashwagandha, Vitamin B12 - 60 Capsules
review_body:
I have been using this product for the past week and am truly amazed at the difference in energy and overall mood I'm feeling. After giving birth to my daughter little over 2 years ago I've noticed that my energy level has dropped considerably. Also, no matter what I was doing (changing my diet, going to the gym, etc.), my weight was not dropping. I was constantly tiered, felt like there was a little fog over my mind, I had mood swings, and I was desperate for some kind of answers to why I'm feeling this way. I did some research and everything was pointing to my thyroid (or the lack of it functioning). I went to my doctor to have my thyroid levels checked, but even though the levels were low, they fell within normal scale so no medication was prescribed. I was hoping that there is something out there on the market that will help with thyroid function and I came across this product. I've read the ingredient list and I like that it has zero fillers and artificial binders, is made is USA in an FDA Registered facility, and bears Good Manufacturing Practice Quality Product Seal. After using this product the first day I noticed that my thinking was much clearer (no more foggy feelings) and I had more energy throughout the day - I only took 1 pill the first day as I was not sure how my body was going to react to it. The second day I took 2 pills as recommended - 1 pill in the morning and 1 in the evening. I was so surprised at the level of energy I felt, I was able to make breakfast, clean up, take my baby to the park, cook dinner, clean up some more, and I was not even tiered by the time 6 P.M. came - usually by that time I'm on my 3rd cup of coffee just so I have energy to finish my day. (* Just a disclaimer - I did have coffee in the morning as well). Now I have been taking these pills for the past week and I AM SO HAPPY that I took a chance on them. I am finally starting to feel like my old self again and am very excited to report that I even lost 2 lbs (I don't know if that's related to this product but I sure am glad to finally see the scale going down after two long years of it climbing up). Overall I highly recommend these pills to anyone who suspects that they have an under active thyroid, so far it has made a world of difference to me and it might be able to help you as well. The only thing that I would change about this product, is the top cap. It doesn't have a child-proof top (very easy to open). This might not be important to many people, but as a mother, I would love for this company to change the cap to a child-proof one.

*This product was received in exchange for my honest opinion.don't know if that's related to this product but I sure am glad to finally see the scale going down after two long years of it climbing up). product_title: Philips Wake-Up Light with Sunrise Simulation alarm clock and Sunset Fading Night Light, White HF3510
review_headline: One of my best investments ever!
review_body:
I purchased one of the HF-3510 wake up light clocks and I can definitively say it is the best money I have spent in a long time. I have to wake up at 6:00 AM every morning. For all of last year, I would go through the day tired and falling asleep with barely any productivity. I just had a regular alarm and it was clearly not working. Eventually, I made the decision to try out the wake up light. I woke up after the first night of using it with almost no grogginess. I actually felt like I slept well! I went through the day without falling asleep at all. For the first time in a very long time I was actually make it through the whole morning feeling perky and alert.
Pros

Small, easy to fit on my night stand
Easy to use interface
Sleep mode
Radio

Cons

No possibility to plug in aux port for my phone or iPod
Only has 3 wake up sounds, (again I could have it play music with my iPod)
Doesn't get great radio reception

I would strongly recommend this alarm clock to anyone who wants to feel great.

product_title: Depend Real Fit Underwear for Men Maximum Absorbency Economy Plus Pack
review_headline: Effective, Comfy and Costly: A few tips as well
review_body:
Okay, "I love it" it's not something I would say about diapers at my age, but it is the most comfortable with the best control for active wear. I'm not talking about running a marathon here, just going shopping to meetings etc. At home and at night regular depends are fine and cheaper.

Having just had radical prostectomy incontinence is a major problem. I have tried these, Depends and Prevail (in descending cost order and in descending preference.)

With practically no control to begin with I would go through 10-15 pair a day. That's more than I care to pay. With my PT's recommendation I put guards inside the full diaper (yes folks, a rose is a rose) and changed those out 3 or 4 times to keep the cost down. That works. This product is absolutely amazing! I would have never believed the effectiveness of this massager if I had not experienced it myself. product_title: SinuPulse SinuAir powder irrigation solution, 300g bottle.
review_body:
Bought this with a SinuPulse nasal irrigation unit (read Water Pik). Issue I have with the powder is that it appears to have a lot of insoluble contaminants in it. I use two small spoons (about 2.8 gr) of mix to about 220 cc DI water for a nasal rinse, and there is always undissolved debris in the solution, and the solution is cloudy. Even if heated, there are still solids undissolved. Not a good sign of high quality.

So I began mixing my own solutions using Morton Sea salt and USP sodium bicarbonate, and the solutions are always crystal clear. I also add aloe vera juice, xylitol, GSE, and Pau D'Arco and the solution is much more effective than this SinuPulse mix. The complex mix lasts for 8-10 hours and keeps my sinus clear without need for Nasal Sprays. With the SinuPulse mix I barely got a few hours before my symptoms would return, and sometimes I would plug up right away after treatment.

I guess if you only have very mild issues this may work OK. But try the other products with Xylitol and aloe, and you will probably find they work a lot better. If you just need saline, get yourself some Sea Salt and food grade Sodium Bicarbonate. It will work the same and is a lot cheaper than this stuff, and probably a lot purer.

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_headline: was so excited . . . and then reality hit
review_body: I had my Fitbit Charge HR for a few months when a very hard hike in the Kentucky mountains killed the side button.  Miraculously, the unit's tracking functions still worked, even if the display didn't, and Fitbit customer service worked with me to figure out what had gone wrong.  When nothing we tried worked, they sent me a new one.  It was the most pleasant customer service experience I've ever had.  More than that, I love my Fitbit.  I do challenges with my friends, am more aware of how active I am, and at one point was actually able to lose a decent amount of weight with the Fitbit in conjunction with MyFitnessPal (which I also highly recommend!).  I got the HR specifically for the heart rate tracking, as most of my exercise these days is on the bike (which is hard to quantify with the other Fitbits).  It uses my measured heart rate to calculate my calories burned and seems to be doing a great job at it.  LOVE, LOVE, LOVE my Fitbit Charge HR.    Update:  I got a new tracker after the aforementioned breakdown, but within a year that one, too, went to hell.  Band started bubbling, the back plastic charge cover literally just fell off, and it would only charge spottily.  I did wear it every day, but I never immersed it in water or anything else too weird.  All I did was sweat in it (something that a FITNESS tracker should be able to deal with), and the unit disintegrated.  Although my replacement didn't last a full year, the warranty only covers the original purchase, so I've been left out in the cold on this one.  Not super happy with FitBit at the moment.  I get that they can't just continually replace messed up replacement trackers, but neither of mine lasted EVEN A YEAR.  It's so aggravating.  Make your product to do what it's supposed to do, and don't use sub-par materials that can't hold up. It's simple. For over a hundred bucks, this little baby should be the s***.  Instead it's just crap.    Also, a note on the calorie counting.  I believe full-heartedly that the trackers overestimated calories burned, so you need to be REALLY, REALLY conservative when trying to use that count to lose weight.    Overall, after more than a year of using the Fitbit, I like the Fitbit software and all the little graphs and parameter tracking you can do, but I'm finding myself unwilling to buy another tracker for 125$ bucks that I'll have to replace in less than a year. There has to be a better one out there without such shoddy construction.

review_body:

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_body:
This is my third fitbit and my first HR model. I gave my first one as a present, and then lost my second fitbit, so I decided to upgrade to the HR and I'm very happy I did. There's something about knowing how far I actually walk that inspires me to walk further(to get my 10,000 daily steps). The heart monitor is a revelation to me. I average between 64-72 beats per minute and have recorded 149 beats while running up a steep hill. I'm not sure what the best average is, but it's fun seeing my heart beats go up and down(I like to check when I'm around certain people to see if they stress me or not).

I bought the plum colored one and after a black fitbit, and a blue one, I really enjoy this color. There's no rhyme or reason, but looking at it is nice. Another reason I like the fitbit is because it tells you how many calories I burn, which has been a revelation to me that working out is not a good way to lose a few pounds. I burn far less than I think I do, so exercise for me has become about staying in shape and being healthy, rather than as a weight loss plan.

I like the buckle better than the way my other fitbit fastened, and I believe I lost it because when I took off my coat while running, I pulled the fitbit off and didn't realize it. But, I enjoy having a fitbit so much, I bought another one. So far it's sweat proof, and fits well and comfortably. I bought the small size because I have really slender wrists and I still wear it on the third hole of the buckle. I'm not sure the small would fit a medium wrist. It's pretty small.

I use the watch on the fitbit because I don't wear my watch while running, I love the calorie counter, the stair counter a little(which is kind of useless in a way because it records the three steps on our boat as a staircase), the calorie counter, and especially the heart monitor. I even put it on my husband and was happy to see that my pulse was lower. Fun device.

product_title: 3-Point Products Oval-8 Finger Splint Graduated Sets
review_headline: Made a huge difference with a trigger finger
review_body:
My husband has had 5 trigger finger surgeries. When he began having symptoms on a sixth finger, I started looking for something to keep him comfortable (especially at night) until he got around to having the surgery. After several weeks of wearing this splint full time, his symptoms have lessened significantly. He now wears the splint at night and during the day only if he is going to engage in a n activity that would be taxing to that hand.

There is a lot of good information on the Oval-8 web site. I recommend perusing that.

The only negative comment I have is that the sizing instructions didn't work for us and we had to return the first splint because it was too small to get past my husband's knuckle. It should be noted that after wearing the splint full time for a while, he was able to use a smaller size. You can buy single sizes or a set of three sizes.

Also, he kept losing the splints at first - probably because he kept taking it off during the day. When he decided to get serious about wearing it full time, he used a small piece of adhesive tape to keep it securely on his finger. That made a huge difference.

This is a great product and, so far, has kept my husband from having to go under the knife again.

product_title: Pregnitude Reproductive Support Dietary Supplement 60 packets
review_body: I received my Pregnitude faster than expected! I have gone through one box of it. I brought it to help regulate my periods. I do NOT have PCOS. I am 28 years old and 300 lbs. I have had a history of irregular periods and prolonged bleeding that started from my very first period as a young girl. I was not treated until I was 18 years old, and the treatment was always the same: Birth control. I have been on birth control on and off since then. Any time I would get off birth control my periods would revert to the prolonged and heavy bleeding that would last for weeks and weeks. I started to wonder what long term use of the hormones were doing to my body, I started wondering why my body would not have normal periods without birth control. Every single doctor blamed my weight and said in order for me to get any relief I would need birth control until I lost some weight and see if that helped once I got off birth control. I started to get frustrated and do my own research to see what causes prolonged bleeding and found that a hormone imbalance could be the culprit. I am married now and my husband and I are also ready for a baby but how could I think about getting pregnant if I can't even have a normal period? I ordered Pregnitude and also bought a bottle of Vitex chasteberry. I started taking both twice daily. Morning and night. My last birth control pill was in July. My first day of taking the Pregnitude and Vitex was August 3rd. Since then I have had two normal periods, lasting 5 days each! I couldn't believe it, I have never ever in my life had normal periods without birth control. I have also been walking an hour about 4 or 5 times a week. Eating a little better, drinking lots of water. I am so excited, even though I haven't gotten pregnant I know that with normal periods I am ovulating regularly. I just ordered my second box, I hope the results stay the same and who knows, I may be getting my baby soon :)

review_body: I received this yesterday and ordered it specifically for cleaning my sewing machine. There are a lot of small tight areas inside the machine where lint accumulates and can cost hundreds to repair. So I needed tweezers that were very thin at the tip. These did not disappoint. They come in a clear vinyl case with a snap flap to hold them in. Each had a plastic cover or band for protecting the tip. The tips are sharp so the plastic covers are a bonus. These are stainless steel so they are non-magnetic, great for computerized areas. The tweezer grips are wide so you don't have to fumble with it. One is a forceps tweezer that can be used for holding something round such as beads, wires, etc. That one has a band that holds it due to the shape. I had one plastic cover missing when I got it but that was easily remedied with a pencil eraser. All-in-all this is a great set and well worth the price. If you need tweezers for specialty purposes, this is what you need. As a bonus, these would also be the best tweezers for removing splinters too. Don't hesitate.

review_headline: Tough bristles - good for detangling but bad for sensitive scalps
review_body:
Decent brush with one minor issue:

Pros:
- Staggered bristles help to actually detangle hair
- Tough bristles actually detangle hair

Cons:
- The handle is slippery and the ergonomically inclined shape actually makes it difficult to hold on to
- The same tough bristles, while working great on long hair, are very uncomfortable if used on the scalp

Overall, it does its job of detangling extremely well, but if you have a super sensitive scalp, then you might want to seriously reconsider this purchase.

review_headline: Your neck will be firmer. I love this.
review_body: I love cremes just for the neck, that's usually where women REALLY show their age. I got the chance to receive this product as a free sample to get my honest and unbiased feedback. product_title: Wahl 97788-100 Hot and Cold Vibrating Therapeutic Massage Gel Pack
review_headline: Nice features, but isnt an ideal design
review_body:
The idea behind it is good, but there are some flaws I thought this German product would have figured out before going to market.

The dual hot/cold use is nice. That works well, but unfortunately it takes hours to get cold enough to feel so it's hard to do repetitive alteration of hot/cold therapy. I'm gonna get a bag of frozen peas to alternate heat with this device and cold with peas.

Second, one side is soft and cozy with the plastic pouch for the vibrating disc between the 2 soft ends. The other side is not as soft. In order to use the elastic strap and velcro it on, you need to use the not so soft side against your skin.

Third, I bought this from a different retailer for immediate relief of the most painful stiff neck Ice ever had from sleeping on bad pillows. Thought the massage would help, but it is too strong for my neck with it already being in pain. On day 2, with my neck a lil better, it wasn't quite as bad, but it's not a variable speed. Maybe it's not so bad for other parts of the body that hurt.

I'll likely return this. Too expensive for not being able to use its key features in an ideal way. Will buy a microwaveable gel pack, and maybe a second or frozen peas to freeze to alternate hot/cold therapy.

product_title: Jumbl™ Rechargeable Oral Irrigator & High Capacity Water Flosser Featuring 3 Operating Modes – Includes 2 Interchangeable Precision Nozzles, Mini Funnel for Water Filling & Rubber Water Plug for Charging Pins – White
review_body: Love this product. Really powerful for such a small item. Much better than the well-known "brand name" that I've used a few times. This is way better. Company was courteous.  **UPDATE**10/8/15 The flosser is not charging after use. I put the charger back in the flosser as soon as I'm done with it and it should blink 3 times and then stop, meaning it's fully charged. Now it just keeps blinking. It's because the water/foam gets into the 2 holes where the charging plug fits. This happens with all water flossers but I've never had one stop charging because of it. Not a good feature. You really have to dry it out and keep plugging/unplugging and keeping your fingers crossed, basically. It's not gonna last much longer. For a few $$ more, you can get something good, sturdy and reliable.  **UPDATE**2/29/16 Just threw it out. The flimsy rubber push button to start the thing stopped working. All of a sudden, it turned on after a while. Today, it didn't start at all. I think 6-mos., even for a cheaper product like this, is not worth the time or money. And this is more mid-range so I think it should have lasted a lot longer. Please note, it's been "acting up" since my last review so technically it's not been prerforming properly since then.

review_headline: Love the Zip, hate that I need to purchase the clip over and over
review_body: I see many reviews here saying the same thing, so I'm just adding my voice to the list of disgruntled FitBit Zip owners. I love my Zip because I don't want to wear a fitness tracker on my wrist, but it's a shame FitBit doesn't design a better product. The first two Zips I owned got lost because the clip failed and the tracker got lost. (To their credit, FitBit did replace them both for free.) It's been awhile since I've lost one, but this is the second clip I've had to purchase in the last four months because the plastic tip at the end broke off. I'm glad I can get them on Amazon (free shipping - yay, Prime!) but am really annoyed that I keep having to replace them. Maybe the Zip is just a loss leader for FitBit and they make all their money on us buying these stupid clips - just like how printers are really cheap but the ink is so expensive. Hmmmm...

product_title: Greenwave Dirty Electricity Filters: Mobile Travel Kit (2 filters)
review_headline: Don't put it in the bathroom
review_body: We put this in the bathroom to see what it would do in a small space. It may be a coincidence, but within three weeks our toilet tank filled up with rust and iron, and clogged the fill valve in the tank.  We have other toilets and this only happened in the tank near the filter, (about 4 feet away). Until we know more about how this works, and the mechanics of the filters, we will not use them. When I mentioned this to someone who works with electricity, they said that there may be a magnetic component that pulls rust and iron out of the pipes. Since the pipes are only a few years old, it would have to be the city pipes.  This doesn't say much for our city water delivery system.

product_title: BiC Soleil Glow Razors - 3 ct
review_body: I recently received this product free through BzzAgent and BIC to try. I absolutely LOVE these razors! I have always used the plain ol' gillette double blade razors, and i must say....i don't think i will ever go back to those!! I am so used to feeling the friction and hair pull of those razors, that when i didn't feel that, or anything really, i thought well surely these aren't doing their job. Boy, was i wrong! I felt the area i just shaved and it was super smooth!! The razor just glides over the skin, so much so you can barely feel it. Afterward my legs were super smooth and soft with no irritation! The handles are great, and easy to hold, not too thick, not too thin. My one and only complaints are that because of the rather large head it is a little difficult to get in those little areas such as the bikini line or the under arms, and that its rather difficult to shave the rounded areas like over the knees and around the ankles. I had to go very slow around these areas to avoid skinning myself. All in all though, i do really like these razors and would recommend them to everyone.

review_headline: My go-to for tummy troubles but has many other uses as well!
review_body: As a mom to multiple kiddos with acid reflux and other tummy troubles, I have been using ginger in other forms for years now so I decided it's time to give the essential oil a try! The Cielune Ginger essential oil is incredibly potent - the knock your socks off if you open the bottle and take a big whiff of it like I did kind of potent (so breathe gently!)! In the world of essential oils though, potent is a very good thing! I love mixing this with a carrier oil (fractionated coconut oil or sweet almond oil are fantastic choices) and a few drops of peppermint to rub on an aching stomach! Ginger works remarkably well for motion sickness, nausea and even vomiting. This Ginger oil would also blend very well with eucalyptus or thyme oil to make a powerful expectorant! Just dilute with a carrier oil and rub on the chest or put in a diffuser to quiet coughs and ease congestion! Ginger oil has terrific mental health benefits and can relieve depression, stress, exhaustion, dizziness, restlessness and anxiety as well! Personally, I am not a huge fan of the Ginger scent, but fortunately, it does blend very well blends well with many other essential oils including lemon, lime, eucalyptus, frankincense, geranium, rosemary, sandalwood, patchouli, bergamot, orange and ylang-ylang, and you get the extra health benefits from those oils as well! I purchased my first bottle during a limited promotional period at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I am very happy with the quality of the Cielune oils and I would order this oil again!
