product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_body:
You know, I really do love my Fitbit HR. When you walk it's accurate, and I love the HR part, accurate too. My favorite part is tracking workouts. So, what do I HATE about it? One major thing!

It tracks steps for me when driving. I got mine in May, and a few months later went on a long car drive (4 hours). I left work with 3,500 steps, which is right and normal. Well, 3 hours into my drive it vibrates that I'd hit 10,000! Ummmm, it counted about 6,500 steps while I was sedately driving. So then I started paying attention to my 25-minute work commute. Guess what? Yep, counted 500 steps+ in that amount of time. And no, mine is not a 4-wheeler on rough country roads. It's a Toyota on the interstate.

LONG story short, I contacted them about this. They gave me the run-around for about 4 emails, quite unhelpful. Finally send me a new one because they admitted mine was "defective." The new one is much better, but it was still counting steps, albeit only like 100. Still not supposed to do that, but whatever. Well, randomly checked my 25-minute commute this morning. Shocked to see it picked up 500 steps again.

Now, if I sit it snugly in my cupholder it barely picks up steps, but it's a pain in the butt to remember this. Just a friendly warning. If you drive a lot, beware of this! I don't think all of them do this (my fiance has the same model and his only picks up minor amounts of steps aka normal).

What they need to do is have the ability for us to turn our Fitbit HR's on and off. That would completely solve this for me. If there was a button on mine to turn it off, I would do so while driving. Voila, problem solved. Then I would give this a 9/10 for sure.

Just a friendly warning. This is a very frustrating thing.

review_body: I love my DivaCup! Best thing ever! I used to get really bad cramps in my back, butt, and legs wearing tampons and pads. Since I've been using the DivaCup I haven't had any cramps! It definitely took one cycle to get used to inserting it but now it's so easy, and I can't feel it when it's in. So comfortable! I had an early miscarriage a few months back and the diva cup made it much easier to handle! No leaks, I just emptied it a bit more than usual. I'm usually very regular and start using it as soon as I see spotting. I would suggest getting the specially formulated soap because they don't recommend using anything else and I like to wash thoroughly after ever cycle and pour boiling water over it. product_title: Uricel the #1 Uric Acid Lowering Formula | High Potency Key Ingredients Designed to Lower Uric Acid, Relieve Gout Pain, Reduce Gout Swelling and Prevent Gout Attacks
review_body:
I have suffered from gout for over 10 years. A few years ago the attacks were less frequent. In the last year they became more frequent, and more severely painful. It is always best to watch one’s diet. Armed with the Uricel treatment plan has been an excellent approach to help support my management of Uric acid.

Eating meat without knowing where it comes from or how it was cooked should always raise the need for caution. Recently I had eaten short ribs that were previously cooked and frozen. I thought it would be OK, but in the end it turned out to be one of worst gout attacks that I have ever experienced. Uricel helped me recover within 4 days.

About 3 weeks later ....I was feeling so good that I immediately thought I could run at 60+ years of age, and I was truly not being very realistic. Additionally, I dropped my guard and went off a low purine diet, and suffered another attack. Once again Uricel helped me to recover from this attack.

Today I stay on Uricel, and continue watching what I eat. But, I need to realize and remain watchful, as my gout had reached a point of becoming more frequent. I will continue on Uricel, but I cannot be so egocentric to think I can conquer this alone, so I advocate using all resources available.

product_title: Jakemans Anise Throat & Chest Lozenge Box, 24 counts
review_body:
I'm a recent convert to Jakemans. Previously, I had relied on Ricola's herbal drops to get the job done, but our local supermarket was out of stock. Seeing these on the shelf, I figured "why not?" and bought a box. Wow, are they powerful! First of all, they taste like black licorice. Now, I'm a black licorice kind of guy, so that worked just right for me. If you don't like black licorice, you'll probably want to choose something else, because these are *strong*.

Not 30 seconds in, I can already feel my nose opening up, and the pain in my throat subsiding. Inside of a minute, all I can taste and smell is mentholated black licorice. For the next 15 minutes, there's not a cough to be had, and it lasts for a few hours afterward before the coughing returns, so it's nice that they last a while, too.

These are so worth the price. I recommend you pick up a box whether you have a scratchy throat, or can't stop coughing. These lozenges will fix that problem quickly, and they taste really good, too!

product_title: Natrol Biotin
review_body:
As I've gotten older, I've noticed that my nails have become much weaker than they were previously - they're thin, overly flexible, and prone to cracking and flaking. I have tried strengthening nail polishes and treatments such as [[ASIN:B000EGIEX0 Nutra Nail Green Tea Nail Strengthener -- 0.5 oz]], and while they seem to work insofar as my nails "feel" better after having used them, I wasn't 100% convinced that they were actually doing anything - moreover, it took time to apply the treatment each day, which I often would forget to do.

I wasn't sure about the hype surrounding biotin, but the price for this bottle was right so I thought I'd give it a shot. I was shocked when within days of taking it my nails felt considerably stronger. I was sure it had to be a placebo effect, but after a few weeks my nails were a length they hadn't been in years and there was no flaking to speak of. I went on vacation and forgot to bring the biotin with me - sure enough, within another couple of weeks my nails were back to their old flaky selves. There was no real change in my routine other than stopping the biotin.

I would caution that my hair has always been thick and grown very quickly, so I can't speak as to whether biotin has any effect on that front. I also didn't notice any drastic change in my skin, but I don't have too many issues with that either. However, if just for the effect on my nails, I will continue taking biotin - it definitely works for me.

product_title: Vamousse Head Lice Treatment Homeopathic 6 fl oz
review_body:
My daughter recently had lice- not sure how long she had it before we realized it! We purchased the vamousse treatment and it has seemed to work. I treated her at night, and when she woke in the morning we treated her again. We found about 6 live in her hair. Everyday since the treatment I have been examining her hair. Day 2- I pulled 18 eggs, Day 3- i pulled out 25 eggs, Day 4- down to 5 and Day 5- Down to 3. They appear to be dead (farther from the scalp and white/silver when the light hits them). I will be following up with a second full treatment today- just to be sure we got everything. I will continue to look in her hair probably for at least another 2 weeks. (if you miss one- the cycle starts again). In addition- we all have been using the vamousse preventative shampoo and will for the next 2 weeks. No one else in the family seems to have been affected- just my daughter. The comb that comes with it only helped during the initial treatment. I have just been sectioning her hair off and going a few strands at a time to find everything. Those things are hard to come off and would slip right through the comb provided.

Overall- pretty satisfied!

review_headline: Vitamins aren't supposed to taste good. However
review_body:
I do not understand why the adults who are reviewing this as ADULTS care so much if these are palatable. Vitamins aren't supposed to taste good. However, the taste and texture of these are tolerable, which by vitamin standards, is not bad.

Like many people, I eat these as a grown woman because of recurring problems with iron and calcium deficiency that result from being an athlete. I loathe taking iron pills because quite frankly, they are nasty and it disincentivizes me from taking them on a regular basis. But voila, mask the gross iron taste with some chemicals (it's really not that much, it's literally less asparatame and coloring than a piece of gum...) and we're back on the road to recovery.

Highly recommend these for those struggling with the female athlete triad.

product_title: Luvs Diapers sz 1, 264 ct (Old Version)
review_headline: so I feel bad for giving such a crappy review but I am ...
review_body:
I know that every baby is different, so I feel bad for giving such a crappy review but I am basing this of my own personal experience.

I received a package of Luvs newborn diapers from a coworker who was also pregnant, she was ten weeks ahead of me. After her baby shower she "gifted" me a pack of Luvs, and although I feel that it was a regift that she didn't want I took them anyways because this was my first child and I didn't know what to expect our what would work.

When my son quickly went through ALL of the huggies, and the pampers, I pulled out this pack of Luvs and tried them out. First I'd like to say that the design was cute enough, but I hated that there was no wetness indicator like the blue line that appears on the huggies and pampers brands. So to a brand new parent that was a pain.

But I could get over all of that if the brand could save me some money so I continued to put my son in these diapers. A few days after getting home from the hospital we ran out of formula and my milk supply wasn't that great. We tried two new things that day Luvs and Enfamil. Within a day my son had little red bumps around his butt "exit" and I instantly knew it was a diaper rash. I stopped using the formula and the luvs. The formula I tossed the luvs I kept for a rainy day. Well yesterday SAS the rainy day when I ran out of pampers and decided to put my son in luvs within 24 hrs my son had a diaper rash cropping up on his butt again, so my husband and I took the test of the pack of Luvs and gave them to a coworker to try.

I will never put my kid in luvs ever again, Idk why he gets a rash wearing luvs but we have tried honest, pampers, and huggies and luvs was the only brand that gave him a diaper rash and horrible red lines on his hips and across his belly.

product_title: Fitbit Charge Wireless Activity Wristband
review_headline: To begin with I'm fairly active but I have a dad bid as I love to eat and drink
review_body:
So I usually don't write very long reviews but I thought I had to review this.

To begin with I'm fairly active but I have a dad bid as I love to eat and drink. I wanted something to remind me to walk more and take more stairs during the day. I got the sizing from a Best Buy then ordered it through Amazon at it's almost $20 cheaper.

Pros:
1. Was easy to set up.
2. Came almost fully charged.
3. Was able to fit comfortably around my wrist with all the slots.
4. Seem to count walking strides pretty well.

Cons.
1. I almost lost it on the second day as it is ridiculously easy for the clasp to come loose. It came loose under my pillow while taking a nap (I didn't realize this until later) in my hotel room. So I tried syncing it to see if it was still in the room as I had no idea where it was. It kept saying it could not find the tracker. Looked all over the hotel room, then retraced my steps down to the car park hoping I would find it. Luckily it got discovered later that day after much moping around thinking about how I had just lost $100+. I'm fully expecting this to get lost in the next few months.
2. Not sure how accurate the flights are but I know I'm walking more flights than its logging. Maybe it counts a minimum height or stairs for a flight.

Mainly it gets a 2 star as I'm sure it will come off in the next month or so.

product_title: Aveeno Baby Wash and Shampoo
review_headline: Not my first choice in baby shampoo
review_body:
I bought this because I read it's a good idea to wash your dogs in the baby shampoo you plan to bathe your baby in. The baby shampoo doesn't work that well for pets.

My concerns were if it wasn't cleaning my 15lb mutt, how well is this thing cleaning my baby? So I tested it. I washed my hair and my body with this thing for a week straight (generally once to twice a day). I don't blow dry my hair or anything, it goes into a bun for work every day. I'm pretty clean except for when I go to the gym.

I liked that it's super gentle! I started washing my face with it because it was definitely soft and feels nice when It's lathered. However, it did dry my face and body out. It even dried out my hair. At the end of the week, I had to go get a leave-in conditioner treatment. I'm not sure I'd want to use this for my baby but if the main concern is stinging the eyes or things like that, this is a great product!

And it's completely oderless which is a good thing! But I kind of want my baby to have a mild scent from the bath... but that's just my personal preference!

product_title: Malem Ultimate Bedwetting Enuresis Alarm
review_headline: After visiting our pediatrician who recommended this for a good 2 years
review_body: OK so... I have a child with a bed-wetting issue, let me clarify. HAD a bed wetting issue. I did a lot of research before buying this product. After visiting our pediatrician who recommended this for a good 2 years, and then eventually seeing a urologist, who also said its the best product out there, I finally bought one. This came after me waiting for the issue to clear itself up on its own, thinking my child would eventually outgrow the problem and, well,  that never happened. I was also hesitant because my child is an EXTREMELY sounds sleeper (this will come into play later). So I took the plunge and paid the $100. Best money ever spent.  BUT- I need to let other parents know something. And its kind of funny, kind of not funny, I wish some of the other reviewers mentioned this. The reason this product works is because of conditioning. It conditions the child to eventually recognize a full bladder and then either hold their urine or wake up to relieve themselves. And the conditioning happens because of the alarm. Imagine sleeping soundly and peacefully and being woken by a shrill, very loud alarm along with vibrations. I'm actually surprised my kid didn't start s***ting his pants instead of peeing them. Poor kid was torn out of a deep sleep and would have the most frightened look, it was horrible. The first couple of times it was torturous. Then, like a miracle unfolding, the bed wetting just stopped. Stopped. And my child stopped wearing the alarm. So, in conclusion it works by scaring the bejesus out of your kid.  If you are OK with torturing you wee loved one, then I say go for it. The product most definitely gets the job done!! Certainly worth every dime this cheap mom paid for it!!  We are in counseling now to cure him pf PTSD. Just kidding....it works, just be warned.

review_headline: Kept my ankles from swelling during a long summer trip.
review_body: I ordered this for a long trip we took last week.  My ankles often swell when traveling, especially in hot weather.  These prevented any swelling and look fairly decent.  They are heavier and more opaque than regular knee high stockings but are a good color for me and don't look "medical" under capris.  I was very self conscious about wearing heavy black or white compression socks.  These worked just as well for me and were much more comfortable.  The band around the top was not uncomfortable to me at all and that is usually an issue for me.  At first I thought they were too long, but I took them off and didn't pull them up as tightly, fitting the band just below my knee and they worked fine.  The open toe feels a little weird at first, but I soon got accustomed to that and I think it makes the stockings feel a little cooler.  I did wear no show socks over these in my tennis shoes because my shoes were slipping with just the stockings and they felt fine.  I wore them all day for three different days, hand washing them each evening and they still look pretty good.  I will order an additional pair before we travel again because these were really good for me.

product_title: Magicfly Multifunction Microfiber Cleaning Cloth for Stainless Steel Appliances Glass Window Cleaning Cloths Blue(pack of 5)- 30*30cm
review_body:
I've always used microfiber cloths on the car, motorcycle, and Vespa Scooter. I never knew they could be used indoors to clean stainless steel appliances and windows/mirrors.

I wanted to see how tough these cloths were so I looked for the dirtiest mirror in the house. I took it outside so I could get a good picture with natural sunlight. I wiped it down with only warm water. Then dried it off with another Magicfly cloth. The outcome was great! I've never seen my nieces mirror that clean.

Then I looked for the dirtiest stainless steel appliance in my kitchen. This happened to be the kettle we use everyday. Again I wiped it down with warm water and finished it off with a clean cloth. The outcome was pretty amazing.

I've found the best way to clean/wash microfiber clothes is to simply wash them right after you use them. By adding a little detergent in a bowl, letting them sit for 5-10 minutes. Move them around so the dirt comes off. Rinse them off. Air dry and their good as new!

These microfiber cloths are great, I'll definitely be using them indoors. I also love the fact that you don't have to use any harmful chemicals or cleaners with them. Just use warm water and your good to go. I received this product in exchange for my honest opinion.

Magicfly Microfiber Cloths
-durable
-5 pack
-no chemicals needed
-simply use warm water
-cleans mirrors
-cleans windows
-cleans stainless steel

product_title: Yoga Fuel - Energy to maximize your yoga practice - Strength and endurance when you need it - Electrolytes for peak performance - Increase stamina for Bikram, Ashtanga, Vinyasa, Iyengar, Power & Hatha - Highest quality natural performance supplement.
review_headline: Great for Sustaining Energy if You Feel Tired
review_body:
[[VIDEOID:ebf9325c1567767ca5bf274bbe86e303]] Pros:
- Has small amounts of Energy
- Will not make you jittery
- Helps you sustain through a workout
- Helps you keep important vitamins while sweating

Cons:
- Minimal energy amounts
- Large pills, must take 2-3
- Small effects

So I like to do yoga and I tend to not have problems sustaining energy throughout my routine so maybe this product was not for me. I was hoping this product would help me push my limits a little bit further but that is not the case.

You must take about 3 pills 20-30 before your workout. This is easy if you have a set routine.

The pills themselves have fairly little amounts of the key vitamins it contains. It has B12 in 50 MCG but you can easily find B12 in 5000 MCG. This may give you a small and almost unnoticeable amount of energy so you will not feel any jitters.

It tries to explain some of the key ingredients on the label but never actually tells you how they help you just lets you know they have been used for hundreds of years. This actually really bothers me as I feel like it can be completely excluded from the packaging all together.

Overall I feel that if you have a routine set or have a bit of trouble making it all the way through a routine, maybe heavier people or beginners, this product may be a good investment. As for me it seems unneeded as it gives little help and I don't always sweat much during my normal routine. I can see it being better for hot yoga which sadly I do not have the option for. I will be giving this to my boyfriend who has trouble getting through simple routines so he can keep up with me.

I give it four stars while as the concept is okay their is such little value of vitamins that it would be better to take these vitamins outside of this pill like the B12 if you need energy.

I got this product at a complimentary discount for my honest and unbiased review.review.

product_title: Doctor Danielle Turmeric Curcumin with Bioperine (120 Capsules)
review_body: I have been taking this for several months and have suffered no ill effects.  It's tough to gauge the effectiveness as I'm taking this preventatively, but I have no negatives to report thus far.  I lost both my mom and my brother to pancreatic cancer and I've been told that Curcumin may have a place in the fight against this horrible disease. I attended a pancreatic cancer symposium, and a Dr. from UCLA recommended Curcumin as part of the treatment against PC,  so I decided to take this as part of my daily routine (couldn't hurt, right? =)  Per Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center, "Curcumin, a curcuminoid, has shown biological activity in pancreatic cancer patients and there are ongoing studies to test its effect as an addition to current cancer treatment." That's definitely enough for me to add to my daily routine. I tried a different brand when I ran out and just went back to Dr. Danielle's.  I can tell you that Brand X smelled just like a processed vitamin and Dr. D's smells like spices, making me think it's more pure. I hadn't heard about using this for animals with joint pain until just now....I'm going to try this on my 14 year old Husky/Greyhound mix....maybe it will help her arthritis!

product_title: Band-Aid First Aid Tapes
review_headline: Band Aid Paper Tape:  Waste of Money
review_body:
There ought to be a rating of negative stars because this product would be a -5 stars. I thought I would forego purchasing the generic store brands in favor of a supposed trusted brand, Band Aid. What a poor choice I made.

The tape hardly has any adhesive. Thus, it does not stick properly if at all. What occurs was terrible. I used this paper tape to hold down a piece of gauze over my wound. As there is basically no adhesive on the paper tape it took but less than half an hour to loosen up completely. So the gauze dropped off my wound which was on a finger. I ended up dumping the rest of the roll of paper tape as it plainly is useless. The paper tape made by 3M is 100% better.

Honestly Band Aid products have failed me in recent years. In addition to the paper tape the bandages are no good either. It appears that Band Aid have outsourced the making of their tapes and bandages to Brazil. Since then the quality has decreased markedly. Their gauze is now produced in China!

product_title: Miswak Club Natural Teeth Whitening Kit/ Natural Toothbrush for Whiter Teeth, Fresher Breath, While Being Chemical Free - 100% Money Back Guarantee!
review_body:
Wifey here. You have to get this just for the entertainment value of their ultra-friendly email alone. Hilarious! On to the Miswak itself. I don't understand how this works but it absolutely does! Not only does it whiten but my teeth actually feel like I've just had a professional cleaning - they're smooth as glass. I'm always on the lookout for ways to brighten my smile, so when I got a coupon for this I jumped at the chance. In return, I wanted to leave feedback to help out my fellow Amazonians.

Miswak is a strange little guy. You get two sticks that look like chew toys for a small doggie. You also get a plastic case that looks like a toothbrush case. I don't know what Miswak is made of, but according to the directions it's referred to as "bark" - I hope so. You soak the stick in water for four hours, trim it 1/2 inch, then nibble away. It feels so good when you make little up-and-down circles on your teeth! It's like getting a massage on your teeth and gums. The directions don't state how long to make the circles, so I just do it until my teeth feel smooth. Generally, that's about five minutes. I find it very relaxing, so much so that I over massaged the first time so my gums were a little sore the next day. Once you've whitened your smile, just rinse off the stick and repeat in three or four days. I much prefer this method over white strips or my Glo device because it doesn't have any harsh chemicals and there is no mess whatsoever. It's also much faster than oil pulling. I don't smoke, but I think if someone were trying to quit the Miswak could be a helpful replacement since it keeps your hands and mouth busy. I love it!

product_title: Omron 7 Series Wireless Wrist Blood Pressure Monitor (Model BP654) Clinically Proven Accurate with Bluetooth Smart Connectivity
review_headline: Handy, but gives low pressure readings
review_body:
This blood pressure monitor is typical of those made for the wrist in that they tend to read low. What sets this wrist blood pressure monitor apart is that you can download an app onto your smart phone and transfer your blood pressure readings to the app. The app shows you a grid of your blood pressure readings against what normal readings are. The monitor also tells you if your heart is beating abnormally. For instance if it beats twice fast then one normal beat.

You must first set the date and time on the monitor before taking readings otherwise the app will not download any of the readings as it stores them by date and time. It's easy to use and carry with you, but as I said, it tends to read blood pressure low.

product_title: Bulksupplements Pure Beta Alanine Powder
review_body:
As a quick disclaimer, I received a 100g sample of this product for free with the condition that I write a review about it. All that aside, my review will be completely honest and unfiltered.

Before I chose to receive Beta-Alanine (B.A.) as my free sample, I went to examine.com to check it out first. I wanted something that has a substantial body of evidence supporting the purported effects of the supplement. On a more practical level, I also wanted to know what to expect. B.A. is a supplement that effectively increases your muscular endurance, with the only downside being something called paresthesia (which is a pins-and-needles feeling in the extremities that is completely harmless) if too much B.A. is ingested too soon.

As far as dosages go, I have been taking about 2-3g every day. I split up B.A. into two or three 1g servings. The powder dissolves VERY easily in room temperature water. It is odorless, colorless, and tasteless (although it does leave behind a very strange feeling in my mouth. But that only lasts for a second or two). I found it best to take B.A. alongside some food, as to avoid the paresthesia.

Moving onto the performance aspect of the supplement, I can say with a great degree of certainty that it works. The reason I can confidently say that is because I monitor my training very closely. I have it planned two or three months in advance, and I have enough of a solid foundation of lifting experience to determine how my body is progressing with training. This includes knowing when I'd normally feel fatigued. That last part is very important because I started taking B.A. towards the tail end of my training cycle, where volume is highest, and where I have historically felt the most fatigue. However, I was noticing that as time went on, I was actually feeling stronger and stronger. I wasn't suddenly moving a ton more weight, but it definitely took me a few more sets than normal for me to genuinely feel tired.

Based off of my own personal experience with B.A., I would highly recommend it to anyone looking to improve their performance in the gym in the gym. The only problem I have is that B.A. is somewhat expensive (from my perspective). $20 of B.A. is enough to last me about a month, whereas $20 of creatine (the only other supplement I take) is enough to last me for half a year. But finances aside, this really is a wonderful, general-purpose supplement that I feel that any dedicated gym-goer should give a try.

product_title: Oxytrol for Women Overactive Bladder Transdermal Patch
review_body: The patches work quite well with me.  I had developed urgency last summer which was horrible(prior only stress stuff,  little drips rarely).  I had heard about the Oxytrol patches.  We were visiting friends and I was worried about ruining our friends' bedding & bed!  So my hubby stopped at a drug store and I bought a pack. What a difference! I have sensitive skin also, so I place the patches on my flank area & switch them around. I'll prepare the skin either by swabbing with alcohol or just wash & dry the area before applying. I've worn other medicated patches in the past for other reasons. This patch material isn't made well or something(why I gave 4 stars). Make sure you apply it as smoothly as you can & try to avoid areas where you have a lot of movement. Most of the time, the patch does shift a little bit exposing adhesive.  You make get what appears to be a little dirty adhesive. It's not a lot to put up with considering it's effectiveness. When it's time to change the patch, I use alcohol to remove the adhesive. Then I'll apply some gel baby oil(lotion is fine).  Remember not to place the new patch over an area where you have lotion, or it won't stick. This is another reason why I rotate the skin areas.  And of course, don't forget to get in the habit of doing your Kegel exercises daily. They really help also. (Now, my problem is availability!)

product_title: Walking Sticks, Canes and Walking Sticks For Men, Best Walking Cane For Arthritis, Stroke Sufferers, Strong For Larger Persons, RIGHT-Hand Ergonomic Handle Eases Wrist Strain, Designed Not To Fall
review_headline: Good but several things you should know before buying
review_body:
I've been walking with canes for several years. I found the best to be a heavy base quad cane. For stability and ability to stand on its own. When my cane broke, I shopped for a new one and saw this gravity cane. It looked interesting. So I bought one.
First....the good:
It's light, has a good size rubber tip.
The hand grip is excellent. Fits the palm and prevents your hand from slipping if you relax and grip it too lightly
When I got the cane it was apparently missing one of the small rubber tips on the bottom of the quad extensions, or it came off. I didn't notice this and found myself slipping several times. Also the cane wouldn't stand up. When I realized it was missing a piece I contacted the manufacturer and requested that they send me the piece and I would fix it. They did better. They sent me an entire new cane and didn't require return of the old one. Great customer service.

The Bad:
Reading the part above about the missing piece might clue you in to why they sent me a new cane. They told me THEY DONT MAKE REPLACEMENT TIPS! Not good. What happens when the rubber tips or quad pieces wear out? Like they do will all canes.....you have to get a new cane. There are no third party tips or generic tips that will fit.. This is one thing I don't like about this cane.
Second. If you think this cane will stand on its own easily you are mistaken. One big advantage of a quad is that you can let go and it stays while you do something else with that hand. VERY convenient. No so with this one. It will stand on its own --- IF the floor is completely flat and level....otherwise it will fall.....and if the floor is flat and level and the cane is standing, just the slightest touch will knock it over...it almost seems like you only have to look at it for it to fall over...

In summary, it's light weight, excellent hand grip, and great customer service are a bit off set by inability to easily stand on its own and worse, the unavailability of replacement parts that normal wear out.

product_title: Small Adult Short All Terrain KneeRover Steerable Knee Walker Knee Scooter Crutches Alternative in Red
review_headline: Worth every cent you'll pay for it
review_body: I'm on day 4 post achilles surgery and simply don't know what I would do without this product. I had some time to prepare for this procedure and had read up on the various knee walkers available.  No DME company in my town offered an all terrain scooter, and the traditional ones they do offer for rent felt unstable and too tall even at the setting recommended for my height (I'm 5'3 and heavy, with arthritis and bursitis in many of my joints). I wanted something sturdy and maneuverable and liked the design and comments on these all terrain models.  I went with the Jr. model and am glad I did as if it were any larger it may not fit through all the doors in my house, let alone my car.  It rides very smoothly, has an exceptional hand brake (critical for use on a ramp) and a comfortable knee pad. I am never more than a few feet away from it these days.  I would love to see a slightly larger basket and one that has some kind of mechanism to prevent it from being knocked off so easily (with a cup of coffee in it:)  The rear wheel on mine had an issue and I wrote the company to ask about a repair/replacement.  I received a response in LESS THAN 24 hours, with full and complete satisfaction their goal.  I am so happy with this item I ordered another one for use at work so I don't have to lug it back and forth.

review_body:
I was really excited to try this product, as I was looking for a natural appetite suppressant while starting a new diet. I didn't want to have to use it in a smoothie all the time so I tried it with raspberry crystal light. The taste was pleasant, it does taste like leafy greens, but not in a bad way. My complaint is that it does not dissolve and you have to constantly shake up your beverage. I used a blender bottle with mine. I didn't really see a difference in my appetite the couple times that I used it, but I think that might be because it took me so long to drink it. Or just mix less in a thin liquid so that its easier to drink. I was very happy with the taste though! I will continue to use this as it has a lot of good vitamins and nutrients as well.

product_title: Utopia Care Long handle Safety Razor with 10 Derby Blades
review_headline: Excellent razor at a great price
review_body: I will admit, I approached this purchase with some trepidation. It seems like some people found it impossible to shave with while others loved it. But I figured, what the heck. At less than ten bucks it's worth trying. According to some of the reviews there are some QC issues, but I'm here to say that mine is a winner. It shaves as well as those expensive versions of this type of razor. I was expecting some cuts, but it's actually shaving me smoother and easier than my Gillette Excel did, which came as a surprise to me. No cuts so far and I'm a pretty fast shaver. I like the longer handle; some safety razors are so small they feel like your shaving with a kid's toy. It also has a nice heft to it. A friend of mine said he thought the handle was a little too thin and the knurling not deep enough, but I find it just perfect.  On the minus side, the part where everything screws together is fairly small, so I can see where this might be an issue, especially if you tend to over-torque things as a general rule. If you are the kind of person who frequently strips the bolts when you're working on things (you know who you are) then this might not be a good choice. Also, because it's not a butterfly opener, you do have to handle the blade to put the thing together, which might lead to accidents if you're a bit of a butterfingers. Of course, if you're a bit of a butterfingers, you probably shouldn't be shaving with a DE razor anyway. I've also noticed, after shaving with it for a few weeks, that the distribution of the blade is not perfectly even. That is to say, the shave with one side of the blade is slightly more aggressive than the other. It's not a major difference, but I did start to notice it after a while.  As to the people who claimed to suffer several cuts, they either got a seriously defective razor, or their shaving technique is atrocious. I've been using it for a couple months now, and on one occasion used the same blade every day for two weeks. That's normally notsomething you want to do. I did it just to see what would happen. I can report I suffered no nicks at all, and no razor burn. While those last few shaves with the blade were a bit scrape-y, they never reached the point of pain (for reference, I was using a Personna blade).  The biggest problem I find with this razor is that the shave is often too smooth! I find myself wondering if the razor actually did anything at all. A quick rub on my chin usually reveals that it did.  I'm very happy with this razor, and I'm extremely happy with the price point. If you are interested in shaving with a safety razor, but you don't want to spend a fortune and are worried about cutting yourself, I'm here to say that this is a good place to start.

product_title: JT Enterprises Strassburg Sock Large (16-21 in.calf) Injury Recovery
review_headline: Back to running again with no heel pain
review_body: I was skeptical about this product after having already been through wearing the hard boot at night and it not working (while cutting off circulation in my leg too).  That turned out to be wasted money.  After reading other reviews on this product, I was encouraged and also had nothing to lose because the pain in my heel from plantar fasciitis was keeping me from distance running and playing basketball.  I began  wearing the sock at night on July 27 after it arrived, and was able to start running again on August 7.  The pain went away in a couple of weeks.  I still wear it now at night just to make sure that the pain doesn't come back.  As other reviewers have said, trace the insole from one of your shoes on a cardboard box, cut it out, and place it in the sock so that it is below your foot when you're wearing the sock.  This will make the sock produce a more even stretch across your foot because it will force the strap to pull the cardboard and also bend all of your toes back.  Without the cardboard footprint, the strap will want to pull more on your big toe and not the others.  If you've tried everything else and nothing seems to ease your heel pain from plantar fasciitis, give this a try and I think you'll be pleased.  It worked for me.

product_title: Perfecto Professional Double Edge (DE) Safety Razor for Men |Long Handle for Comfortable Wet Shaving|Stylish Luxury Chrome Finish|Enjoy the Closest Shave with Zero Irritation|Perfect Gift for Him
review_headline: Looking for a smoother, wallet friendly shave that also has a vintage twist, then this razor is your new best friend.
review_body:
I was looking for an alternative method of shaving for my husband, who has very sensitive skin. I was rather tired of shelling out what felt like hundreds of dollars in other shaving utensils that didn't quite seem to last "long" enough for my peace of mind or wallet. However, someone turned me onto the idea of safety razors, which is the original tool used to shave that pathed the way for cartridge razors. I decided to give this a go, especially knowing that my husband who liked vintage items would probably enjoy knowing that his great-grandfather probably used something similar to shave with a hundred years ago.
The Perfecto Double Edge Long handled Safety Razor, feels nice in the hand. The design behind this tool is to use weight to help maintain balance while shaving and it does just that. One might think it is going to harder to shave, with a double edged safety razor compared to using a modern cartridge razor; however, that is simply untrue. I have noticed that while getting used to it still my husband is a little more patient while shaving, he is also getting a much better and closer shave with the perfecto double edged safety razor then he was with some of the more expensive five blade cartridge razors like Schick or Gillette has to offer. Also, so far no cuts. I get to appreciate the fact that my husband can use both sides of the razor, not a single cartridge razor can make that claim, so the blades last longer- making it a more budget friendly shave by far.
Plus, who wouldn't like to shave with something as handsome as this perfecto double edge long handled safety razor? Seriously, by far the best looking shaving tool I have ever seen.

I did receive the perfecto double edge long handled safety razor either at a discount or free in exchange for my unbiased and honest review. Thus, I can personally say that this review is based on my own personal experience with the perfecto double edge long handled safety razor and was not paid for.

product_title: WonderGel Roll-n-Go Seat Cushion
review_body:
I work out daily on a recumbent exercise bicycle. I think the last two I've used have had a cheap seat pad, or perhaps I'm just getting older. At any rate, pedaling for an hour was becoming increasingly uncomfortable. I started looking for some sort of cushion that was moisture-proof since hour-long pedaling sessions are usually pretty sweaty.

The first cushion I tried was the [[ASIN:B00LZJXEM6 Moss Green Thick Seat Cushion with Holding Handle and Velcro Strap]]. It helped a little, but it was still painful to work through the hour.

I then tried this product. Spending $30 on a cushion seemed a bit much, but I liked that it didn't have a cover. It's proven to be very comfortable; I no longer have any pain from pedaling. To keep it clean, I cover it with a T-shirt before each workout.

In searching for cushions, I tried to find any reviews where someone mentioned using it on a recumbent exercise bike. No luck. I'm hoping this review proves useful to anyone in a similar situation.

product_title: Sunbeam Renue Tension Relief Heat Therapy Pad, Moist/Dry Heat, Digital Controller, 4 Heat-Settings, 2-Hour Auto-Off, Machine Washable, 14'' x 22''
review_headline: Excellent for people who are not lumberjacks, blacksmiths, or roustabouts.
review_body:
I am a man with the shoulders and neck of an NFL lineman - If I wrap the pad around my neck and attempt to connect the magnets to hold it in place I have 2 issues:
1. The wrap is *just* large enough to fully go around my neck and, although it does fit and does not obstruct my breathing, it is quite snug and feels like someone has their hands about my head, neck, and face and could choke me out of the octagon at any moment. I suppose I could try to convince myself at an emotional level that this sensation is not one of murderous intent but instead a loving caress, however, I would need to work on myself and my feelings for a while to get there; possibly start a 12-step program and buy some patchouli oil.
2. The pad bunches up on the back of my neck and the internal heating coils follow suit and bunch up accordingly, creating both an area of excessive heat at the base of my neck and areas of non-heat where the wrap billows away from my body and will not lay flat. The only way I have found to alleviate the bunching issue is to put the heating pad flat on my back and drape the shoulder flaps forward, maintaining a forced cleavage, which gives the appearance of fuzzy green pauldrons.

Other than contributing toward the look of a Valkyrie joining battle at a plushie convention and the above gripes for MOUS's (Men Of Unusual Size) this has been a good heating pad for me. It keeps my neck and shoulders warm, and is there really much more you can ask of an item with the words "Heat, Neck, Shoulder" in its name?

product_title: Organic Neem Oil 100% pure cold pressed - 16 oz
review_headline: My tomato plants were amazing! Not sure if the Neem helped but it ...
review_body:
I bought this for my pot garden....specifically as an insecticide and fungicide. I had ants crawling all over my cucumber plants, plus those plants had some other insect. If I sprayed a neem oil solution (30oz of water with 2 tbs of neem oil and 2 tsp of liquid castile soap) faithfully every 2 weeks, I had no problems with insects.

I also sprayed the solution on my bell pepper plants because every single plant had a black ring around all of the joints. After just one treatment, that black ring was 80% gone and with just one more treatment, it was 100% gone. After that, it never came back.

I sprayed it on my tomato plants because I read that it helped the tomato plants to protect themselves. My tomato plants were amazing! Not sure if the Neem helped but it certainly didn't hurt. Best investment I made for my garden!

product_title: Philips HF3520 Wake-Up Light With Colored Sunrise Simulation
review_headline: Wonderful light, but very obnoxious to operate.
review_body:
So I absolutely love the light that this lamp produces, and it genuinely makes it easier to wake up in those dark winter months. These are the downsides that I have found; I have had this for 9 months now, and I still have a hard time using the menu - it's not intuitive at all. All of the buttons are located around the rim of the lamp, so it's basically impossible to operate from bed since you need to be standing over it to see which buttons you're pressing. The alarm is either on or off, there are no "weekday" settings. I feel like with where technology is at these days, that should be an obvious option.

If this had a remote, or app integration I would be sold. However it's so cumbersome to operate that I sometimes don't use it just out of laziness. The light is a fantastic temperature though, and I really enjoy the "sleep mode". I can hit that button and then have 5, 10, 15, or 20 minutes to get settled as the light dims into darkness.

review_headline: Perfect for shortening drying times and naturally softening fabric
review_body: My first go with dryer balls were homemade ones that were a pinterest project. I loved them... they were great for naturally softening our clothes and did a good job reducing static (we lived in OH at the time so the humidity kept static from being a huge problem). But, as I continued to use them, a few started to get loose strands of yarn, and I noticed that they had begun to collect lint balls of differing colors from our clothes. I wanted some more to help shorten the drying time on our cloth diaper inserts, so I bought these. I'm really happy with them. They're felted so that the individual threads aren't apparent (or coming part at all), and I haven't noticed nearly the fuzz build-up that my homemade ones have had. Now we live in a much dryer climate, so the static prevention isn't nearly what it used to be, but the softening effect and reduced drying time is still great. I'd buy them again.

review_headline: I could not be more happy... baring getting knee replacement.
review_body: I was using a cane when my right knee developed degenerative joint disease. One cane was fine for one bum knee. When my left knee started having the same pain one cane wasn't going to help me be mobile until my knee surgery (or knees surgeries I should say). I looked online to see which Rollator I could get with Medicare and it was a big bother finding the type I wanted, finding a reputable dealer, and then seeing that those reputable dealers charged $100 more than Amazon. Since it was such a bother to go through Medicare and the local distributors of this sort of Rollator looked right shady, I decided to buy it on Amazon. It came in two days, required a few bits of assembly that I was easily able to do on my own. It is sturdy. It has a logic to the design down to the pull up strap for the cross bar connected to all four wheels, that aids folding it up. It is light weight.  It is narrow enough to get through my crowded galley kitchen but wide enough for my bottom. I LOVE being able to sit down when waiting in line. I would recommend the Drive Medical Four Wheel Rollator to anyone who is thinking of getting one.

product_title: Wisk Deep Clean PowerBlasts Laundry Detergent
review_headline: Great product, but the Amazon listing price needs to come down
review_body:
I recently injured my wrist, and had to take a break from the gym / sports. As a result I ended up doing a LOT more cardio in order to keep fit, which generated a lot more sweaty laundry. I had plenty from going to the gym and playing volleyball, but sweating on the exercise bike for a solid hour was a whole new game.

I was supposed to receive these as a free product for review, but the shipment got lost... so I decided to check the local super store (hint, the employees wear blue vests) for it on a trip to get other stuff. They carried it -- and their price was nearly 50% lower than the listing price here on Amazon. Hmm...

As single-serving detergent packets, these are nice and convenient. Just toss one in and then load your clothes on top, run a normal laundry cycle. These are best for High Efficiency (read: slightly smaller) washing machine loads. I have an HE washer so it's really convenient using these. I've read other reviewers on here saying they needed two tablets for extra soiled loads; I haven't had that issue.

My sweaty cardio clothes come out smelling fresh, which is a nice change. The super cheap-o unscented liquid detergent I was using actually wasn't doing a good job handling the extra sweaty laundry.

These tablets are also convenient for travel -- you don't have to worry about packets of fluid or powder, just toss a couple of these in a snack baggie in your luggage and you're all set for a couple loads of laundry on the go.

The one thing that DOES concern me, though, is that Amazon is currently listing these at nearly double the retail price of the local Wally World. Even with Amazon's current coupon for a buck off, it's still significantly more expensive. Even for the convenience of having these shipped to me, I have a hard time justifying a price tag for the same product I can snag on a normal groceries trip.

product_title: Moringa Oleifera and Amla Fruit Combination Powder in 50:50 Ratio. Premium Quality - USDA Certified Organic - HerbsIndia
review_headline: It was sweet, yet you could slightly taste the moringa a ...
review_body:
I have been growing my own moringa from seeds for a few weeks now, but have been needing moringa to use while my seeds grow. I decided to start growing it because of all the benefits it has. The most note worthy ones for my family are the anti depressant aspects, the fact that it increases milk supply, and lowers blood pressure. If you look up moringa, you will see all the benefits you can have from it.

I decided to try this powder in a vegan banana milkshake. When I opened the bag, a small similar to green matcha tea came out, except a little less bitter. I added half a tsp into my blender with a cup of water, added pitted dates, and a few bananas and mixed. It was sweet, yet you could slightly taste the moringa a bit. The taste is not bad, you just have to get used to it if you are not familiar with it. As you can see in the picture, it did give it a shade of green to my milkshake. The bag will surely last many smoothies!

product_title: Adjustable Night Splint w/Stretch Wedge
review_body: I rarely write reviews but feel a duty to report my results in dealing with plantar fasciitis and my results using this device. Initially when I got PF it came on quickly and I would feel its effects in the morning after my evening 3-5 mile walks. It made me very hobbled in my right foot and hurt very much for the first few hours of each day. I did some research and bought very rigid insoles for my walking shoes. After a few weeks the pain randomly lessened to anywhere between 10% to 70% as bad as when it started. I bought this device to wear at night and so far it seems to work very well. When I anticipate the pain after a long day on my feet or walking a long distance I would wear it at night. Unfortunately, even though they’re padded, the straps that keep your foot in place would eventually caused enough pain to wake me in the night. I’ve since learned that just wearing it for 2 or 3 hours in the evening seems to be enough to keep the pain down to 10% or less the next morning. So, I don’t wear it every day but it really helps on occasion.

product_title: Pampers Baby Dry Diapers
review_body:
***Update 11/17/15***

I recently purchased another box of these diapers and they are different! The smell is gone completely, and they are unscented which is a great improvement. Also, the inside of the diaper isn't as blue, I don't know that it means anything is chemically different but I feel like there are less chemicals. The tabs are different as well, instead of the entire piece being adhesive, just a 1 inch by half inch strip is, and so far I haven't had any issues with the tabs getting stuck and ripping the diapers. If I do I will update again.

I will say that we have now tried several diapers and these are the best for overnight. They get very full but don't leak or bust.

**Original review**

I cloth diaper my baby most of the time, but we have been using these diapers at night. We started with the size 2 at 2 months, and the absorbency has been wonderful. She was easily going through the night at first, but now she's waking up early with a very full diaper (she weighs 14 pounds at 3.5 months) and I wind up having to change it.

Now, I thought it was a fluke at first, but the tabs on these diapers stick horribly. About 1 out of every 5 diapers winds up shredding rather than opening up. The problem is that when you are trying to change the diapers in low light you don't notice in time to salvage the diaper.

I also hate the powdery scent, it makes me nauseous. When they are peed in or pooped in... Ugh. Gag me. Maybe all diapers smell like this, as stated I cloth diaper and wouldn't know.

product_title: Zahler Mastermind, Comprehensive Mood Formula, Contains 5-HTP, Same, L-Tryptophan and more, Certified Kosher 120 Caplets
review_body:
After giving birth 7 months ago, I have struggled with postpartum depression. I also made the decision to use natural family planning after my body reacted negatively to hormonal birth control. Lastly, I've had three kids and have noticed increased forgetfulness that is scary to me because my grandma was just diagnosed with dementia and I don't want to succumb to the same fate.
First, the packaging of these pills is classy in my opinion. They come individually packaged in a foil card that is stacked inside a neat black box. The instructions say to take two pills twice a day with meals. They are easy to swallow and I have not noticed any negative side effects at all.
I do think they are working. I feel that my emotions are balanced and my responses have been better controlled. I don't feel like I'm under the influence of anything and feel that my thinking is clearer. I feel like these pills have helped me get on top of the sadness that has been such a big part of my day.
In conclusion, I do feel like this product is worth the price tag because it is a natural alternative to mind-altering medication.
I received this product at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest review.

review_body:
These pads do seem to stay bacteria-free and stain-free, and they do a good job making plates and glassware sparkling clean. However, they have a few limitations that have caused me to subtract a star from their rating.

The instructions accompanying these pads say not to put the pads in a microwave, and not to use them on stainless steel pans. I would be wary about using the pads on the non-stick surfaces of any pots and pans. They have a tendency to scratch if used somewhat vigorously.

So taking these provisos into account, it might ultimately be more economical to buy the regular, less expensive Scotch scrub pads. The standard pads can be used on all surfaces, and they can be put in the microwave to rid them of bacteria.

Worked like a charm . I was a little wary of possible burning, as I had read the reviews. there was absolutely no burning for me at ALL. not one bit of discomfort. Would definitely use this again.

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_headline: I love the fitbit and it is helping me to meet ...
review_body: I love the fitbit and it is helping me to meet my weight loss goals. There are some things that I don't like about too like for example I wish it was waterproof, it's not and I do a lot of swimming so that does suck especially for the price. I don't like that you can't change the band (in case of breakage), but the band seems to be very well made so I think that the chance of breakage is probably very low. I recently changed from central time zone to eastern time zone when it was after midnight which ended up adding all my data from the day before to the new day (since a new day starts at midnight) I guess because it didn't hit 12 on the dot it didn't reset like it normally does, so I had to call fitbit to get it fixed, some type of glitch. And I wish I would have put a screen protector on the face because I accidently scratched it while working one day so now it is scruffed up. But I love that I can sync with Myfitnesspal (since I was already using it I just like keeping all my data there). I like that I can set my goal to calories burned rather than steps because I could care less about steps. I also like the fact that I can set how I want to lose weight by setting to a moderate mode or more aggressive and it tells me if I am over or under for the day. I can also interact with my friends with fitbits and we can push each other with daily competitions which I think it a really fun feature to keep us motivated. I have already lost 23 lbs since I bought the fitbit, I still have a ways to go but I have no doubt that I am going to get there with the help of this little device. Thanks Fitbit!

product_title: Perfecto 100% Original Pure Badger Shaving Brush. Engineered for the Best Shave of Your Life.For all methods,Safety Razor,Double Edge Razor,Staight Razor or Shaving Razor, Its Best Badger Brush.
review_body:
This Perfecto shave brush isn't quite all that I hoped it would be. This is the second shave brush I've owned, but I've been shaving for years with a brush. When I am shaving, the tips of this brush feel like needles on my skin, particularly when I change the direction I am brushing, or use the brush in a circular motion. Please note, I do have very sensitive skin, so let that guide you. I never had that problem with the Bump Patrol shave brush I was using before (it was something I got for free with an aftershave purchase). These Perfecto brush fibers are coarser, but perhaps meant for better durability. I've never felt or had a chance to try a "badger brush," until now.

On a few positive notes, the finished natural wood handle of this brush is really nice. The handle is wide, easy to grip and that small brass ring at the base of the hair is a fine accent. I also purchased the Perfecto Deluxe Chrome Razor and Brush Stand here on Amazon. It has made organizing my shave area a breeze and it looks sharp. It fits this shave brush perfectly.

Honestly, I still have a few more strikes against this brush. First, the fibers of the brush do not absorb water as well as I would expect. I seem to have a hard time getting water to stay in the brush, and thus it's harder to start creating a lather with the high-quality shave gel I use. I will see how this brush does over time and perhaps it will get better the more that it is used. Secondly, I would mention I noticed an unpleasant odor on the brush hairs when I was shaving. This may be because the fibers are natural and not synthetic. My first reaction was that something smelled like a soiled diaper. Lastly, this brush is Made in China. For $12.95 [08/25/15], I am going to keep using this brush. It's a great value when stacked against some of the brushes you see online for triple and quadruple the price. The brush is dense, has class and serves its purpose.

product_title: Fitbit Surge Fitness Superwatch
review_headline: Definitely a superwatch for the data conscious user!
review_body:
I have had other activity trackers over the years and have seen Fitbit come out with products. When they came out with the Charge HR I was going to purchase it but then I saw the Surge. I decided to go with it since I liked the size and display. I wasn't sure I was going to be able to sleep with it given the size of the display; but from the first moment I put it on I was amazed at how comfortable it was and how after just a few minutes I couldn't even tell I was wearing it. Sleeping with it has become an absolute must since it shows me so much valuable data using the Fitbit app on my sleep quality. The silent (vibrate) alarm is also a total win. Since it allows me to set an alarm for my early morning workouts without waking my wife. The interface is simple to use and customizable enough to place exercises in an order of most used to least used for quick on the run access.

Sizing: I usually am on the end of the straps on most watches. So when I got the large I was concerned it might be too small for me, but it fits great. If you have to adjust your watch bands to the largest width to accommodate your wrist size you will probably be able to get away with the Large, but I now have the XL which has a very XL strap. I am at the top of the strap instead of the end. This works much better so the watch is sitting on the top of my wrist.

product_title: Foxnovo Portable 7 Day 28-Cell Tablet Pill Medicine Boxes Holder Daily Pill Storage Case Container Organizer
review_body:
I needed to space medications out for a relative over the course of six hours in the morning. These seemed a better option than the large single container because he can take one pack with him if he goes out for the day. It opens at the top and the cover is divided into four sections, two in front and two in back, so you are able to open just one at a time. The lids were rather difficult to open at first. It took some effort and might be difficult for someone older or with arthritis. It would be best to have a person help you the first couple of times if that is a concern. It does seem to loosen up over time though.

I applied labels to the top to indicate the time of each medicine. The current labels have words like "breakfast, bedtime, etc.". There is braille on the top of each segment as well.

Each compartment slides into the base. It does not lock in though, so they can be knocked out.

All in all it is a good set. I am happy. One star less because they were challenging to open initially.

I have taken ~ 250mg / day for a week, and though I don't notice any huge differences, I tolerate it well (some people seem to have drowsiness or excitability, but I haven't noticed either, taking it with breakfast). There are quite a few interesting studies on quercetin, worth a little searching to see if it might be useful addition.

product_title: LotFancy® (FDA Approved) Automatic Digital Upper Arm Blood Pressure Monitor ,Heart Beat Meter , Large LCD Display,120 Memories, WHO Indicator (NO power adapter,NO batteries)
review_body:
While I regularly check my blood pressure at stores, I have never had a automatic machine. I have experience using a manual cuff as I have had to check my youngest sons blood pressure for many years of his life. Here are my likes and dislikes, will mostly likes. I like that I have the ability to store 4 people. Then with those 4, I can take several readings and it will save those numbers and average them out. It will also let you know if your reading is too high, boarder, or normal. It can measure your pulse which is fairly normal for these machines but this one can tell you if your beat is abnormal. The size is somewhat portable and it has a nice bag you can keep it in to carry with you. The cuff is an average cuff size of medium so technically, I am not supposed to use this size and my youngest should be using a smaller cuff but it will do a decent job. Now to my dislikes: it does not come with a charger or batteries. Not too much of a big deal but using batteries is a little annoying. On the other hand, it only takes 4 AA batteries but who knows how long they will last but with the batteries, you can use this just about anywhere.

***I have received this monitor at a discount in exchange for my honest review.***

review_headline: Contains Yohimbe -- caution if you're sensitive
review_body: I had high hopes for Forge as I'm a fan of Legion's other fat burner, Phoenix.  Unfortunately, Forge left me feeling jittery and out of breath during my workouts -- exactly the opposite of what I want in a pre-workout!  I started with a half dose as recommended but even that bothered me.  I'm certain the effects were from Forge as they went away when I stopped taking it and came back as soon as I started again.  This might work great for some but not for me.  Overall, I'm a fan of Legion's no-BS, evidence-based formulas but I'll have to pass on the Forge. UPDATE 6 Oct 15:  After some back & forth with Matt in Legion customer service, I figured out it was the Yohimbe which was bothering me.  Even at a small dose (1 capsule), this didn't work for me.  I have used Legion's other fat burner, Phoenix, several times and think its great so if you're not sensitive to Yohimbe, give Forge a try.   Once we figured out why this didn't work for me, Legion replaced it for free with a bottle of Phoenix.  Legion is a great company and I'm a huge fan of their other products!

product_title: Wondfo Ovulation (LH) Test Strips
review_headline: Used for Baby #1 and now using for # 2
review_body: I've used these in the past and is using them again for our 2nd. I'm tracking current month so I can get an idea of when to have sex to conceive next month.  If you google or do other research,  you'll read that your LH level surges a day or so BEFORE you ovulate which means for the highest chance to conceive, have sex when you get a positive LH reading.  You can also start having sex when the lines start getting darker because that means you are getting close, plus sperm lives almost a week anyways. I read some negative eviews of people comparing to other brands or using water which doesn't make sense to me. You can't just do one test and that's it. This is a tool to understand the time period when your LH is slowly rising. You should do one everyday leading up to your ovulation and you'll see the patterns and notice the line get darker and darker.  There preggo tests are awesome too. I would never buy store tests because they are so expensive and I like to be able to test a few times just to be sure.

product_title: Mack's Ear Care Slim Fit Soft Foam Earplugs, 50 Count
review_headline: Important info on how these are designed and how they fit....
review_body:
The thing to pay attention here on this product are the words, "SLIM FIT." I'm not sure who these are designed for...super models? Children?
The ARE smaller in diameter than your average ear plug which is what I've been using for years so what happens, if you don't happen to have skinny ear canals is that they won't block sound as well.
They still work, but you won't get the desired result if you are looking for an ear plug that shuts out the most noise.
The other thing to watch when you buy ear plugs is the number of decibels that it blocks...this one is 29. I normally buy 32 which work great.
I still decided to keep these and use them when I need to still be able to hear the dogs bark when I'm sleeping, at the theater when the sound is too loud but you still want to hear the movie and for concerts...oh, and for the visits with my husband's family - several are very hard of hearing so everyone talks so loud to each other that I get a headache!
Sooooo....those of you who have super model, thin ear canals - you will love these! Everyone else...consider yourself warned ;)
Hope this was helpful info for those shopping for ear plugs!

product_title: Nature's Way Cayenne Extra Hot, Capsules 100ea
review_headline: A Very Good Cayenne Supplement, But Approach With Caution
review_body:
I have taken cayenne for several years primarily for its anti-inflammatory properties. I had always used a lower dose product, and was surprised to see this "Extra Hot" formulation from Nature's Way. Even though I love spicy food and frequently cook with very hot peppers, I had a bit of a struggle initially adjusting to this dosage. If you have a sensitive stomach or are new to using cayenne or capsaicin supplements start with a lower dose and work your way up to this. It is absolutely vital to take this supplement with food. Taking it on its own is a recipe for gastric upset of the highest magnitude.

If you are used to a lower dose of cayenne and tolerate it well, this is definitely more powerful option, but even cayenne veterans need to be mindful to take it with food. As for me, when I finish this bottle I'm going to return to a lower dosage and, if necessary, take it more often.

review_headline: What person doesn't like to be pampered
review_body: [[VIDEOID:d7b363f3ff9821869a836b4285c4e3de]]I am HUGE fan. What person doesn't like to be pampered? This is a super simple, very easy to use product. Overall I really like this PediBunny, my feet look better than before I had this electric file and that alone makes this an awesome product for me. review_headline: Convenient and safe for little ones with sensitive skin. Good deal!
review_body: I have been using this product as a sample sent from bzzagent.com in exchange for my honest review. So here it is! I think these PODS are extremely convenient. There is zero mess, I just toss it in with my clothes and turn the washer on. My son and myself both have skin sensitivities to almost every detergent out there. My son gets random rashes that we were not even sure of the cause. Well, since using these PODS, the rashes have stopped.  Granted, it has only been 2 months and things could change (never know if something else was eliminated when school break came around) but he has not complained of itching or redness since school started back up again. So I would recommend this detergent for the sheer fact that it is simple to use and harm free for my kiddos. The price is so-so, but that is what you get for convenience....and I generally do not use just one pod if I need my clothes really clean it takes two....making the cost per load increase.

product_title: Air Cam Walker/Cast Boot With Shock Absorbers (Fracture Boot) - Small/Medium 5-11.5 Adjustable
review_headline: Would recommend for a broken foot...
review_body: I broke my foot and have been wearing this boot since the beginning of July.  It is not heavy, very comfortable and easy to get in and out of.  It is well-vented  and the liner was easy to remove from the boot and hand-wash (air dry). The air pump is  attached to the boot making it very handy to inflate or deflate in seconds for comfort as the swelling varies. The "platform heel" is about 2-2 1/2 inches, and I found it much easier on my hips when walking if I wore a similar height shoe on my other foot.  The only thing that I wish was different with this boot is that it makes a noise with every step you take - kind of sounds like a  horse walking on a road.  While I definitely could not sneak up on anyone, I got used to the sound and appreciated that I could walk (without crutches) comfortably while my fractured foot healed.  Very happy I chose this boot!

I also like l-theanine, 5htp, l-tyrosine, dopa mucana & DLPA. In conjunction with each other alongside a healthy lifestyle makes a huge difference in finding balance for me. Though I suggest unless you have all the same diagnosis as myself, please don't copy my list & start taking all of that right off the bat. I am under a medical professional's supervision. Though I have free reign to pick & choose. But that is because I've done ALOT of research. All in all I hope this helps someone!

review_body:
[[VIDEOID:e3824bbb980d8b620e4ed2eaa829c999]]I've suffered for years with horrible headaches and finally discovered trigger point massage therapy is the only way to get rid of them. Massage therapy is expensive, especially with frequent headaches, so I've been looking for something I can use at home to achieve the same results. When I was offered the Shiatsu Neck and Back Massager Pillow from LiBa, I was excited to try it.
The first thing I noticed when I opened the box was how well made the unit was. The construction and stitching is extremely high quality, as is the velcro strap that secures it to the chair/car seat. That brings up another point- the car! Most of my headaches start in the late afternoon after sitting at my desk most of the day. When I get to my car my head is pounding so much I can hardly focus. I couldn't believe this massager came with a car plug in and I was able to try it out right away. Since my daughter drives home from work I put it on the passenger seat and was headache free by the time we were home!
Most of my headaches originate from my should and the fit of this massager is so versatile I'm able to use there or on my back, depending on where I need it most. The heated \\"stones\\" work miracles on my shoulder and never get too hot. The rotation and temperature are perfect to work out the knot that causes my headaches.
In just the short time I've had this massager, it has been a life saver! And a wallet saver!

review_headline: it looks like this product contains organic turmeric powder only (no turmeric ...
review_body: Per the label on the bottle, it looks like this product contains organic turmeric powder only (no turmeric extract standardized to a certain percent of curcumin).  Pure turmeric powder has 2% - 3% curcumin by weight.  So if this product contains turmeric powder only, then one capsule which contains 500 mg of turmeric provides 10 – 15 mg of curcumin, not enough to achieve therapeutic benefits.  If the bottle is not clearly labelled and the product does contain a higher percent of curcumin, I’d ask the manufacturer to comment on how much curcumin is in the product.

product_title: Rainbow Light - Kids One
review_body:
Got these for my 2 year old. He LOVESSSS them and asks every morning as soon as he wakes up for his "vitamin candy." I searched a LONG time for a vitamin to give him. I chose these because of the high iron (he is anemic), the probiotic, and the whole foods. These 3 things are hard to find altogether. I have been very pleased! We go back to the doctor tomorrow to see if his iron has increased over the past 2 months. Interested to see if he's really absorbing it from these.

product_title: Liceadex-eX Home & Bedding Spray :: Complete Lice Removal Home, Bedding, Clothing and more- All natural, organic, and safe - 32 oz value size
review_headline: Seems to be successful for lice prevention
review_body: We use this in an old time photo studio. In the summer we are very busy and sometimes the same hat is worn multiple times a day by different people. We spray this on hats after each guest. We used to use a Lysol spray. But a nurse told me there was a recent lice outbreak in our area so I figured we should take extra precautions and start using something specifically for lice. If we have enough time we treat hats with the Lysol spray AND this. But more often than not we just use this spray on hats. I do want to be completely honest and say that we have never had lice in our studio. So I can't comment on how this works for someone currently suffering from lice. But as a preventative measure it seems to be working. Granted, there's no way for us to know if anyone with lice has even come in, so the only proof I have is that we are currently lice free. We love the peppermint smell. But it definitely does burn your throat if you forget to hold your breath for a few seconds after spraying it. I was hesitant to purchase it because another review mentioned the nozzle only shot out a stream, instead of a mist. However I noticed the nozzle has a stream and mist option and both seem to work just fine.

My son who is a Division 1 baseball player soon discovered how incredible the balls are to his overall training program. Somehow, they made their way back to college with him. And I'm back buying round two because these balls are 'must haves' in my anti-aging arsenal.

product_title: Majestic Pure Geranium Essential Oil, 4 fl. oz
review_headline: Perfect Geranium Oil to use in making my skiin care products!
review_body:
I love how nice my home smells when I diffuse Geranium Essential Oil. It has a lovely light sweet floral scent that's refreshing and calming without being overwhelming. Unfortunately, I rarely treat myself to that pleasure because Geranium Oil is absolutely fabulous at tightening up sagging skin and reducing wrinkles. That wins at my age, so I use it in my homemade facial creams and toners to stave off & shore up sagging cheeks and jowl lines.

Here's one of the toners I make with it in case you'd like to make some too. Blend 1 cup rose water, 2 tablespoons witch hazel, 4 drops rose essential oil, and 4 drops geranium essential oil in a spray bottle and use it twice daily after washing my face. I like to follow up at night with a Shea Butter night cream I make with Geranium oil and other essential oils so I benefit from moisturizing and toning all night long.

Geranium Essential Oil is also great for reducing scars, including old acne scars, so you might like to experiment in making your own creams, toners, or lotions. You could also add a drop or two to your favorite creams and lotions to give them the added benefits of Geranium Oil. Juts don't apply it directly to your skin without adding it to a carrier oil like coconut oil or jojoba oil because this essential oil is pure and concentrated so it may cause skin reactions if undiluted.

Majestic Pure's Geranium Essential Oil is exactly what I'm looking for when I buy oil to use for my homemade skin care creams, toners, and lotions because it's 100% pure unfiltered therapeutic grade Geranium Oil that's been steam distilled and doesn't contain any additives or fillers. It's also packaged in the USA so I feel assured that it's safe to use. It comes in a generous 4 oz size dark glass amber bottle to protect the oil from light. The bottle is capped, but they include a glass medicine dropper which I prefer because it makes it easy to dispense just the right number of drops I want without wasting any. This Geranium Oil is exactly what I'm looking for. Perfect for use in aromatherapy, cosmetics, and for skin care products. Five stars.
