product_title: Short Air Cam Walker Fracture Boot
review_body: I previously had the Breg Vectra Premium Air Tall Walking Boot which was given to me by my Ortho.  Since I no longer needed the high boot, she suggested I spend a lot less money and buy the short boot from Amazon.  I shopped and figured this was basically the same thing.  Well, not quite.  The brace tends to rub in uncomfortable places.  Also, the fabric of the boot goes higher on your leg than the top strap, which means it is constantly coming open while you walk.  Admittedly, I walked miles and miles in this boot, so I may have been rougher on it than most.  With some modifications, I made it much more comfortable for me.  First, I wear a heavy sock with the toes cut out underneath the boot.  Second, I took a velcro strap from one of my old boots and wrapped it around the top and this made it stop coming undone.  Third, I had to use all of the pads that come with it, plus shove a pair of socks down inside or the support bars rubbed so hard, the bruised my leg.  However, with these modifications, I have been able to use the boot on my many travels.  I have noticed that the glue that holds on the straps is coming undone a bit, but it is still functional with modifications,  In the 5 weeks since I have had mine, I have flown 6 times, driven across 4 states and averaged about 5-7 miles a day, so it has gotten its use.

product_title: Ivation Oral Irrigator Compact Countertop Water Flosser - with 5 Interchagneable Tips, 2 Jets, Tongue Cleaner, Pocket, Orthodontic & Plaque Seeker
review_headline: Doesn't Beat My Waterpik In Terms of Power
review_body:
I received a free item to review.

The Ivation is meant to be a more-stylish, functionally-equivalent version of the Waterpik Water Flosser that I've had for a couple of years.
Some design choices seem a bit misplaced however: the tank on the Ivation is larger and higher (as in less stable) and includes measuring markings on the side - but to what purpose? I fill barely half of the admittedly smaller Waterpik tank to floss my teeth just fine measuring water by eye.

Rather than an easy to access open clamp on the front of the Waterpik for the dispenser tip, the Ivation has a directional socket on the side to seat it. The effort required to position the holder tip just right is annoying and doesn't feel as secure so close to the edge of the tank. If you've ever had the tip fall over and flood the top of your bathroom countertop you care about that hold being secure.

Speaking of tips, the base holes on the opposite side for tips - in addition to the same compartment under the top the Waterpik has - is to me another case of a feature in search of a customer need.

But the primary failing of the Ivation flosser and the main reason I hesitate to recommend it is its lack of power compared to the Waterpik. I use the Waterpik on level 8 for pulsation that's both comfortable and effective. Level 8 on the Ivation feels like level 4 on the Waterpik and maximum force doesn't feel all that much stronger.

Bottom Line: The Ivation doesn't accomplish Job One as well as my current Waterpik and I see no reason to downgrade.

product_title: Unisol 4 Preservative Free Saline Solution - 3 4oz bottles (2 packs)
review_headline: I actually forget the devices are in my eyes at times - quite amazing! Yes
review_body: I wear PROSE (Prosthetic Replacement of the Ocular Surface Ecosystem) devices, which are rigid and cover the entire ocular surface - they are for medical purposes for those with complex corneal disease. I have Primary Sjogren's Syndrome, an autoimmune disorder that attacks moisture-producing cells, thus, I have zero tear production, which has caused major eye disease and discomfort,  severely impacting my daily life.  When I got the PROSE devices, I was instructed as to how to clean and fill (yes -fill) them with either sterile saline (the kind used with nebulizers) or Unisol 4. These devices are filled with saline so that the cornea is kept moist and spared further injury.  For whatever the reason, using this saline promotes the comfort and extends the wear time for me.  I actually forget the devices are in my eyes at times - quite amazing!  Yes, it is more expensive for me than using the nebulizer-type saline, however, there is no contest as to which is the MVP for me - it's Unisol 4.  If you are hesitant, try one.  You only get one pair of eyes!

review_headline: Good razor for the price ... But not a butterfly opening razor
review_body: Great wall built racer, nice weight, great finish... But not a butterfly razor... But that was my mistake in not more closely reading the details. In order to load a blade you need to remove the entire handle and the bottom plate of the razor head... Left out the old razor and drop on a new one then reattach the bottom plate and screw the handle back on. Not as convenient as a butterfly razor but not difficult either. As for the shave, pretty good. The razor comes with 5 Gillette blades that seemed to do a good job, however, I did buy some other blades to see how well those work. The razor is easy to hold, handles nicely as you're going across your face and seems to take up a good angle as you hold it for an excellent shave. I will probably buy another razor in the future that has the butterfly opening feature... And will use this one as my travel razor or my camping razor.

review_body:
These Cottonelle rolls have DEFINITELY shrunk. If you zoom in and look at the TINY writing, you will see that each square is 3.82" x 4.0". The last roll I purchased in the store was 4.5" x 4.0". Quite a difference and impossible to use on dispensers that don't have the roll holder. I found the larger size at Costco over the weekend, but I am still stuck with these 32 rolls that won't fit in my master bath. Whether or not this was intentional, it felt like Cottonelle was: a) shrinking the size to cut costs and keep their profit margin, and b) deceptive in hiding this information in the picture. $.72/Count means nothing here. This could have been a different story if the size would have been included in the Product Details.

I see no reason to ever purchase this product from Amazon and will consider changing brands next time I go to a brck-and-mortar store where I can see the sizes.

review_headline: Very nice lighter for the price, would recommend
review_body:
This is a really nice torch lighter for the price. I mean like damn it's pretty nice. It has a really good weight to it and feels really nice in your hands and feels a lot like a zippo but slightly heavier and sturdier. It has a wheel on the bottom for measuring the intensity of the flame. I read another review on here where someone was saying it was hard to turn the wheel, but ive never had any troubles turning it. At it's highest setting, the flame is pretty big, maybe 1 1/2" to 2, but at it's lowest setting, it won't even make a flame. The only complaint i have about this lighter is that it doesnt have a fuel indicator. So when Im filling it i have no idea when to stop except when it's spewing and spraying out butane.

Overall this is a pretty rad lighter and I'd definitely recommend it if you have an extra 10 or so bucks laying around and want a nice mini torch

product_title: Acid Reflux Wedge Pillow (32"x30"x7") with Memory Foam Overlay and Removable Microfiber Cover "BIG" by Medslant. Recommended size for GERD and other sleep issues.
review_body: I love this pillow.  I do not have acid reflux, but had discovered that if I used a stack of pillows at night, I slept better.  The problem with that of course was shifting pillows etc. so it was not the ideal solution.  After doing some research on wedge pillows, I determined that Medslant had a good product and decided to purchase the Big wedge.  I am so glad I did.  I did have a couple of nights of acclimating to sleeping on the wedge; however, my sleep improved from the first night.  I now routinely am able to sleep soundly for 5-6 hours which I was not able to do before.  And I can get back to sleep easily for another 90 minutes to 2 hours if needed.  I can sleep very comfortably either on my side (preferred) or on my back.  Unlike other reviewers, I have not experienced sliding down on the wedge during the night.  And the company seems to value its customers and want the best for them, so that is a plus too.

product_title: Natrol 5-HTP 100mg
review_headline: It wasn't for me but try it and see if it's right for you.
review_body: I'm only giving this a 2 out of 5 stars because I, unfortunately, wasn't one of the lucky ones. I feel like I should take it longer so my body can get used to it and maybe, just maybe it'll start to effectively work. However, due to the side effects that I've gotten like headaches and nausea, and even perspiration and slight increase of anxiousness, I cannot "tolerate" it enough to "wait" for it to fully work. A little background of myself: I do suffer from migraines with aura but I've been successfully maintaining that. I haven't had a migraine in quite some time until I started taking this, which flipped that around. Unfortunately. Also, I have anxiety problems and insomnia. Interesting fact: One article that I read stated that salivary cortisol can increase in first three hours but some with panic attacks also have an increased anxiety after the first three hour mark. I feel like that happened to me because I felt calm at first. Later on, I started to feel anxious again and to make it worse, I felt nauseated with a headache. I missed a day of work because of it. Even my blood pressure went up. I was perspiring in bed. Oh and it didn't help me sleep. It was hell. Another thing I wasn't a fan of was it suppresses your appetite. I can see why some would want that too but it's just not a fit for me. It did suppress my appetite but it made me feel sick at the same time. I'm also the type who has troubles gaining weight and will eat a lot but still not gain weight. Therefore, this just wasn't ideal for me on many levels. I still give it a two though because it does suppress appetite and it will help make you calm even for a little. I think this is definitely one of those "you have to try it and see it for yourself" type thing because for some it works, while others it doesn't. Lastly, I got mine from Costco. Buying it here should be the same. A little pricier but whatever is more convenient for you, try it.

product_title: Crushables Air Fresheners. Home, Gym Bag, and Car Air Freshener. 100 Percent Natural and Pure Essential Oils. Instant Aromatherapy in Just 1 Crush. Box of 10
review_headline: Convenient all natural great smelling air fresheners
review_body:
I absolutely LOVE these Crushables air fresheners! My granddaughter lives with me and I drive her and four of her friends to and from school every day in addition to carrying the dogs in the car now and then, so it can get a little ripe between trips to the car wash.

When I read that these would work in a car I crushed one and stuck it underneath the front passenger seat, and checked on it an hour later. Oh my goodness was it ever smelling fresher! I tested the Anti-Stress Blend which contains Bergamot & Clary Sage essential oils, and after an hour with just this one tiny Crushable tucked inside, the car that had smelled like somebody's locker now had a fresh citrusy-herbal aroma!

These air fresheners don't contain any chemicals or artificial fragrances, in fact they don't contain anything harmful at all. They're made entirely of pure essential oils in a glass ampule enclosed in porous paper just like an ammonia ampule, and about the same size as one. They work exactly the same way, just crush the ampule once in the center and place it where you want it to freshen the air.

According to the manufacturer, each Crushable should continue to deliver fresh scent for up to 30 days in a gym bag, 1-4 days in a car, or 2 weeks in a vacuum bag. The length of time the scent will last is affected by the size of the area they're placed, plus other conditions that make essential oils dissipate or deteriorate such as lots of air flow, or exposure to heat and sunlight. In other words, your Crushable will deliver fresh scent longer if in a small space than in a large area and if placed in a cool, dark place away from drafts, heat and direct sunlight.

These REALLY work wonderfully and I really like the Bergamot & Clary Sage blend. I can't wait to try the other combinations they offer too. I'm using it for the car, but these are great for lots of other places too. These make a fabulous all natural way to freshen up smelly gym bags, school lockers, cars, trucks, kid's rooms, closets, wherever you want to have smelling fresher. I love the fact that they're long lasting, all natural, easy to tuck away discretely wherever I want to use them, and the scent is fabulous without being "heavy" or too much. These are small, convenient, and work very well.

product_title: Rainbow Light - Menopause One
review_body:
I just need to say that these pills saved my life & my sanity.Due to the fact that I've had no children & as family history goes, like it or not, I entered early Perimenopause.It started about 3 years ago and I was in denial saying the reason I kept sweating through my clothes at night was because I had too many blankets on the bed.

Long story short, recently, depression increased to the point where I just didn't want to function and my mood swings were so bad that I couldn't even stand myself and my poor husband was at his wits end and just hid from me until he felt it was safe to come out.

Due to our 100% cancer track record history in my family with the female's, I am not eligible for conventional HRT so I have to do the alternative options. So in my desperate attempt to get my life back from this cloud I was put under, I tried a LOT of different products.I'm still getting my cycle but the way it was working, my body was clearly lacking something to help it go along so I knew I needed a product that had a balanced blend of vitamins, minerals and herbs.

I could ramble on here and tell you everything that I tried that didn't work and the things I use now in my daily regiment that help balance things out but I'd rather keep the focus on THIS product.

I was hopeful after reading all the reviews on Amazon and several other sites & felt I had nothing to lose.I was so excited that I couldn't get this fast enough.Once I received it, I have to tell you that it only took about 3 days for the effects to start working!I have been on this now for 4 weeks and I have not had any night sweats since I started taking this, no depression or mood swings.

Thanks to this product, I got my life back & words can not express how grateful I ( and my husband) am.It has the perfect balance of vitamins & herbs that a woman's body needs during the transition.I knew after doing extensive research that I needed a product that had the best of both worlds and this one is perfect.

Just a side note and I do apologize for the TMI but the pills are big so they may be a tad tricky to swallow.Aside from that, they we will turn your urine an extreme bright yellow and I'm only sharing this so you will not be alarmed.In any case, I will NEVER go without this product again.I urge you if you are on the same quest that I am to find yourself again through the journey that is Perimenopause, please do yourself a favor and give this a try.est of both worlds and this one is perfect.

product_title: Nature's Way Calm Aid
review_headline: Grounding, calming, sanity restored! Thank you CalmAid.
review_body:
I was prescribed Xanax for anxiety but wanted something natural instead. I found this product a couple of months ago and it has changed my life. I carry it in my purse and take one if I feel an anxiety attack coming or just when I feel nervous. They work incredibly well but are quite strong, so I wouldn't take one and drive. They can make you pretty sleepy. The effect they have is calming and grounding. I feel like I just did a bunch of yoga and meditation and I "don't sweat the small stuff".
In the mornings, I will break open a capsule and squeeze the oil into a water bottle. I swallow the empty capsule in the morning and I drink the infused water throughout the day. This keeps me chill and prevents the irritability that comes when I feel anxious. My friends and coworkers are very relieved, I'm sure, and I feel like taking this supplement has improved my relationships. I am no longer snappy. This also helps with PMS .

Yes, you will have crazy lavender burps. I happen to love lavender and find the flowery burps amusing. If you don't love lavender, I wouldn't recommend squeezing these capsules into your water.

This is the best product I have found for anxiety and I have tried many. I think they are reasonably priced and are worth trying! I hope they work for you, too.

product_title: BiC Soleil Glow Razors - 3 ct
review_body:
"Babe, this is the best shave I have EVER had!" Those are the words that came out of my mouth this past weekend as I shaved my legs! The razor was gliding so smoothly that I thought it wasn't working. I had to check and feel my legs! I am so used to feeling the razor skim across my skin that NOT feeling it was odd. After I shaved my legs, I was pleasantly surprised at how smooth they were. Not a speck or stubble in sight! Out of all the razors I have ever used (Schick, store brands, Gillette, even other BIC razors), these have definitely been the best. I let my husband know that if they have a male version of these, he should definitely try them! My only complaint (which is not a full blown complaint) is that the head is somewhat large, so trying to get into any crevices proved to be difficult. When shaving my underarms, which are not a straight surface like legs can be, it was a bit impossible, so I had to stretch my skin to get a good shave. I loved the colors - pink, green, and purple, and loved the way they were designed. They were easy to hold and didn't slip out of my hand even though I had shaving cream and water working against me! I am very feminine and love all things that are such, so the curves and colors were appealing to my eye. Overall, after I am done with these, I plan to get more! I honestly could not see myself finding another set of razors that shave this well. Apart from the large head, I will gladly figure out a workaround for that!
I received these razors for free from BIC via BzzAgent along with several coupons in exchange for my honest review! #GotItFree

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_body:
Started with a lower level Fitbit, which worked very well. Recently updated to the Fitbit Charge HR. Works reasonably well and has a lot of nice features. Two issues keep it from being a real winner.
1) I have a large wrist and the "large" wristband barely fits on my wrist and is essentially too tight. They should make make the band longer and those with smaller wrists can trim it shorter with a pair of scissors.
2) The battery sucks! I bought (2) of these Charge HR's, one for me and one for my wife. Both fitbits last about 1 1/2 days tops. The manufacturer's data says the charge should last 5 days. We've had them for several months now and never has the charge lasted for more than 2 days on either fitbit.
Other than these (2) major issues, it's a great tool and is easy to use.

product_title: Brookstone iNeed Neck and Shoulder Pro Massager with Heat
review_body:
I was seriously wounded in the Vietnam war decades ago and had a major surgery my lower back in the U.S. Over twenty years. I now have had arthritic,chronic pain in the joins on my neck and my lower back. I visited the chiropractors for years without help,and I purchased around two dozens of all kinds of the massagers included the previous models back vibration massagers to the late model of the whole body shiatsu,kneeding plus thumping console professional massager(big reclining chair)which made in Japan and needless to mention about the good of it and it is quite expensive. As above physical problems that makes me very picky on choosing the massagers from the all brands handheld portable massagers to some midium size massager pads(shiatsu,kneeding and thumping)which can put on any office chair for temporarily release tire and stiff muscles and I would say besides my professional console massager,this I-need unique massager is the best Brookstone neck massager I've ever owned. Actually,I had one before with the ivory color I used it for awhile then listed for sale and immediately someone bought it. This one is a second extend model(BR6500E) black color with more powerful in the thumping and percusion. I have owned another Brookstone's powerful handheld thumping massager but I don't like it because it's too heavy to hold it while Operating in my back which makes my elbo and the join of the holding arm hurt so much after the operation. And this I-need massager is quite heavy too,but this time the Brookstone has designed the right tool in a useful way for the users. It's operation similar to the U.S. Made thumper massager which was designed for the chiropractors used and it has a strong thumping plus it's heavy built and its robust body which helps to transfer all it's vibration& percussion energies down to its target. And this I-need massager too! Which learns that physic way on massage and the user just relaxes and releases. This neck massager has a circled iconic which all the functioning operation buttons inner. The big mirrow color power button(on/off)is in the center,the low,midium,hi buttons are on the left side and the three programmed buttons of energize,pulse and soothe are on the right and the heat button is located in the bottom of the inner circle. As the user I warn that you must pay attention to the heat "do not turn on the heat" when you're massaged unless it's in the winter when you get cold. The massage's percusion knobs get very warm and it's hot for someone with sensitive skin when you're operating the machine and this would stay really warm like the heating pad for the period of 30-45 minutes even you turn off the button and unplug it. And I like this because I can use it as a heat pad to warm my stiff neck after the machine stops. Some reviewers mention the machine stops around fifteen minutes causes by its over heat when operating and I don't think so that because I owned many different brand of shiatsu thumping massagers pads and plus the previous original I-need massager. In order for the safety of the patient or the user,they are factory pre-programmed the machine to stop operating,pause in every fifteen or twenty minutes after each use defends on its manufacturing. Mine is factory preset pauses after 15minutes and I push the power to turn it off and push again to turn it on for continuing operating the unit and move the massager(I-need) pad to another stiffing muscle.Remember,the massager's manufacturer doesn't want the user operates the massager in one place more twenty minutes. Moreover,this I-need massager is pretty powerful thumping& percussion in medium and needless to mention when you press it in hi. I love this massager is it fits right on my neck and I relax and recline back on my office chair or sometimes I lean forward a little bit to let the whole massager weight directly on my neck&shoulder that helps the thumping plus percussion and soothing to the most of its effective. As I mention above the heating and it's powerful in the thumping percussion would make someone small in size or ladies hurt or get burned and bruises after the massage. To prevent this from happening,operate the machine in low and do not turn the heating button on. If low doesn't help your stiff muscle and medium is too strong,you might put the thick bathing tows on your muscle for both damping the thumping and reducing the heat. The price on Amazon is a little bit high and if you are tigh in buggets and don't mind the refurbished items or some opened box new merchandises(store displayed). Look on eBay some cost around $99 or even cheaper.

Edited the review on September-1-2015(Tues).
Nothing is perfect ! Besides its powerful effective thumping&percusion,it's a flaw in mechanism designed. The powerful of the mechanical that consumes a lot of electricity which generates a large amount of heats without any good heating dispatch that causes the machine to temporary stop working. The other reviewers were right and I was wrong about this heating problem ! So I take way two stars for the device.ion above the heating and it's powerful in the thumping percussion would make someone small in size or ladies hurt or get burned and bruises after the massage. To prevent this from happening,operate the machine in low and do not turn the heating button on. If low doesn't help your stiff muscle and medium is too strong,you might put the thick bathing tows on your muscle for both damping the thumping and reducing the heat. The other reviewers were right and I was wrong about this heating problem ! So I take way two stars for the device.

review_headline: OMG IT really really works! Finally.
review_body:
I have had many nights sleep with this so I am ready to give my review. I am 37 year old woman who has a snoring problem. It's not apnea, I just snore. badly. I've been sleeping on the couch as to not wake up my husband. I have tried numerous other snoring devices trying to find one to allow me to sleep in my bed once again. I've tried the zquiet, the things you stick up your nose, and the chin strap thing. I was seriously beginning to think I would never find a solution.
I ordered this. You have a little work to do upon getting it but it really is easy to follow instructions and doesn't take long at all. Molding it to my teeth was very easy. But the best part is! It has worked for me. I am sleeping back in my bed. I asked my husband and he said it has definitely worked. Now a few things, It has fallen out a couple of times while I was sleeping. but no big deal. second thing is, and they warn this on the insert, is that my front teeth are a bit sensitive first thing in the morning after removing it but it goes away very quickly. It's definitely worth being able to sleep with my husband again. I did receive this at a discount in exchange for my honest review but I would honestly repurchase this at full price if I lost or broke it. It means that much to me I am so happy this worked!~

product_title: Tay LaRue Yoga for My Toes Toe Separator and Toe Stretcher, Large
review_headline: Don't be afraid to customize them
review_body:
I read more reviews than usual, before settling on this product. There was a similar product I believe was called Yoga Gems that I decided against, after seeing many comments that they were huge to the point of being painful and unusable for many customers....as well as being more than twice the cost of this product.
The problem with any product like this is that it is "a one size fits all" concept, trying to match the variety of human feet. But I felt confident after reading other comments here that this product would work for me. I have size 8.5 US women's feet....and I also have had problems with bunions and painful feet my whole life. I had bunion surgery on both feet at age 12...one foot had a tendon release, while the other foot had a big toe realignment procedure complete with bone pins and weeks in a cast....because of this, my feet are asymmetric. I've worn orthotics most of my adult life and had been experiencing increasing foot pain in the last several months... I also have plantar fasciitis and hallux rigidus. I wore Yoga for My Toes several times and concluded that I liked them, but that they weren't quite right for my entire foot. Specifically, they made a perfect spacing between my first three toes, that provided a lot of relief from discomfort....but then had my 4th and 5th toes out at angles that were ridiculously overstretched. So I altered them to be something that would work for me. I simply took out a pair of scissors and trimmed off the fifth toe hole. Then I laterally bisected the divider between the 4th and 5th toe, which allows for perfect spacing for my particular toes.
These can be refrigerated as mentioned elsewhere, and are soft and comfortable to wear. The material does catch on fabrics, so if you toss around while sleeping they likely won't stay on for overnight use. I cannot slip them on and off, I have to place them on my feet, putting the spacers between my toes. I can walk around with them on indoors, though it isslightly awkward. I definitely experience pain relief and a feeling of well-being after wearing them....even 10-15 minutes makes a difference. I believe much of my foot pain comes from my toes being out of alignment, the tendons can't keep the toes where they belong, even though I never wear cramped shoes. This product sets all my toes where they ought to be, and I'm hoping that with regular use that they help me as much or more than expensive medical treatments....I've already been through surgery, which is not always a permanent fix. I will be mentioning this product to my doctor, to recommend it, at my next visit. I feel the only way Yoga for My Toes could be better is if they were offered in a few sizes, with a sizing chart that customers could use to match the best choice to their own particular toes.

product_title: Progesterone Cream 4 Ounces
review_headline: FINALLY found a "cure" for my menstrual migraines!
review_body:
I started getting migraines with my period around the age of 40. Common and normal, yes, but depending on how heavy my flow was for the month, sometimes they would be tolerable and sometimes I'd be close to bedridden. Of course I'd take plenty of Advil to treat the headaches, but they never fully went away, and I was still left with horrible brain fuzz that made it next to impossible to concentrate. I tried to prevent the migraines with CoQ 10, curcumin/turmeric, and butterbur, the main ingredients in Migravent. They didn't really help at all.

When I finally did more research on the cause of menstrual migraines, the cause is a sudden and drastic drop in progesterone. I ordered this and tried it daily until my period came - no headaches! I thought it had to be a fluke, so I waited until my next period. I started putting it on twice a day the minute my typical PMS symptoms appeared, about 4-5 days before my period. Again, I had zero headaches. In fact, when I woke up with a slight headache one morning, I used this and needed no Advil whatsoever. Bonus side effect: my PMS symptoms were also drastically lessened. Considering that some months my PMS is more like PMDD, this is a HUGE relief for me.

Will this work for you? I'd guess that it probably will, but I am the kind of person who is sensitive to medications and will get drunk on two glasses of wine. Even if you have a high tolerance for meds, this stuff is worth a shot if your menstrual migraines are interfering with your life the way mine were.

product_title: GastrobiPlex Shake
review_headline: I can't get on board the GastrobiPlex Train...
review_body:
I really, really wanted to love this product, but I can't get passed the taste. I am not very picky when it comes to taste, especially when it comes to sweet flavors, but the taste of this shake is really artificially citrus flavored and chalky. The only time it was "alright" tasting is if I mixed it with a LOT of frozen pineapple and orange juice in a smoothie. However, that adds a lot of unnecessary calories since this is supposed to decrease your food/calorie intake and you shouldn't need a lot of add-ins to cover up the taste. I would have preferred a chocolate or vanilla flavoring since that seems to be easier to tone down with almond or cashew milk.

The one time I did manage to get the whole serving down, it did indeed seem to decrease my appetite at meal time. However, having to choke down this shake or go through the process of making a fancy smoothie just isn't worth that benefit to me. If GastrobiPlex Shakes ever end up coming in another flavor, that is easier to tone down or hide, I would definitely look into trying it out though since I would love to have a positive weight loss experience like a lot other reviewers have.

I did receive this product at a discount in exchange for an honest, unbiased review. This review is a reflection of my personal experience with this product.

product_title: Homoeolax Gentle Natural Laxative Tablets - Herbal Alternative Remedy by Bestmade for Safe & Rapid Relief of Constipation
review_body:
***Warning: this review contains bathroom talk. Don't read if you don't suffer from stomach issues. If you do, you'll probably think "I feel ya, sister!" but if you don't, you're going to be grossed out and feel dirty. You have been warned!**

This isn't a typical laxative. Over the years I've tried everything from Miralax and Colace to fiber and Ex Lax. When I used Ex Lax, I ended up doubled over in agony, explosively pooping and violently puking at the same time. This is not an exaggeration. I was pushed to use it after a week of no bowel movements and urging from my mother in law who had convinced me I was going to basically die if I didn't produce some form of waste from some orifice of my body immediately. Colace honestly didn't do too much for me and Miralax is really hard for me to take. (I'd probably choose death over drinking liquid medication, even if it's liquid I just add a powder to. I am not kidding. I can swallow pills and that's it.)

I'm already on so many prescription drugs, I really didn't want to add one for pooping. I watched my diet, increased my fiber intake, and was lucky to poop twice a week - and that's painful, round and hard types of poop. Like they could probably be used as enemy fire in the form of small cannons kind of poop. Not fun.

This was so much better than anything I've tried before. It's all natural, first of all, which is always preferable to harsh prescription drugs. This gently motivated my body to eliminate, instead of intensely evicting everything I've ever consumed. I take it twice a day and it just helps me go like a normal person. I do not go every day yet, but I'm more regular than I've ever been in my adult life. This is not your typical laxative - it gets and keeps your body on a regular schedule of bowel movements. I even waited a few days to review this to make sure there were no weird side effects because it worked so well. So far, I've found nothing. product_title: Beverly International Ultra 40, 100% Beef Liver, 500 Tablets
review_headline: I use these like food -- and I'm glad I do
review_body:
I am not a bodybuilder. What I am is a woman who has been pregnant with twins and then breastfed three children at once. I have absolutely enormous protein needs.

Protein is absolutely essential for building bodies -- including little ones. And beef liver is one of the best sources of that that exists. When frequently exhausted, with neither time nor inclination nor energy to cook, I need to have a source of excellent beef protein that I can swallow easily. These fit the bill perfectly. Beef jerky is good, too (Ostrim Beef and Elk Jerky is awesome), but sometimes you just get sick of the taste. These pills are cost-effective (about the same price as your average price for ground beef, gram-for-gram of protein), no problem if you've just brushed your teeth, and very, very easy.

They're also very large, so if you have trouble swallowing enormous pills, bear this in mind. (You can buy dessicated beef liver in powder form instead, if that's a problem for you.)

I use these like food, because that's what they are. I've been known to take thirty pills in a sitting. More than once a day. I'm not so concerned about building muscle as I am about meeting my basic protein needs and growing and feeding small children.

But on the bright side (and this is a super bright side), I think I AM building and maintaining muscle more effectively, even with just mild exercise, like walking. These are exactly what I needed, and I've bought something like ten bottles of these because I find them to be one of the most valuable foods I have.

product_title: Naturo Nitro Pre-Workout Decimus, Best Fat Burning Energy Drink with Caffeine, Nitrix Oxide Boosters and Amino Acids, Powerful Pre-workout for Men and Women, 28 Servings, Pink Lemonade
review_headline: Best pre workout on the market!
review_body:
Very rare do I find a product that lives up to its name. (especially anything with octane in it) And to prove a fact I don't get back on ever and rate items. (this is honestly the first time.)

With that said here I am, rating and reviewing this product and the most effective word I can use to describe it is yes, just yes.

Got this as a pre workout for us, and the first day trying it and I was hooked. You get out of working out what you put in, and with that philosophy any supplement I add to my workout better damn well help me put in more, push for more, or in some way help me achieve more. (why bother if not?) This gets your ready for your workout and delivers the whole time you work out. Mine are usually 45-70 minutes long all together and this powder keeps up with that. Fair warning though, this product is not for show, so do not take it if your idea of a work out is 5 minutes of a light jog and 3 minutes of weights this item might be on a higher level than one you should be seeking.

This item is great and I'm putting this review out here so people searching for the best pre workout can see. This is great for men and women (we are a couple over here that uses it) and really helps your step it up. If it hits your stomach a little hard in the morning (if you workout in the morning like us and are not ready for a drop kick to the face of sheer awesome workout energy) we have found a cheese stick or one of those baby bell wax sealed cheese wheels works perfect to allow for no yuck feelings. The flavor is great, we both enjoyed the fact that it tasted good. (would have drank it if it tasted bad after seeing the results of it)

All in all, hands down, this will be what we buy for pre workout from now on.

review_body: I'm almost 29 and have been struggling with severe cystic acne the last few years, so embarrassing. I went on birth control pills last year hoping it would help clear it up, to no avail. After doing more research I stumbled upon these vitamins. I think I've found my holy grail! I started taking these two weeks ago and my skin has improved drastically! My existing cystic acne is drying up and I only have one new active cyst, which is a major improvement so I'll take it! For other acne sufferers out there, I have tried everything under the sun but this is the first time I've found a regime that is having daily improvements. I know everyone's skin is different but maybe this will work for you as well. I started using the CeraVe hydrating cleanser morning and night, and using pure, organic maracuja oil nightly (NOT from a major retail store, they strip out the good ingredients). The cleanser and the oil are doing a great job of making my skin very soft and taking away the redness from my acne scars, and the vitamins are actually drying the cysts out and making them dissapear, hooray! I will definitely be purchasing these vitamins monthly!

product_title: Mueller XLP Ankle Brace
review_headline: Lacing up the brace is relatively easy, although once laced on tight there are several ...
review_body: I was looking for a product that would be a compromise between allowing flexibility in the ankle but still providing safety against a sprain for playing soccer. This accomplishes the flexibility without any of the safety benefits. Lacing up the brace is relatively easy, although once laced on tight there are several concerns. The first of which is that the brace does not prevent any of the movements that might result in a sprain. While the brace does cover the upper ankle sufficiently, it does not extend far enough along the foot to prevent either an inversion or eversion ankle sprain. The foot is essentially free to move. This defeats the purpose of protecting the foot from these types of injuries. Second, the lace is absurdly long, with a traditional (shoe tie) knot resulting in giant loops and strings hanging down well into and below the shoe area, providing not safety but a trip/tangle hazard. I cut off about a foot or more of lace, only to find that it was then impossible to lace up the product after that since the lace holes were too small to accommodate a cut lace, and since the lace has to be pulled out of at least 3 lace holes on either side in order to be removed or put onto the ankle. Essentially, this is a product for people who do not want to wear a brace for safety, but are required to wear one by doctor's orders. It is the equivalent of using a crushed Dixie cup as a shin guard - technical you are wearing a shin guard, but it won't help protect you when it counts.

This is my favorite "recovery" product post-run and post-weights. Personally, I prefer to combine with milk rather than water.

But the point of collegiate rather than regular muscle milk is that it meets NCAA standards - so there's no additives that might get you banished from competition (at least, it' not supposed to). Therefore, I trust is slightly more than regular muscle milk.

review_body: I'm a waitress and my uniform is white shirts and white aprons. They get horrible stains every day that show like sore thumbs. Wine, marinara, spicy Thai sauce and a whole lot more. I soak them in a bucket with my regular laundry detergent, some of the all fabric bleach and some legacy of clean trizyme fabric booster. I stir it with my hands in the bucket to dissolve it, the add 2 aprons and 2 shirts. They soak overnight and the next morning I throw them in the wash along with my black pants. Everything comes out. All stains are gone with no scrubbing. And it's safe to wash my black pants with my white shirts. It doesn't damage it. I've been cleaning them this way for a year now and since sometimes I use 2 sets of uniforms in a day and I work 6 days a week, that is a lot of stain removal with no yellowing. My uniforms are as white as the day I bought it.  Also I rescued some aprons that my coworkers had thrown away because they were too badly stained. Set in huge stains. I soaked them for 3 days and they looked like new again. This all fabric bleach is wonderful! I have found it works better to soak it in a small bucket first vs soaking it in the washing machine. Less water equals less all fabric bleach you have to use for same results. And it does need time to soak to do its magic. Don't expect a 30 min soak for no scrub miracles. Overnight it.

product_title: LiveMus!c HearSafe Ear Plugs with Silicone Triple Flange and Noise-Cancellin
review_headline: They may get stuck in your ears
review_body:
I never write reviews of Amazon products, but I feel I should write one for this product. I play bass guitar in a loud rock band. The first time I tried these at rehearsal they got stuck in my ear canals. I have never had this problem with comparable models of high fidelity earplugs, which I use on a regular basis for rehearsal and performances.

Take a look at the stems in the photograph--they are much shorter than comparable models (Hearos, Etymotic Research, etc.). They do not provide much length for your fingers to grab a hold of; and since they are made of smooth plastic like all other models, you really need to get your fingers on them well to get them out. In trying to get the volume down low enough for my comfort level at rehearsal, I accidentally pushed them a bit too far into my ears. They did not feel uncomfortably pushed in too far at all, so I was not aware of the issue until I tried to pull them out. I had to get my band member with the smallest fingers (petite female) to try to help me get them out. Even her fingers weren't small enough, so she had to dig a bobby pin out of the bottom of her purse and sit there for several minutes anxiously trying to extract them without pushing them farther in!

I'm sorry to be the bearer of bad news, because I really wanted to like these. But, unless you have very small ears and fingers, I have to suggest that you find an alternate pair until the manufacturer provides longer stems.

review_body: Within 5 minutes of taking the first dose, I had a severe reaction. It started with bad cramps and nausea, followed quickly by overheating. My face felt like it was on fire and it turned beat red. Then the same with arms and then my legs. I broke out in hives and my heart was racing. I also started to shake. For a few minutes, I thought I was going to have to call 911. My wife jumped online and gave me a Benadryl and I took a cool shower and things started to calm down. It was definitely a scary wake up call. I'm not allergic to anything that I know of and don't even have seasonal allergies. I'm not on any other medication or supplements. Don't make the same mistake I made and do your research. Others have reported similar incidents with this product.

product_title: Chinese Skullcap Root Cut Pieces, Organic / You Ji Huang Qin / Scutellaria Baicalensis 1lb Bulk Herb
review_body: It was shipped immediately and is exactly as the picture shows, and as one reviewer stated these are dried roots, therefore are hard, not soft, like dried roots are. You can either use a grinder to powder them, or soak them, they absorb water quickly. I use the blender after soaking for an hour and grind them up and drink as tea. Although you don't need to grind, they become very waterlogged just by soaking as they are, since they are cut thin, and release their chemicals quite well-----UPDATE 2 WEEKS LATER-----I made tea (WITHOUT COOKING, JUST SOAKED AND BLENDERIZED), the next day my Achilles tendon on one foot was in A LOT of pain, I didn't connect it to the skullcap because I had done a lot of walking and thought nothing of it. The next day the pain was worse, and for over a week the pain got worse and spread up my leg and into my pelvis, it hurt to walk or sit, it felt like my bones were hurting with bad arthritis. I tried to figure out what was causing this, so I remembered that it started the day after I started taking skullcap root tea and I hadn't done anything new besides that, and had been taking it everyday because it is a great relaxing herb.  So I thought well I should stop with the skullcap and see if the pain subsides. The next day 85% of the pain was gone, the day after 95%, by day 3 after stopping skullcap there was no more pain. Now I don't know if this was the fault of the skullcap root or the way it was processed or grown in China or Taiwan, I have been taking American skullcap for a while (leaves, stems, flowers) with no adverse reaction, but it isn't as strong as the Chinese root, although they are similar in makeup. But the chinese root is processed I assume as are most all herbs coming from China, I learned that they use different ways to process herbs (sulfides, aluminum, etc) and from what I hear they are not very healthy or necessarily inspected. Different sources are not following standardized procedures which are well inspected. Some maybe alright while others not.  For example not long ago this year I bought some sichuan pepper imported from China for the first time in many years, and it made me violently ill (intense nausea and painful headache, felt like food poisoning), which again is from the processing orf maybe pesticides. So, I was wondering if anyone knows if skullcap root is to blame, or just that particular brand due to the way they grow it or process it - because it is way better, both in taste and potency then American skullcap, having much more of the potent chemicals that skullcap is known for.

product_title: Lemon Zest Health Organic Turmeric Curcumin with BioPerine Black Pepper Extract 120 Vegetarian Capsules 500mg
review_headline: no fish and sodium free which is nice for those of us who need to watch what ...
review_body:
I have suffered from inflammation and joint pain from Lupus for years. I use supplements to compliment medications I take to assist in easing the pain and discomfort. Always check with your pharmacist before adding supplements to your routine if you are already taking medication. I have been using Turmeric (Curcumin) for about 6 months to assist with the inflammation. Curcumin which is the active ingredient in turmeric has anti-inflammatory, antioxidant and antibacterial properties. I can't claim that this supplement will heal all pain, but i do feel my flareups have been less frequent and intense in the months I have been using Turmeric pills.

The bottle is clearly labeled is clearly marked no artificial sweeteners, no artificial colors, no preservatives, no sugar, no starch, no milk, no lactose, no soy, no grain, no wheat, no yeast, no fish and sodium free which is nice for those of us who need to watch what we put in our bodies more carefully than most.

The pills are medium sized, and leave no after taste. I have only begun using this brand but believe it works as well if not better than other brands I have tried.

*I RECEIVED THIS PRODUCT AT A DISCOUNT IN EXCHANGE FOR MY FAIR, HONEST AND UNBIASED REVIEW.

product_title: Creatine Monohydrate Powder Micronized by BulkSupplements | 99.99% Pure High Performance Formula | Pre/Post Workout Bodybuilding/Crossfit Supplement for Extreme Muscle Building & Energy
review_body:
I started working out and read that creatine can be a very useful supplement. I decided to buy this package because it costs less per gram than the competition. It doesn't come in a big plastic jug, so it saves you money.

The creatine itself is great, it's a pure white powder with no flavor. You can add it to water, milk, juice, a protein shake or whatever else you want to add it to.

As I see it, there are two downsides to this product.
1. There's no scooper, so save one from one of your protein powder containers or just use a regular measuring spoon.
2. When you first open it, you might have trouble sealing it plastic zip lock. I recommend you take something thin and scrape out any creatine powder that may have gotten into the grooves and that should make it much easier. It's still not the best zip lock out there, but it does the job.

Overall, I am very satisfied with a product, and for this price, you can't beat it.

product_title: Similasan Dry Eye Relief Eye Drops .33 Ounce
review_headline: The best product for dry eyes!
review_body:
These are the best eye drops I've ever used and I have tried many different types over the past 10 years. What makes these so nice is that the solution never cakes and gets gritty in my eyelashes like other brands do. Also, Similasan never gives me temporary blurry vision after application like some of the others.

Before I started using Similasan, I would have several days of irritated eyes a few times each month. Since I have been using these drops (more than three months) , I have not experienced any days of eye irritation. A couple of drops in each eye every morning keep my eyes (and eyelashes) happy. They are very soothing and the dispenser is really easy to use. It is a bit different that the bottle expires in 30 days but I label the bottle with the end date and I always have a couple of unopened backup bottles on hand. I wish I found this product a long time ago.

Also, kudos to the suppliers this far. The shipping time and the packaging through Amazon has been great. I did order one bottle of Similasan from the "bullseye" store web site and the packaging was horrible. I was surprised the bottle survived. I'll order through Amazon in the future.

product_title: Garden of Life Raw Organic Meal
review_body:
The Vanilla Spiced Chai flavor is surprisingly good. Typically these organic raw meal powders have a strange aftertaste, but this one was more like an actual chai tea aftertaste. Given the taste and the nutritional value, it's a great product.

The main downside is how clumpy and thick it gets. Upon mixing with water, it gets really "muddy"...almost like a thick sludge that you have to drink. It's something that needs to be mixed and chugged down right away, otherwise the bottom of your glass will be raw meal cement.

If you can get used to drinking this consistency, then I recommend the product to you. However if you can't get over that and need something that goes down smooth as a liquid, this probably isn't what you're looking for. For me, I can get used to the consistency, so 4/5 stars.

The side effects from the regular/cumulative use of ibuprofen and naproxen are becoming more widely known and I believe that the continued use of Dr. Danielle's product will help me avoid those kinds of problems.

review_headline: and more importantly I know what they are and that they are good for me to sustain energy while being satiated
review_body:
I recently tried Health Junkie energy bars as they are new on the market and a friend referred me to them because of the ingredients in the bars. A lot of bars have ingredients I cannot pronounce and therefore I don't really know what I'm putting in my body. But with Health Junkie bars, all the ingredients are simple and healthy. I appreciate that there are only a handful of ingredients in these bars, and more importantly I know what they are and that they are good for me to sustain energy while being satiated. I also love that fact that these bars are gluten free and vegan and paleo approved energy bars.

I really liked the taste of both bars as they are delicious and more of a chewy texture. But if I had to choose, I think the Chocolate Nectar is my favorite over the Cherry Vanilla Cashew. My last point is the price. Compared to similar bars' ingredient makeup, these bars are nearly half the price as some of the other bars I've seen on the market. Would highly recommend this product.

review_headline: These are NOT flip top packages!
review_body: I'm so annoyed!  I got these on Subscribe and Save since they took away my Pampers option and these are no better! HOWEVER, I'm incredibly nit-picky about packaging and this packaging is the worst!  First of all, I need individual packs of wipes with a flip-top, NOT a resealable closure, because those are never actually resealable.  Not only are these wipes NOT packaged with a flip top, the packages that they do come in won't fit in the provided tub.  Meaning, the packs are about double what fits in the tub so either you have to hope you have another tub laying around or you have to tape the remaining wipes closed so they don't dry out. product_title: Gray Riddance - 4 Fluid Ounces, Spray Bottle
review_body:
I previously gave this product quite bad review and feel a bit guilty now. It DOES work BUT in my case it took 1 week, not 3 days as suggested by manufacturer. And my grays did not turn light brown or even golden, they turned very pale blond with some yellow shade to them. It would be alright but in my case all grays are based around my hair line so I look a bit odd with very light blond front and sides of the head while the rest of my hair are darker (I am dark blond). I still managed to make it work by adding light highlights to my hair, just something extra I had to do.
However somebody else I know with very fine hair who used this product got nice golden blond locks (again not light brown) within 3 days so maybe there is issue with my hair as my hair is quite thick.
I will be buying this product again as I still think its better than cover all hair with commercial dye while I only have gray hair around hair line. I also noticed the effect lasts longer (2 months) than any commercial dye I used so I am giving an extra star for that.

Pros:
Easy to apply
Targets gray hair only
Free from harsh ingredients (comparing to commercial dyes)
Good option for people who have grays here and there and trying to avoid colouring the whole head

Cons:
Colour is not intense (my grays turned very very light blond, not light brown or golden as stated by manufacturer)
Took me a week of application to get some colour into grays, 3 days did not make any difference
This product stains badly so be sure to wear gloves and clean the face after each application (also I would recommend buying cheap pillow and pillow cover as mine turned all yellow)
Have to plan hair wash to make sure there are at least 18 hours between each application

review_body: I wanted the Fitbit Charge HR to help me get started on my exercise program.  I have owned other Fitbit items in the past. It also will connect with your smartphone (I have an iPhone) to sync your information, as well as to notify you when you have a call.  So far it has worked great.  When you sync the device with a smartphone or computer, you get more detailed information, graphs, and recommendations.  And Fitbit will work with the My Fitness Pal app to track your exercise. review_headline: Smaller pill so easier to swallow
review_body:
I volunteer at a house for homeless pregnant women and a lot of these girls don't get the vitamins they need while pregnant. The girl that I got these for is in her first trimester and so the morning sickness, really all day sickness, is terrible. As we all know, it's really important to get the vitamins to your unborn child but for anyone that has suffered from sickness, knows that easier said than done. These pills are smaller than the other ones that she was supposed to be taking. That's a huge pro because they are easier to swallow and don't trigger her gag reflex. There also wasn't that terrible smell that is usually associated with vitamins. She also said that these didn't upset her stomach, which is normally empty because of the vomiting. These were exactly what she needed and she can no have confidence that her baby is getting what it needs. I can't recommend these enough for anyone looking for a great prenatal vitamin.

product_title: Amazing Nutrition Norwegian Fish Oil - 16 Oz (473 Ml) * Purest & Best Quality Fish Oil, Extracted Under Strict Quality Standards From Around the Waters of Norway * Rich in Omega-3 Fatty Acids * Supports Cardiovascular Health, Brain Health, Respiratory Health, Eye Health & Overall Well-being * Fresh Orange Flavor to Avoid Fishy Aftertaste
review_headline: A great way to maximize Omega 3s
review_body:
We recognize that our diet, as hard as we try, is most likely deficient in many key nutrients. One that we recognize is Omega 3. We are loving the Omega 3 Fish Oil supplement. It's high dosage, and I feel helps keep our diets more balanced. Fish Oil is a supplement I believe in. Studies show that it may help with joints, the mind and the heart. I received this product at a discounted rate in exchange for an honest review. All opinions are my own. My dad has been taking fish oil for thirty years and swears it's what keeps his joints moving and his mind sharp.

I recently switched from capsules to the liquid form and I am loving it. I read about the varying amounts of EPA/DHA and found this information from Omega3 innovations website:
One regular fish oil capsule – Around 300mg of EPA/DHA
One capsules of krill oil – Around 75mg of EPA/DHA
One teaspoon of liquid fish oil – 1200 mg of EPA/DHA
One high concentrate fish oil capsule – Up to 600mg EPA/DHA.
A normal-size serving of salmon fillet – Up to 3000mg EPA/DHA (depending on the time of year, how it is prepared and where it is coming from)
If you look closely at this table, a few facts should jump out. First and foremost, one teaspoon of liquid fish oil contains about four times as much EPA/DHA as one fish oil capsule. And, more shockingly, to get as much omega-3 as you would from eating a salmon fillet for dinner, you’d have to consume a minimum of 10 fish oil capsules! In other words, taking one capsule doesn’t give you much more than a bite or two of salmon. That’s hardly enough!
This Norwegian Fish Oil is smooth, doesn't have a fishy taste and I don't notice an aftertaste. It is easy to take, in my opinion.

product_title: Ball of Foot Cushions - Metatarsal Pads 1 Pair Insoles - Provide Support and Relief to Metatarsalgia, Mortons Neuroma, and Sesamoiditis Pain
review_body:
Most attractive shoes are not comfortable and there is no getting around that.

Kate Middleton wears heels all the time and it turns out she is wearing inserts as well with one of the keys being not allowing your foot to slip back and forth. The ball of your foot is cushioned and your heel and toes are not being rubbed back and forth over blistering and callousing surfaces. Zoomie's fit that bill and the silicone feels good on the foot without knocking you out of alignment in your shoes.

For me, I think the advantage of Zoomie's is that silicone doesn't break down easily and resists the effects of overheated feet or getting your shoes wet. My samples to review are holding up well and are doing what I hoped they would.

One caveat, in order to not slide back and forth in your shoes, these are adhesive backed and will be staying in your shoes. You will need more than one pair to switch back and forth, each pair of shoes will need their own but that seems a fair trade, given how many shoes I won't wear because they aren't comfortable enough and other inserts have not done the trick.

I got this because mid-colitis flare-up I was badly dehydrated and anemic and needed a way to boost my minerals without pills (iron supplements usually hurt my stomach, and I can't take pills anyway.) So I ordered this and have been double-dosing on it daily for a few days to help get my blood levels back to normal. I put it in my aloe vera juice for my ulcers and it neutralizes the icky flavor of the aloe vera juice. The results have been good so far. My stomach doesn't object to it, my energy levels are closer to normal, and I'm pretty sure that I'm going to be able to cut back to a maintenance dose soon. It's no cure for colitis by any means but it is definitely a good tool in my arsenal of surviving the flare-up (and might even help long-term with other low-energy problems I can get related to anemia/thyroid/etc...that remains to be seen.)

review_body:
I got this for urinary tract infection. The ad on Amazon said it was once daily, but the bottle suggested 2 or 3 a day when a UTI is present. That means I used the whole bottle up in just 2 weeks. I wasn't sure if that would be enough time to knock out the infection, but once I finished the round of pills, I could see improvement.

I used cranberry juice during the time I was taking the probiotics. It reduced the urgency and burning and now after another week has gone by since taking all the pills, the UTI seems to be gone. Just to prevent any flare-up, I'm continuing to drink cranberry juice with a little vinegar in it. I'm also taking a daily supplement now of cranberry in capsule form.

This product really helps with my digestion, i.e. no gas or bloating after eating foods with high carbohydrate content such as pastas, wheat products or veggies. I have to read up on what ATPro exactly is though. And it's the best selling enzyme in the nation!!

http://enzymedica.com/products/digest-gold-enzymes-digestive-enzyme

Enzyme deficiencies may result from a combination of age, diet and lifestyle. These deficiencies can lead to a variety of digestive discomforts, including occasional gas, bloating, indigestion and irregularity.

Digest Gold™ is an advanced formula that breaks down carbohydrates, fats, fiber and protein.* The enzymes in Digest Gold support optimal digestion by helping the body absorb nutrients and convert food into energy.* Digestive well-being improves concentration and increases vitality.* Digest Gold is an excellent choice for individuals seeking a high-potency enzyme formula.

Recommended Use: 1 capsule with each meal. More may be taken as needed.

†According to SPINS, a market research and consulting firm for the Natural Products Industry

NO FILLERS ADDED

Many people choose to supplement their diet with a high-potency enzyme formula to relieve occasional digestive discomfort.* A powerful enzyme product may be helpful for individuals with digestive complaints.* Enzymes are key players in the digestive process. They help to maximize nutrient extraction and turn consumed food into energy. Enzyme deficiencies can lead to a variety of digestive discomforts, including occasional gas, bloating, indigestion and irregularity.

These deficiencies may result from a combination of age, diet and lifestyle. For example, natural aging depletes the amount of enzymes available for use in the body. And when foods are cooked or processed, the enzymes contained within the food are destroyed, requiring the body to use its own enzymes to break down foods. Keeping up with the process of digestion can strain the body. Supplementing with enzyme products like Digest Gold™ can aid in the digestive process.*

Digest Gold is the most potent formula on the market.‡ The broad range of enzymes included in Digest Gold supports optimal digestion by helping the body absorb nutrients and convert food into energy.* Digest Gold contains amylase, lipase, cellulase and protease Thera-blend™ enzymes, for breaking down carbohydrates, fats, fiber and protein, respectively. Thera-blend is an exclusive process that combines multiple strains of enzymes that work in various pH levels. Thera-blend enzymes have been shown to be three times stronger and work more than six times faster than leading digestive supplements.* For more information, visit www.enzymedica.com.

ATP (Adenosine triphosphate) is produced in every cell and is found in all raw foods. Without ATP, nutrients would not be able to pass through the cell membrane, so it allows cells to benefit from the nutrition in food. A combination of natural aging, lack of exercise and eating cooked and processed foods can significantly increase the demand to produce large amounts of ATP, making it difficult for the body to keep up. Even those living a healthy lifestyle may be challenged with a constant state of energy deficiency. A digestive supplement that provides ATP and enhances ATP production may help offset such a deficiency.*

The ATPro™ Blend in Digest Gold is a combination of ATP, Magnesium Citrate, Alpha Lipoic Acid and CoQ10. Research has shown that ATP is present in the digestive tract by oral intake (unprocessed foods carry ATP) and it is used as a signaling molecule for many important processes. This signal is vital for timely, proper and complete digestion of food.*1 Digest Gold contains 300,000,000 LCUs of ATP per capsule. Combining a full spectrum of digestive enzymes with ATPro, Digest Gold offers unsurpassed digestive support and is the #1 selling digestive enzyme formula on the market.*†

product_title: Sebamed everyday shampoo, for all hair types and sensitive scalp,  6.8 Fluid Ounce Bottle
review_headline: Excellent shampoo, no dyes, soaps or perfumes.
review_body:
Expensive, but fantastic shampoo. Recently bought my second bottle. It's the only shampoo I've found that improves my scaly scalp condition. Anti-dandruff shampoos have only ever made things worse, in addition to making my wiry hair even more crispy and frizzy. Maybe my issue was traditional soap ingredients all along?

The small bottle lasted longer than expected. I've found that adding a bit of warm water before lathering, or REALLY soaking your hair works best. I have very thick, but short hair. I still only need about a tablespoon to get my hair clean. If I've been exercising or doing yard work, and got especially sweaty, I will wash a second time.

I use Aussie 3-Minute Miracle Smooth conditioner with this. I haven't found anything better. I typically wash my hair every other day. If I don't use too much conditioner on my scalp, my hair is still clean and shiny well into the second day.

I also like that this product has almost no scent, which is great if you don't care for strong perfumes.

It may also be worth noting that I regularly dye my hair to cover grays, and have seen no change with this shampoo, so it appears to be at least relatively dye-friendly.

product_title: 3m Tegaderm Transparent Film Dressing 2.375" x 2.75"/Picture Frame Style/Package of 20
review_headline: it can stay on for a long time even over very active joints like knees and elbows
review_body: As a mountain biker, I hurt myself a lot (hence my name), so I have an arsenal of medical care products with me at all times.  Tegaderm films are always in my first aid kit.  FIlm has enough stretch in it that, if applied correctly, it can stay on for a long time even over very active joints like knees and elbows.  About the only time this film has difficult time staying on is when the wound is more than mildly exudating, but even then, I use this film and just change it frequently as it gets soaked.  Eventually exudating will start to subside and the film will stay on longer.  Watching your skin regrow underneath the transparent film is like science project and it's fascinating!

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_body:
i have suspected that my Charge HR has not been recording an accurate heart rate since i got it. today at the gym I used the heart monitor on the biking equipment and my Fitbit topped out at 100 while the gym equipment showed 140. During this test I readjusted and re positioned the Fitbit several times and the result has been the same. When I contacted Fitbit chat support this is what i was told. (Willian is the Fitbit chat support "specialist")

Willian: Take in consideration that the equipment from your Gym don't take in consideration your gender, age, height and weight to calculate your Heart rate.
You: isn't heart rate a somple count of beats per minute?
Willian: The algorithms in both devices are different. We have performed multiple internal studies to rigorously test the accuracy of PurePulse against other equipment and we see only a small percentage difference across a variety of workouts.
You: so is my fitbit working properly?
Willian: Yes your Fitbit Charge is working properly.
Keep in mind that for someone of my height, age, and weight the calorie calculator at beachbody.com told me I burned approx. 700 calories while doing the the Kenpo X workout. My new Fitbit has cut that caloric count in half. If this is how they designed it then the Charge HR is a bust and you should look into some of the other fitness trackers. I know I am.

product_title: Green Coffee Bean Extract
review_headline: 800mg Per Capsule AND Standardized for Chlorogenic Acid
review_body:
This is my second bottle that I've order, the first bottle was 60 capsules, but I decided to get the whole shebang this time with 180 capsules. Admittedly, I did 'fall off' my eating and exercise plan for a bit while I was taking the first batch, but I managed to lose 3lbs nonetheless within that month; I took two capsules before lunch and two capsules before dinner. This go around, I endeavor to stay consistent with eating the necessary portions and getting adequate exercise. The main reasons I chose to get the second bottle is: A): It is standardized for Chlorogenic Acid, which is the active ingredient in Green Coffee Bean Extract products; regardless of which brand you use, just make sure that it is standardized for this ingredient as many brands are not standardized. B): I am especially happy that there are 800 mg per capsule - I used to use a different brand and it was only 400 mg per capsule, so I had to take more of them, which I was not a fan of doing. C): No fillers - just the GCB and the veggie capsule.

All in all, I am pleased with this product and brand.

product_title: GermGuardian AC4900CA 3-in-1 Air Purifier with True HEPA Filter, UV-C Sanitizer, Captures Allergens, Smoke, Odors, Mold, Dust, Germs, Pets, Smokers, 22-Inch Germ Guardian Air Purifier
review_headline: Works great - slightly quieter than comparable units
review_body: I have bad allergies and sinus problems.  I've gone through many air purifiers and like to put them in multiple rooms.  I just moved back in with my mother to help out.  My room is smaller, so I needed something a little smaller than what I was previously using in my bedroom.  The GermGuardian AC4900CA is larger than the typical small room units, but it has a smaller footprint than typical medium room units.  This works out well for me.  I also have a dog that has allergies.  Her eyes water really bad and she scratches.  A lot of the scratching is from outdoor allergies, so that can't really be helped by an air purifier/filter.  However, since using this unit (over a month), her eyes are watering less.  My allergies seem better, too.  Odors disappear much  quicker.  There are 3 dogs total in the house and they often may follow me into my room throughout the day.  Only my one dog sleeps in the room.  Even though the dogs are bathed often, they still have "doggy" smells.  I've noticed that has minimized since I started using this unit.    Upkeep/maintenance is fairly simple.  You vacuum the filters once a month and replace them about twice a year.  This is very reasonable.  So far, I love my GermGuardian and was glad to be able to find a great unit smaller than my "go to" larger unit to fit my new bedroom.   Also, the sound is lower than my other unit.   I don't mind noise from air purifiers, because I also use a sound machine (set to white noise), in addition to the sound of the purifier.  Most people may want to use a lower setting than high when they sleep, if they use it in their bedroom.  I, however, am fine with it on high.

product_title: Ivation Oral Irrigator Compact Countertop Water Flosser - with 5 Interchagneable Tips, 2 Jets, Tongue Cleaner, Pocket, Orthodontic & Plaque Seeker
review_headline: Very good, easy-to-use item  promoting dental hygiene
review_body:
I am a big fan of water flossing, because it feels much better than running a piece of string between your teeth in hopes of proper dental care. It is also much friendlier for individuals with sensitive gums, and it is a lot nicer when you have hardware in your mouth and do not want an expensive filling or crown coming out because string flossing caused it to give way. Additionally, it is also something that kids enjoy and that mixes up the flossing routine, so you can have them standing with you and enjoying flossing while also promoting proper dental hygiene.

When switching from standard floss to irrigation, this can seem a little overwhelming and especially so when unpacking and trying to adjust to "when to hit the trigger" and "when to stop the water flow." This does not take that much time to adjust to, however, so do not feel intimidated by the switch. The Ivation Oral Irrigator is the third water irrigator I have tried out, too, and it is my favorite so far because of a few things including the fact that it has a lot of features I think will appeal to both new users and older hands.

First, the Ivation model is put together really well and seems as though it will last. Ivation has been really good about withstanding random abuse within our home, and I note that owning more than a few of their items so I feel confident it will do well. With regard to this, I also think the overall design is very user-friendly. I like the fact that it has a good storage set-up allotted on the side and plenty of water storage at the top, plus the lid has plenty of storage for the extra tools. The off/on switch is easy to locate and the pressure dial is marked really well and easy to use.

Second, it actually comes with instructions that note useful items plus some mildly entertaining safety information.
Do not use in the bathtub, with mouth jewelry, if the plug is damaged, or handle the plug if your hands are wet. Do not spray it in your ears, nose of other delicate areas. Do not use more than five minutes per two hours. Do not immerse the unit.
These warnings are combined with a brief note on set-up, first, and regular use, plus tips. Honestly, I found this helpful and entertaining/ scary when I think about people doing some of the things these warn against, and am happy to have some actual, physical instructions when using something the first time.

Third, this has multiple settings for pressure control, ranging from 1 - 10. I had another than ranged the same types of pressure but in three settings, and this is a lot more user-friendly. It really helped me figure out exactly what settings work for myself and my family.

Fourth, this has a lot of accessories intended to help, including a tangle-resistant cord, multiple tools, and so much more. The tools clip on very easily and they detach equally well, making the whole unit simple to use and to clean.

Fifth, speaking of cleaning, I like the fact that this makes cleaning easy, too, because this has been one issue with former units that I tried out and you do not want any issue related to cleaning and items that house water and end up in your mouth.

Please note that this was provided for sampling purposes and was tested for a period of 20 days before reviewing. All opinions are my own, and I like the item and Ivation quite a bit.it in your ears, nose of other delicate areas. Do not use more than five minutes per two hours. Do not immerse the unit.

product_title: Vitamin World Triple Omega 3-6-9 Supplement, 120 Count
review_headline: great when recovering from a chronic illness where digestive comfort is a must.
review_body:
Omega 3 fish oils are so cardio protective that once we shared this with our cardiologist and he did further investigating, he called back to instruct us to take THREE "fish pills" daily instead of the ONE "fish pill" daily he presumed we were taking. Vitamin World's Triple Omega is a good source of fish oil ( Omega 3 essential oil.)

Omega 6 oils are found in more traditional sources of oils such as canola oil (aka rapeseed oil ) Usually these oils are adequate in the standard American Diet but my husband recently experienced a seasonal long illness that turned out to be a ginormous kidney stone. In a case such as his situation where he's avoided most sources of foods in recent months his LDL and HDL cholesterol are both so low we need to supplement Omega 6 as well.

Omega 9 oils are generally manufactured in the human body so are not considered essential fatty acids.

In my husband's case of not eating enough for a longer duration, he's needing to supplement with the whole array to ensure he's receiving enough of each nutrient, particularly essential fatty acids.
