product_title: Withings Wireless Blood Pressure Monitor for Apple and Android
review_headline: I am happy I chose this over the Qardio brand
review_body:
I am in my early 50s and recently been diagnosed with mildly high blood pressure levels by my physician. This is after a lifetime of having perfect blood pressure (and I am in the best physical shape of my life).

I had been planning for quite some time to purchase one of these wireless blood pressure monitors and was keeping an eye on the reviews for the Qardio brand that is also sold on Amazon. However, after all the negative reviews over hardware and sync failures with that brand, I knew I had to look at something else. Actually, what finally drove me to Withings was the 5-star reviews of its app on the iTunes store. There's nothing worse than a strong product that comes with a lousy iOS/Android app. Fortunately, Withings comes through with flying colors in both departments.

Out of box, setup was easy. With batteries already loaded, I simply hit the bluetooth button on the cuff and paired it with my Apple phone. I would recommend that purchasers install the app first, launch it, and have it walk you through the process.

I would also recommend that before you hit the START button on the app and take your first reading, to click on the settings icon on the upper corner of the app and have it automatically take three readings to average out your readings.

I was pleasantly surprised, using the enclosed instruction booklet, how easy it is to place this cuff above the elbow, wrap, and take a reading. It's really effortless. The results are not only sent to my iOS device, but readings are logged within the app and can easily be shared or emailed to my physician.

Have not had to change the batteries yet, so I don't know how difficult that process will be. There is a screw at the bottom of the cuff tube to access the batteries, though I am concerned about it becoming stripped over time. I would be very, very gentle with any coin used to open it.

I also, at the time of purchase of this Blood Pressure monitor, put the Withings Body Scale in my cart. At the last minute, I removed it due to a few negative reviews and the mention that there is no customer support from this company. That is concerning. However, now that I have seen the Withings app in action and the fact that it supports all their fitness products, I have gone ahead and ordered the body scale. It's kind of cool that I can track my weight gain/loss and blood pressure numbers all in one app, sent wirelessly, without me having to do anything than just use the products.

So far, I am very happy with this Blood Pressure Monitor. If I have any problems I will come back and update the review.re monitor, put the Withings Body Scale in my cart. product_title: Drive Medical DV8 Aluminum Steerable Knee Walker Crutch Alternative
review_headline: Love it. Get around if have any foot problems.
review_body: My nephew fixed it so I've changed this review from three stars to five stars. A friend and I had assembled it improperly which is ridiculous because assembly is simple and straight forward. What can I say? While I'm able to put weight on my foot at the moment, I'm happy to have it back in use for the ride down the hall to my bedroom. I've already ordered another one so I'll keep one in the car.   I noticed the less then stellar reviews. Here's what I'll say in response, crutches are more treacherous. If someone is having problems they're either attempting to move around too fast or should be in a wheel chair. I'd probably set one brake in order to slow the scooter down if someone is having trouble controlling it. The instructions clearly state it works better indoors, not outdoors. I'll keep one in my car for emergency assistance but will not attempt to use it like a regular scooter. This is designed as medical assistance not a toy. I haven't had any stability problems and my house has laminate, linoleum, rugs, and carpet with a couple of high floor mouldings separating the varying materials. This handles it all well because of the big wheels. I anticipate I'll have to move much slower outside my home.   The only problem I have is my knees and shins are a little sore from using it for several days. The padding is adequate but let's face it, we  weren't designed to be on our knees and shins for extended periods of time, especially those of us overweight. I suggest icing your knees and shins when you'll be down for a while.   Original review:  It was opened and assembled too late to return or exchange. The steering column thingy wasn't quite right and now it's broken and unusable.  HOWEVER, I've used it twice during week plus inability to use my right foot. I'm 5'6 and 250, I needed something that could handle my weight and fully adjustable and a seat well padded because this is a lot of weight to put on one leg. I have flare ups of metatarsals and now plantar fasciitis.  This was great fun to scoot around on. Very stable, good brakes, and reasonably comfortable. I use a canvas bag to cart supplies back and forth. We couldn't get it to fold down or I would have taken it with me a couple times when my knee hurt or left foot hurt or whatever other pain this old body made me woefully aware of.  Regardless of three star rating, I'm going to order another one and have someone more mechanically inclined assemble it immediately. If all goes well I'll be back to change the stars from three to five.

product_title: BedCare Classic Low Profile Cover Queen 60x80 (5-7" deep)
review_headline: Fantastic to find a "low profile" allergen barrier that works on our clasic futon mattress
review_body:
We have an old, classic futon and needed an allergen barrier that would fit it. Most of the barriers available are sized for the new super-thick mattresses, so I was very pleased to find this "low profile" one. It fits our futon nicely and was not too difficult to wrestle onto the futon, with two of us working.

My only disappointment was that it is not made of tightly woven fabric which is membrane-free. It has a membrane on the inner side of the fabric. We've had one of those before, and eventually the membrane does tear, at which point one must replace the allergen barrier.

When the membrane in the allergen barriers on our pillows tore, we replaced them with membrane-free allergen barriers and have been very pleased.

We did not return the mattress allergen barrier, because the "low profile" size is so hard to find, and it will do the job needed. But we will have to monitor the integrity of the membrane and then replace the barrier when it tears, probably in 10 years or so.

product_title: Prism Glasses, Prism Eye Glasses or Bed Prism Spectacles
review_headline: No more neck pain, I hope...
review_body:
I was really skeptical about this product, but I was given an Amazon gift card with instructions to spend it on "something frivolous." For a while now I've been trying to pay more attention to how much time I spend with my neck bent at a painful angle. One of the most distinct culprits is the time I spend reading either sitting or laying down. If I try to hold the book at my eye level, my arms get tired pretty fast. Any other position hurts my neck after a fairly short time. I have been considering this product as a possible-though slightly ridiculous-solution. I haven't yet tried them out for a long period, but the angle is dead on to read comfortably without bending my neck out of shape.

Two negative thoughts, at the outset; The eye pieces are slightly farther apart then my eyes, giving me a grey line in the middle of my vision. This could lead to a headache, but I'm not sure it will yet. Also, I will not be able to put them over my glasses, so I'll have to take out my contacts after I finish if I want to read before bed. Not ideal, but definitely an upgrade from neck pain leading to day-long headaches.

product_title: Finish All In 1 Gelpacs, Orange 96 Tabs (3 Packs x 32 Tabs), Dishwasher Detergent Tablets
review_headline: Stick with "harsh" chemicals, avoid fruit/nature themes.
review_body: I purchased a 96 ct. based solely upon the performance of their 3-in-1 powerball tablets.  I think that's right... I don't have a box to double-check.  Those worked really well.  Surprisingly well.  Enough for me to trust that these would be comparable.  They are not.  I don't think the smell is so much a problem - I haven't noticed a smell that is more annoying than the 3-in-1 tablets, but the discoloration on the dishes and in the dishwasher is unbearable.  Using these has been rather sketchy, because you can't be sure your stuff is clean, versus rinsed with really hot water and perfumed, especially when bits of food debris linger when with the tablets there was nothing left except for your dishes.  I will go back to the tablets, until they eventually stink on ice, too.  Personally, I blame the environmental alarmists making a push to less harsh chemicals.  I think you should want a chemical that is harsh in a dish washing machine - otherwise stick with mild soaps and detergents and wash by hand, like with knives or other delicates.  The whole point of such a machine is that you don't have to worry about whether or not your dishes are clean of food debris AND harmful bugs, for which you need intense heat, powerful jets of water, and harsh chemicals.

product_title: Rosemary Essential Oil, 4 oz - 100% Pure & Natural
review_body:
Essential oils are kind of "my thing" so when I find good quality, large quantity and great price combined in one, I get excited as if it was the night before Christmas and I was 6 again. Rosemary oil is in my top ten to have on hand at all times. There are so many uses for it that I just can't stand running out. I think one of the most important reasons that I try to keep it stocked is hair. THe females in my house all have long hair.

Guess what time of year it is? Yup. Back to school. Unfortunately, there is a not so exciting thing that comes with back to school when you have kids that are elementary aged. Between now (Early September) and early spring the dreaded head lice tend to make the rounds around the school. I make a diluted spray using the rosemary oil and fresh mint that keeps them away from my girls' hair and smells really good. I don't think I'm supposed to include the mixture here, but if you look in your favorite search engine under rosemary oils applications and mint, you should find it or one similar to it. There are a million other ways to use rosemary oil, but I really think that this is the most important one for a young family.

product_title: Variant Pack Easy@home 12 Panel Urine Drug Test Cup for 12 Different Drugs
review_body:
When I was recently given the opportunity to receive this product for a discounted price in exchange for my review and honest opinion I of course jumped at the chance. I had been looking into purchasing drug tests for about a month for a few different reasons.
I'll be honest anyone that is reading this review has their own personal reason as to why they are considering purchasing a product like this. Whether it is to be used to test potential employees for pre employment purposes, giving your child or other family member a random surprise test(for whatever reason), or somebody just wanting to check their own levels in advance before taking an official test elsewhere. I am writing this to hopefully help you with your decision process by giving my opinion on the product.
So here are my thoughts and experience on and with this product.... Like I said I purchased this product for my own personal reasons and I was very happy with my purchase. I chose the 5 cup option but you have the choice of a 5, 10, 25, 50, and even 100 pack. These cups work very well and are pretty much dummy proof. You just open the foil package that the are each individually packaged in, unscrew the cap and pee into the cup. You then peel back a tab to check your results. Another thing I really liked about these cups is that they test for such a wide range of things 12 different drugs so you can always be sure and clear about what someone does or does not have in their system. The results starts showing almost immediately I think it took less than 2 mins to see the full results. One line is positive and two lines is negative.
Just to be sure that this test worked properly and accurately I of course (being the kind of person I am) had found and asked someone who I knew had certain substances in their system(ones that I knew this test checked for) to take the test for me so I could really test it out. And like stated the test had very fast and accurate results.
I was verypleased with this product and I would definitely recommend this to others. If you are reading this review trying to decide whether or not to purchase I say go for it you will not regret this purchase.

review_headline: it tastes just like molasses, to me
review_body: Right now I am giving this 4 stars, because of the congealing issues. I do not know if it works as intended yet, because I just got it. What I want to talk about is the complaints about the congealing. I almost didn't buy it because of those issues. People say they don't get the full 8 oz. because they can't get it out of the bottom of the bottle due to congealing. Well, I followed the company's advice & when I got it, I shook it well & used a long knife(because I didn't have a skewer, as they recommended). I stirred it around in the bottom even digging at the sides & bottom edges to loosen it. I decided to pour it up to see how much I got & after about 5 tries, scraping & shaking & even beating the bottle upside down in a bowl, I ended up with 8 1/2 oz of product in my small sandwich zippy bag. (minus of course the weight of the bag). I am going to store it in the bag, so I can hopefully knead the lumps out eat time I use it, hopefully getting to use the whole bottle. You can see when you look at my photos, that it still has some lumps in the bottom of the bag. But, anyway, if this stuff works, as they say it does. It's totally worth that effort to me. If I'm able to come back later & review the effectiveness, I will. By the way, it tastes just like molasses, to me. :)

product_title: SKALD
review_body:
I was simply amazed.

I came across Beldt while trying to decide on a thermogenic to help with dieting. I was wary of Hydroxycut and the bad reputation it garnered over the years. I first heard about this while examining Shred Matrix from Musclepharm, and a came across a recommendation for Beldt's cleaner ingredients and single pill serving.

I used this product in conjunction with moderate exercise and light dieting. Within a month I was down a full twenty pounds. I felt incredibly energetic during the day for periods of around fourteen hours, which still left me plenty tired. I didn't suffer any crashes or jitters, as I avoided most other sources of stimulants. The energy felt really clean and long lasting, letting me stay alert and focused even while bodily exhausted.

I only needed a single pill per day, as I had some stomach unsettling using two while testing for tolerance. It is important to note that the item is a very potent diuretic. My water intake was almost two gallons a day, and every twenty to thirty minutes I needed to seek a lavatory. Best avoided during long trips, when bathrooms may be scarce. I lost approximately eight pounds the first week as it drained me of excess water weight, but not immediately bouncing back kept me in high spirits while I further progressed.

I give this product a full recommendation if you are looking for a little extra boost to get on the path to a healthier lifestyle.

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_headline: Fine as a Casual Gadget -- Not for Runners
review_body:
It's okay.

First off, I returned mine. I didn't return it just because it was only okay, but because it kept a charge for less than a day and caused my phone to quickly discharge, too. It also had a very hard time syncing, often not finding the device when they were close or even touching. When I called Fitbit tech support, they didn't offer a technical solution, but instead said it should be replaced or returned.

Why I chose to return instead of replace:
Before I started running with my Fitbit Charge HR, I would run with my phone to keep accurate distance and for interval training cues.
After I started running with my Fitbit Charge HR, I would run with my phone to keep accurate distance and for interval training cues.
The net effect here was that I was just wearing one more device, which wasn't what I was hoping to achieve. My phone was already able to track my sleep, count my steps, and track distance accurately.

So what DID the Fitbit Charge HR add?
It did add heart rate monitoring, but the effect was disappointing. Garmin offers watches that not only track heart rate, but then do something with it by giving you cues to keep you in a target zone. They also have training programs (including interval training). Polaris does as well (using a chest strap). Even Fitbit's top of the line watch, the Surge, does not offer anything like this. It seems as if Fitbit doesn't truly recognize the usefulness of what HR monitoring provides, thus missing the mark, almost entirely.

Conclusion:
If you just want to compare steps with friends, this is a fine option with the additional advantage of doing some neat-o activity charting. But if you are at all serious about running for health and limiting yourself to one gadget while running (and maybe a second for music), you'll want to look at a more serious fitness watch like the Garmin Forefunner 225 ($300) or any of the many that use the significantly more accuratechest strap HR monitor.

Did Sasquatch help you make a decision? If so, mark him helpful.

product_title: iHealth BP5 Wireless Blood Pressure Monitor for iPhone and Android
review_headline: I tried to set this up on an Android phone, a tablet, & iPad. Twice. Repeated "Device not found" message on phone & iPad.
review_body:
I charged the battery of the BP cuff, downloaded the app both on the iPad and on my Android phone and my daughter's Android tablet, and paired the Bluetooth. I put the cuff on and turned it on and tried to take a reading. Nada. The iPad, phone, and tablet all returned the same message: device not found.

So.....I double checked to see if the Bluetooth pairing had gone through (it had). Then I went back to ground zero: I deleted the app from all three, turned the devices off, and turned them back on and reloaded the app, re-paired the Bluetooth, trying the phone first, then the iPad, then the tablet, this time deleting the app and turning off the phone, iPad, and Galaxy tablet when each one did not work.

I will try to get the device to work on ANY of the three devices one more time within a few days when I have an additional chunk of spare time and the frame of mind to deal with multiple devices and recurrent frustration. But for now, I must make the obvious point: a blood pressure monitor that will not connect with your phone or tablet(s) is useless.

UPDATE: I was able to get this to work TWICE (two separate occasions) on my Android tablet. I have NO idea why it finally decided to work.....and why it doesn't when it doesn't (even on the tablet). No luck whatsoever on phone or iPad

product_title: NOW Red Mineral Algae,180 Veg Capsules
review_headline: Great calcium supplement, with other good minerals
review_body:
I'm a vegetarian and I don't like milk very much, so I thought this would be a great way to get my calcium. Plus, I've been trying a bunch of other different kinds of algae products, and I found that this is a great way to get both my algae and vitamins for the day. I think that they just mine the vitamins out of the algae, because the capsules are completely white, and not red at all. At the same time, the minerals aren't overprocessed, because you have to take four big capsules to get 100% of your RDA of calcium out of these. It also has vitamin D and magnesium, and a lot of other trace minerals.

product_title: ReliefX 4oz. Pain Relief Cream with Arnica - May Help Relieve Soreness in Muscles, Joints, Feet and Lower Back
review_headline: Strangely effective, whether placebo or not.
review_body:
Here's an odd review for you. This is a product that I am not sure works, but I suspect it does. Pain management of joints is a tricky thing and I have yet to find a cream or ointment that immediately removes the pain completely. However, this is a product that actually masked the pain somewhat or that made us believe that it was indeed working. This has a gentle and faint aroma, unlike most ointments out there designed to alleviate joint pain, so when applied, we weren't sure if the product was working or if we imagined it. Either way, I would say it is a win-win situation because the pain was masked and lowered, and ultimately, that is what you seek from either the real thing or a placebo. I suppose we have been conditioned to accept that only smelly and/or malodorous ointments will help at all. Kind of like the Listerine effect where you expect your mouth to feel the burn of the alcohol to consider it effective. Anyway, you will have to be the judge on this one.

Did the positive Amazon reviews incite me to purchase in the first place? Yeah. Would I buy again? Sure. Would I recommend it? Yes, I would.

product_title: Fitbit Charge HR Wireless Activity Wristband
review_headline: Good for those who need a nudge while losing weight.
review_body:
The first thing you should know about the Fitbit Charge HR is that it won't make you lose weight. What it will do is make you aware of how much you move around and how many calories you burn.

Pros: Keeps track of your steps and mileage pretty accurately. Also tells you your heart rate. There is a website and an app that also keeps track of your stats and will help you keep track of your food intake. You can also share it with your friends and have competitions.

Cons: Doesn't accurately calculate your activity in gym classes like spin or toning classes. It will calculate some of the movement and calories. The band is not all that comfortable but you get used to it.

review_headline: It occurred in the late spring and I was confronted with losing the better part of the Midwestern golf season
review_body: I'm over 60 and never suffered with elbow tendinitis in the past.  A combination of too much upper-body strength conditioning and too much golf resulted in a fairly sever case of elbow tendinitis.  It occurred in the late spring and I was confronted with losing the better part of the Midwestern golf season.  Friends that reported the same tendinitis experience told me to expect a slow months-long recovery period that could possibly require corrective surgery. I purchased elastic and Velcro-based elbow support items.  I shopped online for analgesic solutions.  I purchased Penetrex based on reviews. I followed the manufacturers prescribed application regimen -  applied the crème about 3-4 times a day.  Of course, my healing routine included termination of strengthening exercises and golf.  After several days of the application regimen - noticeable improvement/reduction in pain. I attributed the relatively quick recovery to the combination of rest and Penetrex application.  I continued the Penetrex rehabilitation process for about 2 weeks and the tendinitis was healed.  I began playing golf without a reoccurrence.

product_title: Fitbit Zip Wireless Activity Tracker
review_headline: I actually enjoy it more than I thought I would and it's ...
review_body: I bought this thing on a whim to see what all the fuss is about.  I actually enjoy it more than I thought I would and it's holding up well.  I just changed the battery for the first time this past week (been 4 months).  A two pack of batteries at Wal*Mart (yes, they sell CR2025's at Wal*Mart) was $4.  It's small, it's discrete (I usually wear it clipped to the waist band of my skivvies).  Only thing I don't really care for with it is the food tracking section of the app.  Basically the problem with the food tracker is that there's a boat load of information in there and whether it matches up to reality is debatable (especially if you're a scam artist like me who will log the lowest calorie chocolate chip cookie when I know damn well there's more than 50 calories in each of the ones I ate).  Using it can also be clumsy and tedious to search for every scrap and bite of anything you've eaten.  If you're decent at estimating the calories in what you've eaten and don't care about having a record of each individual item then I suggest just creating your own custom "estimate food" with it set to 100 cals per "piece" and logging things that way (ie my breakfast was about 350 calories, instead of searching for and putting in toast, butter, jam, coffee, sugar, and milk I'm just going to use my custom "estimate food" and log it as 3.5 pieces).  Also the calorie "goal", where it tells you if you're "on track" for the day is aimed at people who work banker's hours, not second or third shift where you're eating breakfast at noon so keep that in mind if you're not a 9-5er.  Only other downside is it occasionally inspires me to do somewhat stupid things... like to get twice as many steps in one day as I normally would (by hiking on rough trails) and then end up hobbling around on sore legs for two days after that.

product_title: BulkSupplements Pure NAC (N-Acetyl L-Cysteine) Powder
review_headline: Great price, great service, great product.
review_body: I got these to try out and review. The package these come in is generic but sturdy. I got the vegetarian capsules as I hoped those would provide better protection against stomach acid. My main concern with some supplements is that they do not loose their benefits while passing through the stomach as most supplements are destroyed by stomach acid and you only get about 10% of their benefit. I wish the seller specified in their listing which form of their supplement offered this type of protection. From what I gathered online vegetarian capsules seem the best choice however capsules with enteric coating would be the best. I would definitely not recommend powder forms taken alone as you might not get the whole benefit of the supplement. My sample order came in a silver bag that makes it easy to protect from degrading properties of light and it also had a moisture control packet inside which was an added benefit. All in all I find this seller and product to be a great source of bulk supplements where you are actually paying for the supplement not the colorful packaging. thx Please update your listings with enteric coating info.

review_body: I have been using this instead of Gatorade for about a month, and I can't recommend it enough! I play tennis, and in the heat and humidity I was really fading, sometimes after only 30 minutes of play (I usually play singles). I thought it might be because I hadn't consumed enough carbs, hence the use of Gatorade. But I can only drink so much of that stuff before it fills me up. So out of desperation I tried this product, and it has really done the job. Since I just add it to water, I can drink much more without it filling me up. I have learned that I simply wasn't getting enough electrolytes, I really didn't need any carbs. I now drink between 2 and 3 quarts of this during a match, and I no longer feel overwhelmed by the heat or humidity. Now if I lose, I blame my racquet!

product_title: ALTIUS Pre-Workout Supplement - Naturally Sweetened - Clinically Dosed Powerhouse Formulation - Increase Energy & Focus, Enhance Endurance - Boost Strength, Pumps, & Performance - Mixed Berry Blast (14.3 OZ)
review_body:
I have been using pre-workout for about a year now and have tried many different kinds. I have been taking Altius for a few weeks now and I am very pleased with this product.
The packaging is very easy to read with all ingredients spelled out unambiguously as there are no proprietary blends. You know exactly what you are getting with each serving. Altius has excellent mixability. The powder is so fine that it takes seconds to dissolve in 10-16ounces of water. The flavor mixed berry blast is the best tasting pre-workout I have sampled. It has a very natural and pure taste that does not leave that chemically altered after taste in your mouth.
Everyone experiences pre-workout a little differently. Altius gave me a little tingling around the eyes and hands but was not overwhelming. I actually like that feeling so it did not bother me in the least. I found that Altius gives an even spread of energy. It does not have a very noticeable onset “rush”. It definitely gives me the energy and endurance I need to sustain my workout. What I am most pleased with is that it does not have a “crash” effect. I work out after 8pm at night and I need the energy assistance. Altius gives awesome pump as well.
Overall I am extremely pleased with this product. I would recommend it and would buy again.

review_body: Very pleased with this diffuser! I'm so glad I read all the reviews before ordering, as this research prompted me to buy InstaNatural. My diffuser is by my desk and it promotes a calming affect upon me (I am very high strung and need all the help I can get)...Seriously, I am eager to try various essential oils but for now, the Lavender is my fave!  Thank you very much!!
